review: I made this recipe as part of the Crock Pot challenge in ZWT 8. I did a few changes, reduced the oil  to 1 tbsp and used chives and parsley for the fresh herbs. I sauteed the onions and garlic in a pan, and added the mixture to the crock pot along with roma tomatoes. It cooked on high for 90 min and on low for 30 min. I removed the bay leaves and blended the sauce with a hand blender and added fresh herbs and tomato past. The flavour and freshness is delicious. Made by Bistro Babes.

name: dark chocolate souffle
review: Awesome, perfect consistency and a great rich chocolate flavor. It wasn't the season for fresh berries here so I topped with a few dried cranberries I'd soaked in rum along with chocolate chips and served with ice cream on the side.

name: spanish tortillitas de camarones  shrimp cakes
review: This made a lot more than what I expected! I made as directed except I put 1/4 of the batter aside before adding the shrimp and added cooked chicken to the small amount for my one son. Probably not the healthiest dish to make but darn good!!! These would be awesome for appetizers and you could use whatever you want in it. I have to admit that I loved the large chopped shrimp! Made for my fellow Chef Gone Wild for ZWT8. Thanks Annacia! :)

name: portuguese rice
review: What a nice way to jazz up plain rice with very little work and just a few ingredients. We enjoyed this rice and will make it again. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8-Spain/Portugal.

name: mediterranean corn salad
review: This was a nice and fresh salad. I opted for fresh orange and green bell peppers,  and added chives and parsley for the herb part. I also doubled the vinegar as other reviewers have suggested but I felt that something was missing, or that perhaps the chick peas were a bit out of place in the salad. Perhaps some lemon or lime juice would pick up the flavours as well. Made by Bistro Babes, for ZWT 8

name: blueberry upside down cake    pouding aux bleuets
review: *Made for Australia/NZ Swap #66*  FAST and easy !!  I used frozen berries and followed directions.  Since I was using the oven for casserole later, baked about 4 PM, and let sit in the pan til serving.  I think that allowed the juices to absorb into the cake, making it not very juicy as it would have been warm.  Found the whipped cream was gone (SHOCK), so topped with butter crunch ice cream.  DH ate TWO large bowls, and we had the rest for breakfast !  Thanks for posting, Bethie -- will be doing this frequently !!

name: french martini
review: Potent, important to chill vodka and pineapple juice prior to mixing.  The pineapple juice took this in a different direction from the usual martini, and I thoroughly enjoyed this variation.  One of these is all I can handle!  Thanks for posting, Michelle!  Made per Shelby Jo's recommendation for I Recommend Tag. 7/23/12: Comparing this to Recipe #462640 #462640, the champagne martini is more subtle; I like it better.

name: potsie s famous fried bolony sandwich
review: I made this sandwich last week, and due to glitches in the site, I have been trying to review it since then. Now on with the review, I've been making balony sandwiches for a long time( longer than I care to admit) and have never made them with sliced onion. And I have to tell you this sandwich is " True Redneck Comfort Food ",the only thing missing is an RC Cola. Thanks for posting and, " Keep Smiling :) "

name: goat cheese   pasta   asparagus   yum
review: O-M-G - this dish is absolutely sensational and a MUST try if you like goat cheese. We could not get over just how good it is; your eyes roll back in your head on the first try. I used farfalle pasta and otherwise followed the recipe to a T. Do use the grated lemon peel, it really adds depth of flavour to the dish that you will not get from lemon juice. It will be a contender for the best dish of the ZWT 8 tour. Made by a fellow Bistro Babe

name: boeuf bourguignonne beef burgundy  crock pot or not
review: I made this for ZWT 8, Bistro Babes, and it was a huge hit!  I combined everything in the crockpot at the same time and the dish turned out perfectly.  Delcious!  Thanks for sharing this recipe.

name: italian breaded tilapia
review: I made this with basa fillets and let them marinate for a few hours in the dressing before dredging them in the breadcrumb mixture. The result yielded delicious results with minimum effort. A great   make ahead meal too. Thank you!

name: purple dream
review: Oh, yummy!  Just thing after a long hard day of work!  Creamy, but with the Chambord still being the primary flavor...  Made for ZWT8

name: 5 hour beef stew
review: This was simple to throw together and put in the oven, this recipe could also be easily converted to a crock pot recipe, so you could be away all day and not heat the kitchen up. I like the addition of tomato soup to stews and it was good in this recipe, also. I love all the hearty veggies - peas, green beans, mushrooms, potatoes and I also used carrots.

name: tapenade bread  a b m
review: This is the best bread in the whole world. It has all of my favorite things in the world. I did run the dough cycle twice before finishing the bread. It is an excellent recipe and I am now so happy that I have a bread machine.

name: boeuf bourguignonne beef burgundy  crock pot or not
review: This is one heck of a recipe!  We all loved the subtle flavor of the tomato, the added bonus of the mushrooms and onions and the beef was so tender I swear I could have fed it to a toddler.  I prepared it in the crock pot and it was finished and literally so juicy and tender in just 4 1/2 hours.  The only thing missing were the pearl onions as my small area of the state just does not carry them at the market.  I will definitely be using this method again as it made a cheap tough cut of beef feel like we were eating the best there is to buy. Found and made during the ZWT8 tour.

name: portuguese spice blend
review: I used this on my salmon, today, and it was surprisingly good! It wasn't overpowering at all, and the blend was an even mix of ingredients. I have plenty of the blend left, and am looking forward to using it the fish again!

name: corn with spicy lime butter
review: My corn came without the husks already but I wanted to try the recipe anyway so I slathered the spiced butter all over the corn, wrapped it in aluminium foil and baked it as suggested. The result was the sweetest corn I have ever tasted in my life with a beautiful hint of lime, and even though I increased the amount of hot sauce it was not spicy at all but it balanced flavors expertly. Thank you!

name: agua de valencia
review: Refreshing, I could drink these all afternoon!  My pitcher was on the small side, so I couldn't fit all of the Cava sparkling wine in it with the other ingredients, so I will know better for next time.  While drinking, you only get a hint of alcohol, so this could be a dangerously beguiling drink.  Made for The Wild Bunch for ZWT8 visit in Spain.

name: french style shrimp salad
review: This salad has everything you can imagine in it, the hardest part about making this salad is gathering together all the ingredients. Only substitution I made was to use salad shrimp which are smaller and less expensive shrimps. This is a meal all by itself and we have leftovers for tomorrow. The dressing is a nice vinegarette. Next time I will try it with a different dressing, while this was good, I think a ginger based dressing might be nice.

name: citrus bubbly
review: Personal reaction: although I like all of the ingredients, the Absolut Citron was too dominant for my taste in this cocktail.  Because there was so much champagne, I noticed the lack of finesse in my Korbel Extra Dry Champagne; but if I were to use a fine champagne, I wouldn't mix it with anything else.  I am very fond of Chambord, so I would probably boost the amount of that liqueur, and then my champagne selection would not matter as much.  With my rating scale, if I were to alter the recipe, I would give it 3 stars.  Give this a taste test and form your own opinion.  Made for The Wild Bunch of ZWT8 for its stop in France.

name: prego no po   garlic nailed steak in a bun   portugal
review: Though the recipe is missing some ingredients in how to prepare it , I muddled through and it was delicious. I sprinked cumin onto the steak then pounded in the garlic. I added the chili pepper to the onion and wine and skipped the tomato paste because it seemed like an odd addition. We ate this without the roll  but it would make a great sandwhich with a nice garlic aioli. DH likes his steak well done, so after searing the second side I tossed in the onions and let it cook on low for a while then added in the wine to let it braise.  I like rare which , was hard to do because the steak wasn't thick enough to pound and still not overcook it a bit - still it came out quite tasty! Next time I will start with a nice thick steak for me! Thanks BK for another great recipe. Made for ZWT 8 by one of The Wild Bunch

name: yogurt hollandaise sauce
review: This went so well with my scrambled egg whites on an English muffin. And surprisingly it even went well with my vegetable salad. It was so good, and I felt guilt free for having this.

name: spanish meatballs with green olives
review: We loved the combination of the salty and tangy olives with the meatballs.  I made extra meatballs and froze them so we could have this again.  Thanks for posting!  Made for the Lively Lemon Lovelies, ZWT8.

name: chocolate almond ice cream topping
review: Oh yum, oh yum, oh yum! Seven of us gave this amazing sauce a test drive. Don't change a thing -- unless you need to make a double, triple or quadruple batch. That said, if you want to, I suppose you could replace the almond with some other extract flavour. It's nice to have a from-scratch recipe for an item you usually buy ready-made. Thanks very much for posting.

name: steamed eggs  kai meung
review: Thanks to Connie Lea's recommendation, I've made this recipe twice now.  The first time just to test the recipe, and the second to take photos for a photo demo in the Gadgets Forum, as I've finally found a use my silicone veggie steamer!  I've tried dozens of methods for hard-cooking eggs and several have been good for easy peeling, but this recipe is far superior in the final product.  Most recipes tend to overcook the eggs, even just slightly, leaving various stages of gray rings around the yolk.  This recipe, made as written, cooked the eggs perfectly, and with no sign of overcooking.  I am so pleased with this recipe that I have to share it with as many chefs as I can!  Thanks for posting it, Peter!  :)

name: chorizo potato frittata
review: Yummo! I scaled this down to fit an 8 inch skillet but used the full amount of chorizo. I didn't have the right cheese so I used shredded mexican blend. We really enjoyed this super-filling breakfast this morning. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8-Spain/Portugal.

name: very easy garlic sauteed spinach
review: Very easy and very tasty indeed. I also added some salt and pepper and it was a wonderful side dish to our fish. Thank you.

name: baked zucchini with mushrooms
review: Prepared roughly half recipe, and chopped the zuke instead of shredding. I added the small diced to the veggie mixture, to soften before adding to egg mixture . I found it a tad dry, and surely needed some salt .  Added to the ways to prep zucchini -- plenty left over for another night.  Thanks for posting, vivmom.

name: bailey s hot fudge sauce
review: Delightful!  I also made and posted Recipe #484185 #484185 using Bill Kates's review directions, and the end result was virtually indistinguishable.  Use the very best cocoa powder you can find, because THAT is what you will taste.  Because it is more difficult to control heat with the pan directly over the flame, I did prefer using the double boiler method in Recipe #484185.  This recipe made 400 ml (1.69 cups), so please store in a 2-cup jar so it will be easier to access from the refrigerator.

name: glazed carrots  carottes vichy
review: We loved the flavor of these carrots!  My husband has never really liked carrots, but even he talked about how delicious they were.  Made for ZWT 8, Bistro Babes.

name: peas with mushrooms  bacon   cream
review: This had a delicious flavor!  I did make one small change with the addition of just a smidgen of garlic powder, just cause I like it.  Loved the bacon added in!  Made for ZWT 8, Bistro Babes.

name: prego no po   garlic nailed steak   portugal
review: After reading the other reviews I decided to grill the steak. I did as breezermom suggested with the garlic and made the sauce in a skillet on the stove. The wine with the onions made this an outstanding meal. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8-Spain/Portugal.

name: warm manchego cheese popovers
review: Super delicious!We ate them warm from the oven with a glass of red wine for an evening snack. I left out the the olive cause I can't stand them : ) other wise I made as written except for cutting the recipe in half. Using my cast iron muffin pan I got 6 popovers. Next time I make these I might add a little onion or garlic granules. Thanks for sharing alli! Made for ZWT 8 by one of The Wild Bunch.

name: mocha crackle cookies
review: YUM no need to say more : )  Very moist and delicious!  Thanks loof!

name: mustard garlic pork tenderloin
review: My whole family raved over the flavor of this pork tenderloin.  It was easy to make and I love how quickly the recipe came together.  I marinated the meat for about 2 hours before cooking in on the grill.  Delicious!

name: lemon herb roasted beets
review: Another nice roasted beets recipe.  Watch them closely though, at such a high temperature they go from just browning, to nearly burning quite quickly.  I liked the lemon flavour, think I'd add more herbs next time, or make sure the 2 tbsp of fresh herbs is measured after they are minced.  I eye balled it and the herbs were a little lost.  I like to use roasted beets in salads, so these flavours will be great.

name: green beans with shallots  lemon  and thyme
review: This is a really good recipe for fresh green beans from my garden. The fresh lemon really makes the dish.

name: fennel butter
review: I really liked the flavor of this.  I melted just a jot of it on a really cheap steak which was transformed into a million bucks. I also used it with sauteed potatoes and green beans. I think it would be great in scrambled eggs. I guess I will find out tomorrow!

name: vinaigrette aux oeufs durs  hard boiled egg dressing
review: Very nice dressing, indeed! I made half the recipe using white wine vinegar and made a salad of hearts of romaine with radishes, cukes, and green onions. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8- France.

name: spanish tuna salad
review: I have to say that although I like all the ingredients in this dish, the combination didn't blow me away.  The sherry really made it taste too 'boozy', a flavor that really didn't compliment the fish.  I'll try again with sherry vinegar, I think that would be a smoother flavor.  Thanks for posting!  Made for ZWT8

name: poached cherries
review: I made these for our dessert tonight and we really enjoyed them.  I served them with a dollop of whipped cream, but would like to try them with some pound cake.  Made for ZWT 8, Bistro Babes.

name: sweet potato cottage pie
review:
YES YES YES YES YES! TRUE!
THINK am excited about having made this too? lol
This is terrific LOVE is low fat,
Never thought could have Cottage/Shepard's Pie this yummy! HOWZ THAT? :)
MADE IT AGAIN today!! Added a bit of Worcestershire sauce as used 500 grams of mince...Still healthy and YUM!

name: copycat steak  n  shake frisco melts
review: Delish!  Made these tonight, but combined lean beef and turkey and grilled it.  Toasted the bread, but did not dip in butter, and only used one patty.  It was still fantastic and will be on my list to make again!

name: french baguette
review: My baguettes didn't turn out to be a pretty shape, but the taste made up for it!  This made a nicely textured bread.  Will definitely be making this again!  Made for ZWT 8, Bistro Babes.

name: emeril s lyonnaise potatoes
review: I really enjoyed these potatoes. I just used ordinary russet potatoes and used a box grater to slice the potatoes thin. I also used red onion for color. I did need to salt the potatoes after they were cooked.  I will certainly make these again.

name: portuguese corn bread for the bread machine  broa
review: I'm sorry, but we weren't terribly fond of this.  I find that soaking the cornmeal in liquid before adding it makes a very wet dough and a heavy, dense loaf.  This would probably have turned out better with a different technique.  I may retry this adding the cornmeal with the flour.  Thanks for posting!  Made for the Lively Lemon Lovelies, ZWT8.

name: french courgette  zucchini  quiche
review: This was really good - attested to by DH who ate 1/2 of the quiche by himself LOL.  I actually made 2 quiches out of this recipe as my pie crusts were small - I filled one and still had a little less than 1/2 of the custard left, so I decided to divvy it up between 2 pie shells since I had them. This baked up beautifully - nice and golden on top and very moist on the inside. I did substitute about 2 tablespoons of Hormel Peppered Crumbled Bacon because I was pressed for time and didn't want to cook bacon, and I doubled the onion (personal preference), but followed the rest of the recipe as written. Really nice recipe, and I got double for my trouble !! Thanks for posting - made for ZWT8 - France, and the Herbaceous Curvaceous Honeys.

name: awesome orange chocolate muffins
review: I got 12 mini muffins and 9 regular sized muffins. These muffins are very good, moist and super easy. I wonder if you could use more orange juice and just cut out the milk (I used almond milk)? It took about 10 minutes for the minis to bake and 18 for the other. Made for my fellow Chef Gone Wild for ZWT8. Thanks loof! :)

name: torrijas saladas con ajo  garlic  french  toast
review: Oh wow, did I love this! I cut the recipe down a bit to make just 2 slices. I used olive-rosemary foccacia for the bread and loved every bite. I'll definitely make this often. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8-Spain/Portugal.

name: vanilla latte
review: YUMMY! After preparing it as a hot beverage I decided to poor it over ice since it is very hot and humid in New Jersey. Made for Ramadan tag,

name: sunset orzo with spanish shrimp
review: Five stars all the way! Not sure if the turmeric is even necessary - comes together quickly with lots of huge flavor. Next time I'll use a full pound box of orzo to serve four people. Also there must be a way to reduce the number of pots. Unlike Rachael, I don't have a staff to clean my kitchen!

name: easy peasy apple turnovers
review: This recipe was super easy, but the filling was just okay for me.  I found it too dry and not sweet enough.

name: basque lemonade
review: I wouldn't have thought to mix red and white wines, but this is really good with the lemon - tastes more like sangria than a wine cooler. Great idea!

name: port and paprika chicken bites
review: Oh, yum!  This was just wonderful.  The port gave it a tiny edge of sweetness without going overboard, and the onion and paprika just rounded out the flavors beautifully.  The cilantro was a really nice touch- adding a fresh bite of flavor to a very rich piece of chicken.  I loved how easy the marinade was to make.  I may use this on whole chicken pieces in the future- with a longer marinating time, of course.  I can't wait to have the leftovers tomorrow for lunch!  Thanks for sharing.  Made for ZWT8

name: the spaniard  grilled sandwich
review: The paprika butter, manchego cheese and peppers make this unforgettable!

name: new potatoes in blue cheese cream
review: Luxurious and delicious! I agree with twissis, these are not an everyday side dish, but they are definitely worth the occasional splurge! I had found some nice rock lobster tails at Costco, so I grilled those up to serve with these potatoes. I used some tiny yukon gold potatoes, so I quartered them lengthwise to get tiny wedges. I didn't have a problem with the tops getting too dark, but maybe it's because my potatoes were so tiny that they started off covered in the cream mixture. Edited to add: I almost forgot, I used fresh parsley in place of the flakes because I had so much on hand. Thanks for posting! Made by a Honey for ZWT8 France

name: scrambled eggs with fines herbes and tomatoes
review: The dijon mustard works really well in this recipe and I like the fluffy textue from mixing in the egg yolk at the very end. I used fresh parsley and chives; and opted to keep my tomatoes sliced fresh and not cooked in the eggs. Definitely a recipe I will be making again. Made for ZWT8 by Bistro Babes

name: french pear flan
review: A lovely light baked custard with pear that was super easy to make. Needed about 10 minutes longer to cook. I think this would be lovely served in individual serve flan dishes too. Photo to be posted. Reviewed for ZWT8 visit to France

name: cinnamon glazed carrots
review: lovely carrots to have as a side. I used 'new' carrots as couldn't buy baby carrots photo to be posted. Reviewed for ZWT8 visit to France

name: honey dijon chicken
review: 5 stars for such a quick and easy chicken dish to make. Reviewed for ZWT8 visit to France.

name: eva s chunky guacamole
review: Very good, but I'll stick with my usual guacamole recipe. If using the big Florida avocados, you only need two instead of three.

name: cerdo de barcelona
review: This is a truly delightful combination of flavors.  The more I ate of it, the better I liked it.  I think this would be one of those dishes that tastes better the next day, but, alas, we finished it all.  This has a relatively short cooking time, so be sure to use a tender cut of pork.

name: haricots verts with carmelized shallots
review: These were lovely! My shallots were enormous, so I just chopped them instead of leaving them whole. The caramelized shallots made the house smell delicious (bonus! lol). Thanks for posting! Made for a fellow Herby Curvy Honey for ZWT8 France

name: caramelized french toast
review: I made this for breakfast this morning. I halved the recipe and added a little cinnamon to the batter. The caramel sauce was terrific on this. I served it with bacon and fresh strawberries. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8- France.

name: lemon beer   clara or shandy
review: Great way to cut the alcohol in beer - and so lemony refreshing!

name: spanish fried eggs with potatoes and chorizo  huevos fritos con
review: I halved everything except the chorizo. I couldn't find piquillo peppers so I used roasted red peppers. We thoroughly enjoyed this breakfast for dinner meal last night. Thanks for sharing. Made for Pick-A-Pepper challenge (ZWT 8- Spain/Portugal).

name: cheese topping with herbs and spices
review: WOW! I used an orange capsicum and a sweet onion with extra sharp cheddar cheese. I used potato bread made by the Amish. Great and flavorful lunch. I made 4 slices but next time I'll only make two as they were quite filling. DH told me I can make these anytime! Made for Ramadan tag.

name: chicken breasts with herb stuffing
review: Absolutely loved the stuffing!  The mix of herbs and spinach really made this something special, and the fact that it's healthy didn't hurt either.  I totally forgot to put the oil into the stuffing, but it was plenty moist and I didn't miss it.  The sauce was great as well, my only complaint was that we wanted more!  This was really easy, and I wouldn't hesitate to serve it to company.  Thanks for sharing!  Made for ZWT8

name: cacoila  portuguese stewed pork
review: Easy to make but full of flavor! Your whole house will smell incredible.

name: captivating champagne
review: So elegant - you can't go wrong with these ingredients.

name: lemon beer   clara or shandy
review: Very refreshing way to cool down in the heat.  :)  I love beer and lemons anyway - so why not comine two great flavors?  I used Widmere Brothers Rotator Ipa Series Shaddock IPA.  **Made for ZWT8 2012**

name: basic stir fry sauce
review:
This is definitely 5 stars! I had lots of fresh veggies to use up and some grilled chicken breast. I made the stir fry sauce and decided I would add a second tbsp of sugar and we liked it, but that's a personal preference. Wow the sauce was spot on and just the right amount for what I had to saute.
Thanks for the great stir fry sauce. Carole in Orlando

name: jagacita   jag   portugal
review: We enjoyed this.  A good dish all around, but I thought it could use more paprika.  Instead of making on the stovetop, I used my rice cooker; which worked beautifully.  Thanks for sharing!  Made for ZWT8

name: manchego and serrano crostini
review: Just loved these crostini, Nif! Easy to throw together and so tasty - DS, who turns his nose up at such things (picky eater), went shopping for 'world tour' ingredients with me, so when these were prepared as a 'light' lunch for DH and I, DS asked if he could have some 'world tour' food, too. And them came back twice more...Shocked, is right! Thanks so much for sharing a great , Nif!

name: chocolate almond coffee frappe
review: Easy and tasty beverage.  I will make this again, especially when my DD is home from school, she loves these things!  Thanks for a nice treat to make at home!!  **Made for ZWT8 2012**

name: garbanzos y chorizo
review: My family and a friend all really enjoyed this recipe.  My friend said it reminded her of a twist on hash.  :)  Great quick dish, full of flavor.  Thank you!  **Made for ZWT8 2012**

name: clementine clafouti
review: Despite the long list of directions, it was a simple and easy recipe to make. And it was also well worth making as well, especially since we eat alot of clementimes in our house. It was refreshing and so good.

name: chocolate almond coffee frappe
review: Tasty treat for this coffee lover.  The almond was a bit strong for my taste buds (and my son's) but that is easily reduced the next time we make it.  Love how easy it is to make at home compared to the high prices out at a coffee shop.  Made for ZWT8.

name: avocado   apple salad  ensalada de aguacate y manzana
review: I made this especially for DH as he loves his avocados and I thought this would be a great post-workout meal for him. He LOVED it...didn't even share with me. I'll definitely make this again, as he was quite impressed with the salad and he loved the dressing. Another winner made for ZWT8 - Spain/Portugal and the Herbaceous Curvaceous Honeys.

name: sherry vinaigrette
review: Very good, and very easy- a winning combination in my mind :)  The sherry vinegar is very mild, so this would be great on a delicate salad.  I used it over baby spinach, with some sweet bell peppers and Manchego thrown in for variety. Thanks for sharing!  Made for ZWT8

name: spanish lemon salad  ensalada de limn
review: We really really enjoyed this salad. I made as written, but my garlic was bad so I sprinkled just a bit of garlic powder over the salad before adding the eggs. I drizzled a bit of olive oil over top and skipped the red wine. What a great combination of flavor sensations and textures. The spicy chorizo, tart lemon, sweet orange and neutral flavor of the eggs really worked for us. DH liked it for (one) of his post-workout meals. Will definitely make this again - so quick and easy and really very satisfying. So glad I tried this recipe.  Made for ZWT8 - Spain/Portugal and the Herbaceous Curvaceous Honeys.

name: onion  olive and orange salad
review: I made this easy salad and my family and a friend all enjoyed it.  My DS even asked for seconds - and he is just "discovering" salads!!  NICE compliment of flavors!!  Thanks for a winner.  **Made for ZWT8 2012**

name: rabbit normandy style
review: My very first Wabbit! What a delightful candied apple glazed perfection!  With a few alterations for the cook's benefit, this recipe will get the five stars it deserves.  For me, it helps a lot to list the ingredients in the order used. I added 1 teaspoon of freshly ground sea salt and 1/2 teaspoon of freshly ground white pepper to the flour (only needed about 1/4 cup of that).  To prevent the peeled and sliced apples from turning brown, I put them in a 2 1/2 quart casserole dish and covered them with 700 ml of Woodchuck Granny Smith Hard Cider until it was time to add them to the pot.  I would also prefer that the directions be broken into numbered steps so I can check them off as I cook (and not get lost in the directions). A rabbit has 2 larger hind legs, 2 smaller front legs, 2 5-inch by 1-inch tenderloins and 1 tiny filet mignon strip about 3/4 inch by 2 1/2 inches (TG, my hunter DH expertly cut the rabbit into serving pieces or I would have missed the exquisite filet mignon piece), and neither DH nor I would want to share the meat with even a third person.  Normally I would saute on high heat, but the 20 minutes on low prevented the meat from overcooking too quickly.  My 6-1/2-quart oval Le Creuset pot was the perfect size to fit all the pieces without crowding.  I tossed the chopped onion in with the rabbit, but I couldn't really toss it easily for browning without disturbing the meat; that didn't seem to make a difference in the end result.  Two liters of Woodchuck Granny Smith Hard Cider seemed like a lot, but it cooked down just as the recipe said it would.  My D'Artagnon rabbit from Wegman's was pricy even on sale at $5.39/lb.  DH asked when he could hunt rabbits with you, so we could have this recipe again.  Thank you so much for sharing this recipe, Jim!  Made for The Wild Bunch of ZWT8 for our stop in France.

name: basque style chicken
review: I used bone-in chicken breasts cut in half, so mine did take a bit longer to cook  I followed the advice of another poster and added some garlic and thyme.  This is beautiful, flavorful and easy--who could ask for more?  Thanks for posting!  Made for the Lively Lemon Lovelies, ZWT8, Pick a Pepper Challenge.

name: frenchy popcorn
review: This was interesting, I Iiked the garlic with the popcorn, but some of the herb in the herbs de provence, like the tarragon were a bit odd and off putting. One issue with the recipe,  I don't see how the popcorn amount in relation to the oil can be correct. I used the 2 TBLS of oil with a scant 1/3 cup popcorn. Using my 3 qt Revere Ware pot the oil maybe half covered the popcorn, which covered the bottom of the pot in a single layer and when popped filled the pot.  I would think you'd need a lot more oil then 2 Tbls. for 1 cup of popcorn and a huge pot to pop it in. Thanks for sharing, I may try this again with different herbs. I also cut back on the amount of butter.  Made for ZWT 8 by one of The Wild Bunch.

name: jacques s cauliflower au gratin
review: Wonderful, creamy, cheesy goodness! I made this as written using gruyere cheese. We loved this and will make often. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8- France.

name: slow cooker chicken marbella
review: What a wonderful chicken recipe. I am always on the lookout for crockpot recipes, as I make 1 - 2 of them weekly. Very wholesome flavor, it could use even more sauce as it is the best part of the recipe.

name: chicken dijon
review: One thing I really love is whole grain Dijon mustard.   This recipe did not disappoint.  I did use large chicken thighs which I cut in half.

name: salad with oranges  red onion and olives
review: What a festive salad, I love the dressing for this salad, it is what sets it apart from similar salads that are citrus inspired. Used a garlic, lime olive oil in the dressing.

name: mushroom vol au vent
review: I went the lazy route and used pre-made pastry shells, otherwise made exactly as written. The whole family loved them. The recipe for sure also lends itself to play with addition of herbs and garlic as noted in other reviews. Made for ZWT8 by Bistro Babes.

name: scrambled eggs  oeufs brouills
review: I have to agree with the others. This is the only way to cook perfect srambled eggs. I liked the addition of cream and cheese. Definitely put it over the top. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8- France.

name: kate cowick french dressing
review:
Excellent dressing! We loved it over a bed of Mesculin Mix. It was simple to make with easy to find ingredients. Thanks for an awesome recipe :)
Made for ZWT 8 France

name: orange biscuits
review: Great biscuits with lovely orange flavor! I made it as written and they were delicious. I served them with bacon and scrambled eggs for breakfast. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8- France.

name: chicken   mushrooms with creamy dijon sauce
review: I used this recipe to convert it to a crock pot recipe for the ZWT8 and used the exact ingredients. This is a wonderful chicken dish and nicely done in the crock pot.

name: orange thyme chicken
review: Excellent chicken, we loved the flavour in this. I made as directed, but finished the drumsticks off on the BBQ to give them a "blackened" look. Thumbs up from my whole family, thanks for posting! Made for ZWT 8 Spain :)

name: quesadillas
review: Well, this was delicious, and very easy. I scaled the recipe to one serving, using two tortillas one on top of the other, rather than folding them. Didn't use a chile this time, but do want to try it sometime soon. The recipe gets bonus points because I was able to use my pizza cutter. Thank you very much for sharing this recipe with us.

name: chicken breast with tomato sauce and mozzarella
review: The breading was outstanding, but because of that I think the marinara and cheese covered up the taste. I found myself cutting around the cheese and sauce and just enjoying the chicken itself more. I could have been because I used store bought marinara but either way I'm going to turn this into a schnitzel in the near future. I would also recommend reducing the time in the oven to 25 minutes as my breasts were a bit dry. Thank you!

name: apple slices with goat cheese and pistachios
review: Yum! So nice with all the textures and flavors! I loved the crispy apples, tangy goat cheese, sweet/spicy ginger and the salty pistachios! I put mine together at the last minute, so no lemon juice was needed. And they were scarfed down so quickly, there wasn't time for them to brown! Thanks for sharing a great eye-appealing recipe, Sharon!

name: open omelette
review: Delicious way to use good things from the garden - tomato and fresh herbs - I used some thyme, oregano, a little sage and rosemary - lovely thick bacon and yukon gold potato. Very satisfying and flavorful.

name: zucchini   rice casserole
review: We loved this recipe. The zucchini I used was quite juicy, and I had no problems with the cooking time. I found it to be flavourful and a delicious side that my whole family loved. Made for ZWT 8 France :)

name: mixed potato salad
review: I love these salads with sweet potato and regular potato combined. I used a gold potato, as I've never seen pink ones here. I did dice the potatoes a bit smaller than suggested, as we don't like big chunks in potato salad and cooked them on the stove, which worked out quite well. Could not find the gherkins (later found them hiding behind the OJ), so I added some capers which added a nice touch of sharpness. I did add a bit more dill, which I love. Delicious with ribs for lunch.

name: mango wedges wrapped in serrano ham
review: This was a delicious recipe. The combination of juicy ripe mangoes and the ham and cheese makes this perfect for tapas on the back patio. We devoured this, thanks for posting! Made for ZWT 8 Spain/Portugal :)

name: orange blueberry scones
review: These were really good, and met with unanimous approval with the family. I didn't have a problem with the dough being too wet, but I will say that I subbed yogurt for the buttermilk and that might have helped thicken it up. I also subbed in some spelt and oat flour to add fiber and was pleasantly surprised that these stayed light and fluffy. My only complaint is that the amount of orange zest in the recipe does not match the amount in the directions, which led to some confusion for me. I had dumped in all of the zest before I realized it was supposed to be divided, too, which is my own fault. Didn't hurt the recipe, though! Made for ZWT 8, for the Wild Bunch.

name: french dressing  1908
review: The age of this recipe caught my eye and I had to try it. I subbed pepper for the paprika and omitted the mustard. It tasted just like my Grandma's dressing. Very enjoyable! Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8- France.

name: quick sally lunn bread
review: This is tasty! The adults in the house liked it, but the toddlers/kids LOVED it. Perhaps because we called it doughnut bread?? My loaf fell in the center which led me to wonder if there is too much baking powder in the recipe but upon reading the other reviews it looks like I'm the only one with that problem so it was probably user error! This was definitely easy to throw together, and I can see how it would be versatile as well. As we were having it for an afternoon snack I added a healthy shake of cinnamon to the batter and to the sugar topping. Delicious! Made for ZWT 8: The Wild Bunch.

name: cherries jubilee  fantabulous
review: Easy and good.  Didn't flame it but added a touch of almond extract.

name: minted lamb shanks
review: Wonderful! I used large lamb shanks and the latter times listed were spot on to give perfectly tender meat with a nice golden crust. The combination of mint and honey sounds a little unusual but works reall well.

name: mango wedges wrapped in serrano ham
review: I made this to eat with our breakfast this morning and the combined flavors were delicious!  It was so worth the effort to track down the manchego cheese.  Made for ZWT 8, Bistro Babes.

name: chicken and rice salad veronique
review: I love all the flavors in this salad!  My co-workers were so jealous!  Thanks for posting!

name: easy crustless spinach savoury tart
review: So simple yet so sophisticated and delectable. Thank you!

name: grilled corn with smoked paprika butter
review: I skipped the pre-cooking and just grilled 2 ears of corn. I mixed a little cayenne into the paprika and mixed it into half a stick of butter. I didn't bother chilling the butter, just lathered it on the corn and sprinkled a bit of Pensey's Arizona Dreaming. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8- Spain/Portugal.

name: chicken breasts with green sauce  pollo con salsa verde
review: I love the flavor of this, but do be careful of the red pepper flakes since they do simmer in the sauce. Red pepper flakes get hotter the longer they cook. Also, the sauce is brown and not green!

name: warm manchego cheese popovers
review: These are delightful straight out of the oven! I followed Chocolatl's lead and preheated my tins before filling them, and I don't know if the popovers technically "popped" (I've never had a popover before this), but they rose really high in the oven. Lovely little finger food, thanks for posting! Made for The Honeys for ZWT8

name: fennel butter
review: This was ok,  I found the butter, fennel, garlic combination a bit intense; I've been trying savory butters on corn, so tried this one, maybe I'd like it better on protein. Made for ZWT 8 by one of The Wild Bunch.

name: brie topped dijon chicken breasts
review: Delicieux! This is super rich with both the brie and the sauce. It would be good even without the brie, or use a less expensive cheese, or serve the sauce on the side. Loved it!

name: raspberry vanilla refrigerator oatmeal
review: LOVED this! The perfect way to enjoy oatmeal in a hot climate...like a chilled pudding with some texture to it. The raspberry jam and vanilla added the perfect amount of flavor. I made enough for two days and it was a delicious quick breakfast. Thanks!

name: vegan chocolate shake shake shake
review: Delicious! I used chocolate Toffuti and almond milk and it was very tasty! Made for Veg 'n Swap VIP!

name: easy turkey gravy
review: this has been my back up turkey gravy recipe and has been for a long time. it is easy to prepare and the taste is rich and creamy, the best thing about it is NOT LUMPS. thanks for posting the recipe.

name: spanish burger
review: I love a good surprise! I 'envelope-wrapped' the cheese with the serrano ham and stuck a toothpick in it, to hold together. It also made it easier to 'turn' the ham/cheese nugget in the pan, while frying! These were beautiful and I think I may 'surprise' my friends with one, and soon! Thanks for sharing, GailAnn!

name: pear  blue cheese  walnut and bacon salad
review: I made a vegetarian version of this salad, obviously by leaving out the bacon and chicken...and it was fantastic!  I really really loved it, from the delicately candied walnuts to the creamy blue cheese - mmmm, I wish there was some left over.  This would be a fabulous salad to serve on a special occassion - but certainly not that time intensive that you couldn't make it any old time.  If I were to change anything, I might just double up on the ingredients to 'candy' the walnuts - they were so darn good I would like a bit more of that flavour in the finished product.  Be careful with your pears, sliced thinly they are super delicate.  Thanks GailAnn!

name: spanish tapas   avocado puree and shrimp cocktail
review: I used cooked salad shrimp for this. I cut the recipe down to serve 2. We loved the avocado puree. Thanks for sharing. Made fpr ZWT 8- Spain/Portugal.

name: make your own boursin cheese   paula deen
review:
Yum! This was way too simple to be this good! I won't ever need to buy this stuff again!!!
I made as written except for reducing to 3/4 cup. The garlic and oregeno is very dominant, I might reduce it just a tiny bit and bump up the dill a little - personal preference it's delicious as is. Thanks for sharing LifeIsGood, made for ZWT 8 by one of The Wild Bunch.

name: persimmon bars
review: Different and tasty! I didn't have raisins in the house (I don't like them), so I subbed in Craisins instead, which were perfect in this. My persimmon wasn't quite as soft as I thought, so it mashed into a very chunky puree which left detectable bits of persimmon here and there (not a bad thing). I topped the bars with Kittencal's Recipe#90142 (with half vanilla and half coconut extract). They remind me a little bit of the Starbucks Cranberry Bliss bars, texture-wise. Oh, and I used chopped pecans for the nuts. Usually I pass over things with raisins and nuts in them, but I would definitely make these again. Thanks for posting! Made for The Honeys for ZWT8

name: french bistro steak on garlic croutes and potato frites
review: Really did enjoy these for dinner tonight - I'm not a 'sauce' on my steak kinda girl, but I followed this recipe, except for splitting the steak. The fries were lovely and crispy with a great flavor. The steaks were great on the bread with the reduction drizzled over top. I will file this away for the next time DH deserves a special dinner! Thanks for sharing, Deantini!

name: grilled camembert sandwiches  or brie
review: I made this with a thick toast on my GF grill, as I don't have a panini press/pan. I did use the lowest setting, and weighted the top with a heavy pan. The grill marks were nice, but I couldn't get the bread darker, as the cheese runneth over! That was an 'operator error'. Just loved the pepper-infused oil. This was a really tasty sandwich, as is, and next time I may add some some seasonings or try to 'amp' it up a bit! Thanks for sharing, CJAY!

name: spanish sauce burger topping
review: I made this to go with a grilled ribeye. I used a mild salsa as the base and its true, couldn't be any easier!

name: protein powered oatmeal breakfast
review: Yum! The protein powder keeps you full until lunch.

name: valencia paella
review: Excellent!  I love paella, and almost never make it at home.  This was a wonderful example of the dish, full of flavor.  I added 1/2 teaspoon of smoked paprika with the tomatoes, otherwise made as written.  Thanks for sharing!  Made for ZWT8

name: spanish sauce burger topping
review: I used a medium heat salsa for this, and used this as a topping for my minute steak, instead of the usual bbq sauce. It was really good! My whole family enjoyed it, and we used it again, today, for our veggie burgers. It keeps well in the fridge, which is a big plus for me.

name: saffron scented  couscous with pine nuts
review: This was a lovely side, with mild flavors that could go with just about anything! We enjoyed it with mustard salmon, but I can even see adding chickpeas and maybe olives to beef it into a vegetarian main. It was very easy to throw together, and does make quite a bit. DH thought it was really a great change of pace side dish :). Made for ZWT 8: The Wild Bunch.

name: provence tomato soup
review: Terrific! I liked the kick of the cayenne and was happily surprised by how rich this soup tasted. I used garlic powder instead of garlic salt because the tomato sauce was salty enough. Also, I used a nice beef broth instead of the water and veggie bouillon. Made for my fellow Chef Gone Wild for ZWT8. Thanks Tea Girl! :)

name: creamy tarragon chicken
review: Very tasty, this made a quick midweek meal that would be a great choice for a dinner party. I was  out of mushrooms and only let the mustard and tarragon sit on the chicken for about 45 mins. before cooking. Thank for sharing, I'll be making this again! Made for ZWT 8 by one of The Wild Bunch.

name: french roasted potatoes
review: This is a great recipe, delicious flavour combination. I cooked them on the BBQ, but I had issues with the garlic burning because it's difficult to control the temperature on our grill (seems to be hot or off :).  That's no fault of the recipe, however if you have the same problem, I guess you could add more oil or add the garlic in later with the mustard sauce, which is what I plan to do next time.

name: banana   pb snacking cake
review: Such a moist and easy cake - perfect for a sleepover with the boys! I whipped this up, cooled and iced it in less than 2 hours - quick work! And they scarfed it down, and I sent them home with the leftovers, 'cause I have the recipe! :D Thanks for sharing, Lori Mama; this was a great and simple, from-scratch cake, that I'm keeping close for those fading bananas!

name: chicken and chorizo  leftovers in tasty disguise
review: Great way to utilize leftovers. I used a tablespoon of taco sauce for the tomato puree and grilled Italian sausage. We enjoyed this easy to make dinner and will make again. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8- Spain/Portugal.

name: vegetarian ceviche
review: What a nice alternative for those who do not like or cannot have seafood!  The only caution is, this is not something that can be made too far ahead of time, the texture suffers.

name: frozen raspberry mousse
review: This was a delectable treat. We have a booming crop of raspberries and this was another great way to enjoy them. Thanks for sharing Boomette! Made for ZWT 8 by one of The Wild Bunch.

name: pork tenderloin with merlot shallot sauce
review: This was so delicious! We love pork loin and will add this version to our regular repetoire. I made it as written except for using pork loin scallops instead of the whole loin and cutting the sauce in half for two. This made a reatively quick and elegant dinner, I over cooked my pork a little but the sauce more than made up for it. I love the very slight sweet edge the jams (I used both) gave to the savory flavors of the shallots and merlot. I used a 14 Hands Merlot which has a slight cherry flavor and was very complimentory to the sausce. Thanks Nan for a great recipe! Made for ZWT 8 by one of The Wild Bunch

name: herb salad
review: I made 1/8 of this recipe and there was still too much for 1 person! These herbs weigh next to nothing so I got a lot out of these small measurements. I would guess that this would easily feed 10 -12 people as a side or appetizer. I would at least double the amount of dressing because there really wasn't enough. Also, I would chop up the tarragon and mint because they are pretty overwhelming. This would be great with a rich dish or even bread and butter to cut through some of these distinctive flavours. Made for my fellow Chef Gone Wild for ZWT8. Thanks Annacia! :)

name: warm avocado salsa
review: This salsa is a nice change from tomato based salsa and those with lots of cheese.

name: roast potatoes with olives
review: Well, I did remember the olives, but I don't think they added anything more than color to the dish. They all just wound up sliding off the potatoes and into the salsa verde that I served them with.  I cut the potatoes smaaller so that they would cook quicker. They came out perfectly crisp in the outside and tender inside.

name: peach and roasted red pepper bruschetta
review:
This dish was the hit of our tapas dinner party! I made it as written except for using a yellow pepper instead of red, and cutting it in half. The freshness sweetness of the peach is a nice contrast to the grilled pepper and the bite of the garlic, the fresh basil adds just the right touch.
Made for ZWT 8 Pick a Pepper Challenge by one of The Wild Bunch. Thanks for sharing Leslie, I'll be making this again!

name: jacques  french potato salad
review: This was a nice change of pace from mayonnaise-based potato salad.  I especially enjoyed the flavor of the onions after cooking them (okay, I admit it, I cooked them more like 3 minutes), they were so sweet.

name: roasted peaches with goat cheese and honey
review: Just beautiful! I love the sweetness and juice from the peaches and honey, mixed with the tanginess from the goat cheese and the crunch from the hazelnuts. I might grill these bad boys next time - more work for DH! Thanks for sharing, GailAnn!

name: grilled corn with smoked paprika butter
review: We loved this!  The smoky sweet butter was a huge hit, which I wasn't really expecting.  The bit of extra butter we had made its way onto potatoes too since we liked it so much.  I didn't bother with the pre-boiling because I had freshly cut corn and usuallly cook it straight on the grill (half way with it's husks still on...soaked in water beforehand).  Got some nice colour on our cobs of corn, I was only sorry I didn't make more.  Thanks lazyme!

name: boursin crab potatoes
review: I made a modified version just using the boursin cheese with my baked potatoes, it was quite tasty and was very complimentary to the other dishes I served.  I look forward to trying the recipe as written. Made for ZWT 8 by one of The Wild Bunch

name: tomato gratin
review: This was just delish! I made the feta cheese version and cut the bread and tomatoes in slices for easy scooping out of the casserole dish as recommended by other reviewers. The whole family loved it and I will be making again for sure. Made for ZWT 8 by Bistro Babes

name: grilled mushrooms with garlic oil
review: You really get a limey zing with these, pairs nicely with the chili - makes me think more Mexican than Spanish, but whichever way you look at it, they taste great. I was a little worried about them being dry, but they weren't.  I'd be tempted to make a little more of the dressing next back and hold it back to toss with the cooked mushrooms after - so there is lots of the tasty sauce to go around.  I probably cooked mine longer than the recipe states, so I had no problem with them being underdone.  thanks Cadillacgirl!

name: the best garlic shrimp in the whole wide world
review:
Wow...this was absolutely delicious!! It's hard to believe that only a few ingredients could impart such a wonderful flavor. Of course, with the combination of garlic and shrimp, how can you possibly go wrong? We enjoyed this with cilantro rice for a nice, light delicious dinner. Thank you for sharing this wonderful recipe...it is definitely a keeper!
**Made for ZWT 8 Spain/ Portugal**

name: magdalenas   spanish cakes
review: YUM!  These have a great light texture and a nice lemon flavor without being overpowering.  My kids and I enjoyed these immensely.  They are great warmed in the microwave for a morning treat too with my coffee.  Found and made during ZWT8.

name: spanish tortillitas de camarones  shrimp cakes
review: While quick and easy to make we found these to be rather bland and more eggy, spongy then like a pancake. I cut the recipe in half and after making one test pancake added chopped cilantro, lemon zest and garlic powder for more flavor and this helped a bit. I got four more pancakes which I would consider 2 appetizer servings. Made for ZWT 8 by one of The Wild Bunch

name: crustless country  quiche   omelete
review:
Delicious!! We thoroughly enjoyed this wonderful quiche for breakfast. I used a combination of diced ham and cooked, crumbled bacon for the meat. Also, I had to bake this in my deep dish pie pan because it overfilled my regular pie pan. I served this with a dollop of creme fraiche...yummy! Thank you for sharing this wonderful recipe...it is definitely a keeper!
**Made for ZWT 8 France**

name: roast pork loin with creamy dijon sauce
review:
I adapted this recipe for the ZWT 8 France Crock Pot Challenge by adding some additional cooking liquid and by using creme fraiche, instead of the sour cream. I posted the adapted recipe as recipe #484635 #484635. The new recipe reflects the changes that I made to this recipe. We really enjoyed this delicious, tender roast. We especially liked the tang that the Dijon mustard added to the sauce.
**Made for ZWT 8 France Crock Pot Challenge**

name: better than chicken and dumplings
review: Very good!  We loved it.  I had to cook for longer than stated and was worried that it wouldn't set up with all the liquid, but it turned out great.  Thanks for posting.

name: zucchini rice pilaf
review: Reviewed for ZWT8 visit to France. Easy to make and made a great meal with a grilled chicken breast. I used gluten-free chicken stock/broth to make this meal gluten-free suitable. We really enjoyed this dish and its definitely a make again recipe for my family. Photo to be posted also.

name: new orleans  style choux fritters
review: What a fun treat to make!!  These came together really well.  The only thing I see lacking is the amount of oil - as 3/4 cup is just not going to be enough for frying.  I used about 2 1/2 cups (maybe even a bit more) so there was enough for frying.  They are good rolled in sugar but they are great rolled in cinnamon/sugar!  Be careful as the size really has to stay around a tablespoon as any larger they are still doughy in the center but browned on the outside.  My kids scarfed them down in no time flat!  Found and made during ZWT8.

name: scrambled eggs with fines herbes and tomatoes
review: I simply went out into my herb garden and grabbed a little parsley, thyme, blue sage, and rosemary and tossed it in the pan with the other ingredients. Nice fluffly eggs. I also used tomatoes from my garden so it was nice to use my garden for once. I will definitely keep this recipe in mind when I make eggs for breakfast. Made for ZWT8.

name: fettu skinny alfredo  healthified
review: This is a delicious lower fat version of a family favorite...especially when mixed with a homemade marinara to make a pink sauce!  5 stars for texture, but because next time I would substitute fresh garlic (saute a bit ahead) instead of the powder I scored it a 4.  Will definitely make this again!

name: frango  moda do alentejana  chicken with potatoes and ga
review: This is a nice, simple dish.  The garlic, onions and rosemary add a lot of flavor to the potatoes along with the juices from the roasting chicken.  I didn't use nearly as much rosemary as called for- 20 sprigs is a huge amount of a very assertive herb!  Instead I used 4 sprigs, each about 4 inches long.  I think that next time I would add a little white wine or broth into the bottom of the roasting dish to give a little more of the yummy sauce for the potatoes.  I also added some smoked paprika along with the salt and pepper when I seasoned the chicken- both for looks and for the yummy smokey flavor it adds.  Thanks for sharing!  Made for ZWT8

name: oven baked zucchini and tomato  tian from provence
review: I used all the ingredients listed, but I was not too orderly, just threw them in a glass baking dish. I also added some yellow squash as I had it on hand. It turned out great and the flavor was great (did add a few red pepper flakes for a little pop). Had it with fish and it was a nice side dish. Made for ZWT8

name: haddock with fresh summer vegetables
review: This a lovely recipe, which is a full meal in one casserole. I like the addition of potatoes. I also liked that it had red pepper flakes, garlic and thyme, as a matter of fact I think it could have used more spices - next time I will add more garlic and maybe a drop or two of hot sauce. I also will add more cheese for my husband. But all in all a nice fish dish. Made for ZWT8.

name: warm avocado salsa
review:
Delicious! I have never had warm salsa before and I was very pleasantly surprised. I loved this salsa!! The jalapeno provided just the right amount of zing, and the cilantro put the needed finishing touch to it. I haven't tried it cold yet, but warm...it was yummy! Thank you for sharing this wonderful recipe.
**Made for ZWT 8 Spain/ Portugal Pick-A-Pepper Challenge**

name: caramelized onion bread  bread machine
review: We loved the flavor of this  bread even though I thought the onions would have been more of a star in the finished product. I probably didn't use enough of them. I also used vadalias which gave the bread a sweet taste. Since this was the first time I had ever used the bell to add anything to the dough, I paniced and thought I had missed the ding. So I added the onions as it turned out only 5 minutes before the bell went off. Now I know that bell goes of 75 minutes after I press the start button. I used unbleached bread flour and did not replace any of it with rye. I think the top of the bread didn't rise due to old yeast, no fault of the recipe. I served it with ratatouille on couscous and crab cakes. Made for a great meal! Made for Ramadan tag.

name: avocado on toast with bacon and maple syrup
review: Why does bacon, avocado and maple syrup taste so good together? I have no idea, but it DOES! I used a grainy bread, regular bacon and real Canadian maple syrup that my Aunt just brought for me, directly from a producer in Southern Ontario. I wouldn't change a thing about this recipe! Made for Went To The Market tag game. Thanks I'mPat! :)

name: al andalus paella
review: Artichoke-hater DH said, "give this 5 stars" - he wonders why I say he doesn't really know what he likes and dislikes.  He said he wouldn't change a thing.  I used the authentic ingredients: saffron threads, Calasparra rice, Chorizo espagnole, and small fresh mussels, as well as the green beans, artichoke hearts, roasted red bell pepper, peas.  This may be the most involved recipe I have ever made, but it was delicious.  I found directions on cleaning the mussels on Allrecipes.  I used a huge paella pan that could span 2 burners, and more or less separated the saute ingredients to areas over the burners; for the rice, I rotated the pan so that I didn't end up with overdone rice in one section and raw rice in another.  Given comments on other recipes, I was caution about the amount of saffron; next time I will be sure to use the full 1/2 teaspoon, not just a pinch.  By the way, the chorizo espagnole was spicy sweet, not just hot; it was worth the investment.  It was just the 2 of us, so I cut back on the chicken thighs and the shrimp; we ate all of the prepared shrimp and mussels.  We have a lot of leftover paella rice with chorizo and vegetables for future meals. This was my first time to fix authentic paella, as one of The Wild Bunch for ZWT8 visit in Spain.

name: lyon style chicken with vinegar sauce
review: Wowee, this was yummy! We are a vinegar-loving family from the 2 year old up, and it was a perfect fit for us. I used 3 lbs of drumsticks and thighs instead of a whole chicken, and based on personal preference I removed the skins. Despite having several steps this couldn't have been easier to throw together (especially since you don't have to peel the garlic!) and I loved that I really only had two dishes to wash afterward. All in all a keeper! Made for ZWT 8: The Wild Bunch.

name: creme fraiche homemade
review:
Wow...was this ever easy and delicious!! I love creme fraiche, but I hate paying the high price for it. After trying this recipe, I won't be buying creme fraiche ever again! I let mine set at room temperature for 18 hours to get it to the consistency that I like. I still can't believe how easy this was!! Thank you Charlotte J for sharing this fabulous recipe. It is definitely a keeper!!
**Made for ZWT 8 France**

name: basil scented chicken salad
review: This was a very nice, light summer salad.  I cut the dressing in half, as the full amount seemed like too much for the chicken.  I used light mayo, otherwise made as directed.  The pine nuts and celery gave this a nice contrast of textures.  My basil is going crazy right now, so this was a great way to use some of it up.  Thanks for sharing!  Made for ZWT8

name: magic french fudge
review: This is a bit of chocolate heaven!  Oh my it could not be any simpler to make and the flavors are perfect.  I put some sliced almonds on half the pan after pouring and the other half left plain - that way all my family is satisfied.  Found and made for ZWT8 and definitely using this method for the holiday fudge!

name: fruit and cheese platter
review: Takes me back to French picnics, just need to add Champagne (although Grand Marnier is giving picnic totes with its bottles this summer).  Your fig-hazelnut-apricot spread is heavenly, DH ate 1/2 cup in one sitting.  I used the best cheeses I could find: Brie, Port du Salut and Roquefort.  Once again, quality won over DH: he loved the Roquefort, but had always claimed he hated bleu cheese; he even liked the Brie, and he had also previously expressed distaste for it. In the future I would probably substitute Chevre for the Port du Salut because it was too similar to the Brie, but Port du Salut is a safe choice for picky eaters, so know your audience.  The platter in my photo satisfied 2 (hungry) people for lunch.  Delightful.  Thank you for sharing, pammyowl!  Made for The Wild Bunch of ZWT8 during our stop in France.

name: spanish sauce burger topping
review: This is a terrific sauce for burgers! I used medium salsa for this and topped my grilled burger with it and a slice of cheddar cheese. Yummy. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT8- Spain/Portugal.

name: tomato and sweet onion platter
review: Simple but elegant. Made this for a barbeque potluck and everyone that it was gorgeous and tasted fresh and good. Made for ZWT8

name: grilled corn with smoked paprika butter
review: What a delicious way to serve corn on the cob! We all really enjoyed this recipe, the smoky paprika was to die for and it was so simple to make. Thanks for posting. Made for ZWT 8 :D

name: tomato and sweet onion platter
review: My neighbor brought me a bag of veggies from her garden so I had everything I needed to make this wonderful salad. I put it on individual plates and served the dressing on the side. It was terrific. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT8-Spain/Portugal.

name: tri tip marinade
review: I marinated a flank steak in this marinade and it was delicious. I didn't have low sodium soy sauce so I was afraid it was going to be too salty with the regular one but it wasn't. All around a big hit. Thank you!

name: pesto vegetable soup  crock pot
review: Delicious!  I sauteed 4 cloves of garlic with the onions in about 1 T of basil infused olive oil instead of using garlic broth.  Once they begin to soften, I added the other soup ingredients.(plus carrot and summer squash -- no potatoes) and cooked on high for 3 hours, then low for 1, then added pesto and spinach as directed.   Easy, but very tasty!

name: core spanish omelette
review: This was most excellent ! I made it as Rita~ did, partially cooking the potatoes, onions and garlic in the frying pan, then adding all other ingredients into a baking dish. I baked for 30 minutes in a 350 degree oven, and it came out just right. I should have added a bit more salt and pepper for our tastes, but this did not detract from the recipe. I will definitely make this again. Thanks for posting Dreamer! Made for ZWT8 - Spain/Portugal and the Herbaceous Curvaceous Honeys.

name: maitre d  hotel butter
review: Very nice on cooked carrots! I'll have to make some more when I have good steaks in the house. I really liked the hit of lemon in this. Thanks for posting! Made for the Honeys for ZWT8

name: chambord brunch cocktail
review: YUMMY! I just loved this - of course, I tripled it and then doubled for 2 drinks! ;-) DH and I had one after dinner. Now I want another! Thanks for sharing a fab-u-lous drinkie poo, Elmotoo!

name: chanel no  6
review: This seemed so innocent, but boy do you feel it! : ) We enjoyed the combination of flavors but thought it had a little bit of a bitter edge, even so I'd make them it again, just not when I've driving later! Thanks for sharing gailann. Made for ZWT 8 by one of The Wild Bunch

name: italian dressing
review: I love the amount of mustard powder and lack of sugar in this recipe. The powder made it almost "creamy" which was a nice surprise. Definitely one of the best dressings out there. It seems like one of those recipes that an Italian grandma would make, simple but with a secret (the mustard powder). Thank you.

name: herbes de provence
review: This is a lovely combination of herbs, more complex than I've used before, I can't wait to try it on my roast chicken! Made for ZWT 8 by one of The Wild Bunch

name: dijon tarragon cream chicken
review: This dish was just amazing; the whole family loved it! I used 10% cream and doubled the sauce. Not a drop was left. Definitely a keeper! Made for ZWT8 - Bistro Babes

name: spinach salad with chorizo and apples
review: Very good salad...though I was not crazy about the dressing, but it grows on you as you eat the salad. The dressing is very tangy due to the cider vinegar, but it does blend well with the apples and other ingredients. I had to use Envy apples as I didn't have the others. I think the toasted pecans really added alot to this salad, but then I love pecans. DH and I really enjoyed this. Made for ZWT8 - Spain/Portugal, and the Herbaceous Curvaceous Honeys.

name: tuna sandwiches  nicoise style
review: I love this recipe. so refreshing to make as well, when it gets to hot outside to cook, like it did today. I used cherry tomatoes for this sandwhich, and I love the addition of haricot vertes to the recipe.

name: country garden omelet
review: This was a wonderful omelet, had lots of ingredients to make for a tasty meal. I had no sausage, so mine just had ham, which was fine. I also cut the cheese back, just added enough to give it a taste. I also added tomatoes as my garden is overflowing, so every recipe I can add tomatoes to I do. This would be great for supper, as it is a very filling omelet. Made for ZWT8

name: lemony lentil salad with salmon
review: This is a very tasty and pretty salad, full of flavors and textures. If you are like me, you may want extra dressing because you go overboard with the ingredients. Made for large-sized portions.

name: grilled mussels with red wine and chorizo
review: These were fabulous, we loved the sausage and tomato in the broth with mussels, my DH scrapped up every last bit. Super easy, I  skipped the grilling and just steamed the mussels in the pan. We'll be making this again, thanks for sharing! Made for ZWT 8 by one of The Wild Bunch

name: spiced spanish almonds
review: Loved these! Liked that they had a little kick, but not too much of one. This was my first time trying Marcona almonds, too -- I like them so much better than the garden-variety almonds! I'm pretty sure DH is going to wipe these out pretty darn quick, good thing I snagged some before I left for work, lol. Thanks for posting! Made by a fellow Honey for ZWT8

name: the best marinade for kabobs   beef  pork and lamb
review: This was good...but not the best!  I marinated beef kebobs and they turned out OK....a little on the sweet side for us.  I would consider using this recipe again but modifying it a bit to suit our taste!

name: spanish tortillitas de camarones  shrimp cakes
review: I halved the recipe and used whole salad shrimp. Absolutely delightful! Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT8- Spain/Portugal.

name: smoked salmon sushi
review: Yum! All the flavours were great together and the cream cheese gave a wonderful creaminess to the rice.

name: oven roasted potatoes with garlic and rosemary
review: These potatoes are just super. I sometimes find it difficult not to burn oven roasted potatoes but these were smooth as can be, maybe the slight boiling beforehand does the trick. We loved the garlic/rosemary flavour as well and as said the texture was spot on. I used small white potatoes, cut in half, skin-on. Made for ZWT 8 - Bistro Babes

name: chocolate raspberry clafouti
review: This was very different , never having a Clafouti before, it was less cakey then I expected but the flavors were still good. I didn't think it was done so cooked it some more, than wasn't sure if I over cooked. it  I topped with whipped cream and we enjoyed it. Made for ZWT 8 by one of The Wild Bunch

name: chicken and chorizo  leftovers in tasty disguise
review: What a great way to use leftovers!  I madre this in my rice cooker, which worked beautifully.  The only change I wade was to use a portuguese red pepper paste instead of tomato puree, which added a nice smokey flavor to the dish.  Made for ZWT8

name: trio of spanish nibbles   olives  almonds   chickpeas
review: Great appetizer idea.  I made 1/4 the recipe because there are just 2 of us and only one eats chickpeas. I sought but could not find the classic Spanish mixed-olive mix of manzanilla, arbequina, and empeltre olives, so I selected olives from Wegman's olive bar that most closely resembled the Spanish classics.  I made the aluminum foil packet, but I thought it crazy to put an opened aluminum foil pouch between 2 decorative bowls, so I found another bowl.  I love chickpeas, but these did not inspire me;  I added the smoked paprika with 3 minutes left, but it seemed to turn to gray immediately. They were okay. The olives tasted fine.  I had never had Marcona almonds before, and they were perfect.  Made for The Wild Bunch of ZWT8 during its tour of Spain.

name: salmon with lentils and mustard herb butter  saumon aux lentille
review: Mmmmm.  Nice combination, lentils and salmon.  The butter is lemony and just a hint of mustard.

name: spanish burgers with romesco and manchego cheese
review: This was just ok for us, DH really didn't care for the sauce I liked it a little more. I used yellow pepper in place of the red. It's always good to try something new even if it's not exactly to our liking - thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8 by one of The Wild Bunch

name: grilled camembert sandwiches  or brie
review: This was a nice lunch today. I found the amount of Camembert to be too much and had to take most of it off. I just loved the peppered oil though and will definitely use that in recipes to come. I used a panini press (not the flat griddle plates) but didn't close it. The grill marks look nice and it worked just great. Made for ZWT8. Thanks CJAY! :)

name: brie cherry pastry cups
review: Wow! These were fabulous! So simple, but very tasty and they look great :) I cut the recipe down, using a quarter of  a package of puff pastry and made 9 which we devoured. I love the contrast of the sweet jam and the savoryness of the brie. The directions were very clear and they came out perfect. These would make a great party dish. Thanks for sharing Lainey! Made for ZWT 8 by one of The Wild Bunch.

name: sunset orzo with spanish shrimp
review: I'm with ya, Boomette -- love the orzo! I had two pounds of shrimp, so I doubled the recipe. Really flavorful, and so vibrant in color. My only complaint was that I shouldn't have added the extra turmeric because it gave the dish a bit of a bitter undertone, but that was my own fault (I was looking at the extra spoonful and thinking I shouldn't add that much turmeric, but then I just tossed it in anyway). Other than that, this recipe was perfect for us. I'm sure I'll be making this one again, thanks for posting! Made for The Honeys for ZWT8

name: good  n easy macaroni salad
review:
A delicious and easy salad....DH has been thoroughly enjoying this for his lunch at work!
I added a small handful of grated low fat cheddar on top ( couldn't help myself....pasta and cheese just go hand in hand for me!)....
Thanks Diner. Made for PRMR.

name: jennifer s cobbler
review: I wasn't sure that I would like this, since I've never tried port before, but I thought this was really pretty good. I used ruby porto, and I topped this with fresh raspberries, blackberries and a strawberry. I especially liked eating the icy berries out of this. I think I used too big a glass, so it ended up being a bit much port for me, but I'm kind of an alco-weenie. I liked how sweet the drink was, though. Thanks for posting! Made for The Honeys for ZWT8

name: eva s chunky guacamole
review: This is a tasty version of guacamole! We served it for my MIL's b-day celebration, and it was gone! I did use lime instead of lemon, as I had it on hand. And next time, I may use a jalapeno instead of the serrano chili, as we like a bit more heat!  Thanks for sharing, Boomette!

name: filled croissant sandwich
review: I think this was the most luxurious breakfast I've ever eaten! Normally I like cheese on my egg sandwiches, but the heavy cream made cheese unnecessary. I used cold-smoked salmon and extra fresh dill because I love it. Definitely too rich for everyday, but perfect for an occasional treat. This would be a lovely addition to a brunch table. Thanks for posting! Made for The Honeys for ZWT8

name: warm brie salad dressing
review: This was very very good! Unfortunately, my cheese separated as you can see (it's a little lumpy) but the flavour was there for sure. I have a feeling that my pot was too hot. I just love capers and they were great in this, adding the right amount of salt. I used spinach and I think that this rich dressing would be too much for a delicate green. Delicious! Made for my fellow Chef Gone Wild for ZWT8. Thanks twissis! :)

name: little grilled mushroom bites
review: Very easy and quick to put together while awaiting the main dish to be grilled!

name: aussie rissoles  cross between a patty and a meatball
review: Perfect for an easy weeknight dinner and these were a typical Aussie rissole. Made with around 500 grams quality lean mince and exactly as written. Made 6 largish rissoles though could easily make 8smaller. Served with oven cooked potato gems and salad. My husband said he enjoyed firing up the barbie for these little beauties. Photo also to be posted

name: spiced sweet potato balls
review: I made 2/3 scaled down version of this recipe. Easy to make and served with sweet chilli sauce (asian style)and sour lite cream. I used a blended gluten-free flour to make these suitable to my gluten-free diet. IFor my taste, I enjoyed these, but would leave out the sugar next time round. Photo also to be posed

name: deviled carrots
review: My family enjoyed these carrots for something a little different to the way I normally do my honey carrots. I just used white pepper as I dont care for cayenne pepper and used dijon mustard. I would cut back a little on the butter next time. Photo also to be posted

name: spiced beef kebabs   new zealnd
review: I only marinated about an hour or so and did not season with salt and pepper.  Just terrific!

name: bud s   distract the neighbors   grilled chicken
review: Wow! This chicken was moist and had great flavor. My rosemary in the garden was looking a bit dried up so I used some dry rosemary too. My DH grilled 4 marinated chicken thighs on nonstick foil on our gas grill to reduce flare ups. The flavor was superb, and I will be making this again! Made for NAME tag.

name: peppered rib eye steaks
review: I love pepper and this was no exception! My ground red pepper is very strong and I used double the amount (oops!) so that was a bit much. Great rib eye! I enjoyed this with a nice salad. Made for ZWT8. Thanks Dreamgoddess! :)

name: tomato cabbage soup
review: I made as directed, but I'd do one thing differently next time - leave out the extra sugar. I thought the chili sauce gave the soup a sweet flavor, with the added sugar it was a little on the sweet side for us.

name: quick and easy avocado salsa
review: This is a very refreshing combination of vegetables.  I enjoyed it wrapped in a flour tortilla. Although I just eyeballed the amounts, I did think that the proportion of green onion was rather too much. Next time, I will halve the green onion. The salsa is quite flavorful, though I believe it would be even more so with the addition of a small amount of salt, if the diet of the persons partaking allowed it. I am happy I tried this recipe.

name: grilled skewered beef
review: Beef goes surprisingly well with pineapple.  This took no time at all to cook since I used a bit higher quality beef (what I had on hand).  It must have looked good because DH was all, "Ooh!  What's that?"

name: grilled watermelon
review: Not my cup of tea.  The end result was a slimy piece of watermelon that was less sweet and juicy.

name: bandito eggs
review: Oh so delicious!!! I made this as listed but didn't know what size tortilla to use, so of course I chose the 12"! I made this pretty much as listed except for a couple of small changes - decided to chop the tomato instead of slicing it, mixed some cheddar with the monterey jack cheese and used a pie plate under the broiler and served it right on the plate instead of a hot casserole dish. Made for ZWT8. Thanks CJAY! :)

name: deviled carrots
review: I can't leave any stars for this recipe because the carrots were so hot we couldn't eat them. I only used 1/2 tsp. of cayenne. We normally enjoy spicy food but not this time. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT8- Australia/New Zealand.

name: best ever summer strawberry spinach salad
review: This was a quick and simple salad, we enjoyed the lovely dressing. I chose to do mandarin oranges as I am allergic to strawberries and it was nice. My husband would have liked the strawberries, so next time I will make it for him.

name: beef and bacon rissoles with gravy
review: Outstanding! We loved everything about this recipe. All of the flavors worked well together and the gravy was great. It was very easy to make too. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT8- Australia/New Zealand.

name: banana shake   smoothie
review: Great smoothie - too bad I can't read instructions.  I just blended everything but the cinnamon together and my grandson devoured all of it!  Perfect mix of flavors with the orange juice, milk and bananas.  Thanks for sharing a keeper for our family!

name: sweetheart salad
review: This fit what I had in the frig - chicken breasts and spinach, so I was pleasantly rewarded with a very nice salad which is a meal by itself. Great flavor and easy to prepare. Made for ZWT8.

name: caribbean rice and beans
review:
