These cookies came out soft and delicious. I loved to big amount of spices in them especially the ginger and cinnamon.
I had problem to remove them from the pan, I used a silicon spatula for this.
In any case they came soooo delicious that I think I will make these again and take some photos for your recipe.

name: roasted carrots
review: Great way to fix carrots. The dressing and parm really made them special! Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8.

name: roasted carrots
review:
A real tasty sidedish or appetizer!
I used homemade dressing and followed the recipe.
For some reason sometimes the kind of carrots don't turn soft after baking them a long time (it's not the first time), but I don't care and I love them as they are.
Thanks a lot for the reicpe all my family loved them.

name: parsley  garlic    scallion mashed  potatoes
review:
I used this as side dish and all loved it.
I did not add butter (even if I know that I would love it, I used little more milk instead) to avoid more calories and animal fats, but the recipe is soo good, that nobody missed it!
Thanks a lot for thei great recipe!

name: easy baked macaroni and cheese
review: This was creamy, cheesy and extra tasty with the onions and garlic. We really enjoyed it. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8.

name: green jasmine rice
review: So simple, so good!  Made as directed, and will make again, for sure!  DH went back for seconds.  Made for The Wild Bunch for ZWT8's trip to India.

name: leap year cocktail
review: Do I have to wait 4 more years for another?  This was slightly sweet and much to my liking.  Took a lot of self-control to stop at one. My favorite martini this week so far.  Made for The Wild Bunch for ZWT8 for its trip to Britain.

name: black bean taco salad with lime vinaigrette
review: Excellent main dish salad, or remove the chicken and serve as a side.  Fantastic flavor, but next time I will double the dressing!  Used a garden fresh tomato .... delish!

name: lucky limey float
review: Wow! This was so good. Made as written and loved it. Never thought about using sherbet in a float. This is my new fav. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8.

name: easy and tasty barbecue chicken sandwiches in the crock pot
review: Flavor will totally depend on the quality of your bbq sauce.  But this recipe gets 5 stars for when I got ease.  I took my chicken breast right from the freezer and tossed them in the crock pot with the sauce and onion. The house smelled wonderful when I got home from work. I shredded the chicken because it was falling apart.  Next time I may shred it a little sooner so it can really soak up the sauce.

name: soft chocolate oatmeal cookies
review: I LOVE the flavor of these. I often make oatmeal chocolate chip cookies, but it never dawned on me to add cinnamon. To amp the flavor up a bit I used a combination of chocolate chips and cinnamon chips, which was really delish. My cookies spread quite a bit, though, which made for a crispier cookie than I had hoped for. This was quite possibly due to user error! I will still highly recommend the recipe and will definitely give them another shot soon! Made for ZWT 8: The Wild Bunch.

name: salmon patties   chef s recipe
review: These were a great change of pace from my usual "cracker crumb and egg" salmon patties! My 2 year old especially enjoyed them; I think she ate more than me! We liked the texture of the mashed potatoes, it really sort of made these a cross between a fish cake and a potato pancake. I used about 12 ounces fresh cooked salmon, and since leftover mashed potatoes don't exist in my house I boiled and mashed a few. As a result they were unseasoned, and I think if you are going to use unseasoned potatoes there needs to be a bit more spice in the rest of the recipe. I added a fair amount of salt, and think more Worcestershier, some Old Bay or Cajun spices would have been even better. I cut back on the pepper for little tastebuds, using 1/2 t, and that was more than enough to feel the bite and get the flavor. I think 2 t would have been way too much for us. Thanks for posting; we'll be making these again! Made for ZWT 8: The Wild Bunch.

name: corn marrakesh
review: I only made one ear of corn as I had another recipe to try at the same time. My son and I each had a half ear of each and had fun comparing the two recipes. We really liked all the different spices on this one and the use of the foil made it so easy. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8.

name: gourmet mushroom risotto
review: Great risotto! Easy to make and I even cheated and bought sliced mushrooms. Thanks for posting.

name: 15 minute baked halibut with herbs
review: We loved this, it packed a lot of flavor.  In fact, DH wants to use this treatment on his freshly caught rockfish, which can also stand up to the capers. We have fish often, and this is a welcome change from our usual delicious Mrs. Dash Garlic 'n' Herb and Mrs. Dash Fiesta Lime seasoning with a smothering of butter to keep the fish moist.  The fresh herbs make a huge difference, and we are worth it!  Made for The Wild Bunch for ZWT8's visit in Britain.

name: chicken curry with coconut milk
review:
Wow! This is one of my favorite curries. I love the spices mixture especially the flavor of the star anise in it and the rich coconut sauce.
I love curries and I like the variations of them.
I really can recommend this recipe!

name: curried egg salad sandwich on raisin bread
review: This was DEEE-licious!  I cut the recipe down to 1 serving - I made it for my breakfast - and was very pleasantly surprised. I was a bit skeptical of the ingredient list as I am not very adventurous when it comes to cooking, and for me this was an adventurous recipe! With that said, I followed the recipe exactly as written and had a wonderful breakfast. The egg salad itself has a bit of bite and some sweetness from the coconut. I used Fage plain greek yogurt and organic mayo, so that made it nice and creamy. Loved the chopped roasted cashews too - crunch factor is a plus for me. I served open-face on gluten-free raisin bread and that really worked for me - the sweetness of the bread was a perfect compliment for the egg salad. BTW - I skipped the spinach as I didn't have any on hand, but did not miss it to be honest. Excellent recipe Cookgirl - thanks for posting. Made for ZWT8 and the Herbaceous Curvaceous Honeys!  Photo to follow...

name: yogurt lassi with  sweet or savory variations
review: Great recipe! We had a surplus of gorgeous pears in our CSA box this week so I decided to try the Autumn variation with a peeled pear added in. It was FANTASTIC. My kids loved it, and for me it was such a lovely reminder that Fall is around the corner :). I can see this coming into regular rotation here, and I'm grateful because it may become a nice substitute for our very expensive kefir habit. BTW I  used cinnamon instead of cardamom based on what was on hand, and only 1 tsp of honey instead of the sugar. Delish! Made for ZWT 8: The Wild Bunch.

name: zucchini marinata  marinated zucchini salad
review:
I had giant zucchine to use and I din't know what to do as I like to change recipe.
As I found this recipe I knew that this will be great for them.
I had to make a change as I was using a giant zucchini: I peele the zucchini,cut theit lenghtwise, discarded the seeds and sponge part, placed in a bowl and added 1 teaspoon salt.
After 2 hours I rinced and drained it. In this way most of the exceded was away and I could follow the recipe as described.
I used small leaved basil for it.
Thanks a lot for the recipe we really enjoyed this fresh salad! :)

name: raita  yogurt dill sauce
review: The perfect raita- simple to prepare and very tasty alongside spicy Indian dishes. Reviewed for ZWT8 tour of India. Photos also to be posted

name: original indian naan bread
review: I made these on my griddle. I made half with garlic powder and half with curry powder. I liked both ways but the curry was outstanding. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8.

name: chicken agrodolce  an italian sweet and sour chicken
review: This is a very tasty and easy to prepare chicken dish. I served it with a mushroom risotto and steamed broccoli and it was a fantastic meal. I think I'd up the sour flavor next time a bit because it was a little sweet...but that's a matter of taste. Definitely a repeater!

name: orange marmalade marinated salmon  chicken or pork
review:
This dish was my DD choice! I wondered she took a soo sweet fish recipe!
The choice was great and the fish was delicious.
We used what we had on hand (defrosted from the freezer): 2 small salmon filets and 2 pangasius filets. I really can't say which was better as the result was really top!

Thanks a lot for this recipe!

name: grandma little s 50 year old shortbread recipe
review: These cookies are tender like shortbread, but sweet like sugar cookies.

name: iced mint and cucumber gin
review: This was an interesting drink, it was surprising how dominant a little bit of cucumber can be. After the first tasting, we decided it needed something so added a couple of mint leaves and I increased the gin. This went well with our spicy indian dinner. Made for ZWT 8 by one of The Wild Bunch

name: bombay chops with corn and cumin raita
review: The spice mix was just right for the pork, not too much and not little.  I never knew what a raita was. Now I do, and it is delicious!

name: garlic rice   india
review: This is a great rice recipe. We loved the nuts and garlic flavor. I served it with chicken and raita. Will definitely make again. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8.

name: carrabba s italian grill s penne franco
review: Just love these ingredients, but increased the servings to 3 and changed things a bit.  I sauteed the mushrooms after cooking the garlic.  I then added 1 1/2 cups  of chicken broth thickened with 3 T of cornstarch and the juic of a lemon to the pan and brought it to a boil.  Once thickened I added the other ingredients to warm them through and tossed in 1/4 cup of fresh chopped parsley.  Delicious and light!

name: tex mex breakfast sausage cups
review: I found these a little lack luster.  Cooking time off as well.  Need extra time.  With some tweaking could possibly be better.

name: chicken in white wine
review:
Delicious! We loved this tender and flavorful chicken. The bacon, garlic and wine made the sauce very special. I used twissis' recommendation and added the wine, chicken stock, garlic, and seasonings to the pan at the same time, along with a cornstarch slurry to thicken the sauce. It worked perfectly. The chicken was very tender and the sauce was the perfect consistency. Thank you sharing this wonderful recipe.
**Made for ZWT 8 Great Britain**

name: salmon tikka
review: This recipe deserves extra stars! ******** I didn't make kebobs but used the marinade on Coho salmon fillets and skipped the bell peppers. Reserving a couple of TBLS of the marinade, I spread the mixture on the flesh side of the fish and let it set for about 45 minutes. I pan grilled this in a cast iron frying pan with the olive oil, cooking it skin side down until it was about 3/4  done then flipped it and cooked if for just a few minutes on the flesh side. After removing the fish I wiped out the pan because it had some yogurt scorches and then added back the remaining marinade with a few TBLS of heavy cream. I warmed that and served it with the salmon. The flavors of the salmon with with the yogurt and spices were amazing, I cut way back on the red pepper so this was spicy w/o being too hot thought it definitely had some zing. It was a party in your mouth!!! : ) This is one of our favorite dishes of the tour so far, thanks so much for sharing! Made for ZWT 8 by one of The Wild Bunch.

name: stoved chicken  chicken casserole with potatoes  bacon and onion
review: This was VERY delicious. Made as written except I used chicken breasts, and I baked for exactly 2 hours. Flavors were delicious and I really liked that I could put it in the casserole dish, stick it in the oven and forget about it!  Will definitely make this again diner!  Made for ZWT8 and the Herbaceous Curvaceous Honeys.

name: peach melba shortbread bars
review: It is rich, and sort of decadent. I liked them sort of warm, although it is true that they cut better when they are completely cool. Once they are cooled I like to microwave my piece so I can have it warm again. And the combination of jams are really good, and I wouldn't change a thing.

name: broken egg curry
review: Tantalizing!  This was like eggs poached in salsa, but with coconut milk thrown in.  The coconut taste was distinct but not overbearing, and we were pleased.  I used sweet Korean chiles as I was unsure how spicy this would come out; they were extremely mild, so we would opt for jalapenos next time (we are cautiously working our way up the heat scale).  My photos show 1) the skillet just after the eggs were dropped in, 2) the skillet just prior to serving, and 3) served with Green Jasmine Rice on the plate.  As the eggs sank into the sauce, it became difficult to tell how done the eggs were; make sure that any visible white is fully set before serving.  We ate all of the eggs, but saved the remainder of the delicious sauce for a future meal.  If you want the sauce to congeal more, you might mix 1 tablespoon of cornstarch in the cilantro/chillie/coconut milk mixture before adding to the skillet.  Thank you for sharing this recipe!  Made for The Wild Bunch of ZWT8 for its visit in India.

name: coconut oil roasted sweet potatoes
review: I really enjoyed this sweet potatoes;my first time preparing these. Coconut oil is so good.

name: green peas and mushrooms
review: I used frozen peas, but I didn't boil them.  I just threw them in the pan after sauteeing the mushrooms and onions.  I also used butter instead of vegetable oil--the veggies deserved it!  Thanks for posting.  Made for the Lively Lemon Lovelies, ZWT8.

name: bombay barbecued chicken
review: I used bone-in thighs and mild curry powder to make this delightful chicken dish. We enjoyed it very much and will make it again. I served it with your raita recipe and garlic rice. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8.

name: wilton stabilized whipped cream
review: Kitten, I knew I could count on you!  I followed your directions and added 1/4 teaspoon of vanilla while whipping, and saved that for my future reference as Recipe #485591.  I had no trouble with the gelatin setting too much before mixing. I turned down my Verona Assistent DLX to the lowest beating setting while I drizzled in the water-gelatin mixture, and then turned it up to high to finish whipping.  My heavy whipping cream had come straight from the refrigerator but it was not uber-cold.

name: scottish pancakes  pikelets
review: Yum, yum, yum! We are VERY particular about our pancakes around here so I was a little bit nervous about making something different, but these went over like...well...hotcakes! I made a double recipe but kept the sugar at 1/4 c and I am glad; we don't like a lot of sugar in general and 1/2 c would have been waaayyy sweet for us. I also made self-rising flour with spelt and white wheat flours and the texture of the cakes still came out light and fluffy. My kids really went bananas over these; DS ate 8 of them, I think. We all agreed that they are best spread with strawberry jam, which is also a departure from our "pancakes and syrup" norm. Thanks for posting, I think we'll revisit these little gems often! Made for ZWT 8: The Wild Bunch.

name: cooling mint cucumber raita
review: I only made half the recipe for the 2 of us. It went very well with your chicken recipe (482144) and garlic rice. We thoroughly enjoyed this fine meal. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8.

name: brown sugar and mustard glazed corned beef
review:
We loved the salty/ sweet combination of this corned beef. I cooked a 3-1/2 lb. corned beef in a 4 quart crock pot, using the spice packet included with the corned beef, and adding 1 cup water to the crock pot. I cooked it on "high" for 2 hours, then reduced the temperature to "low" for 4 hours. The corned be was very tender, and the sweet glaze added a wonderful finishing touch. Thank you for sharing this easy, tasty recipe.
**Made for ZWT 8 Great Britain**

name: the brits inspire iceland   stilton  or blue  cheese sauce
review: We loved this! The sauce really made this dish but then Stilton is one of our favorite cheeses. I served it with roasted new potatoes w/ lemon horseradish and a salad. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8.

name: baileys mint chocolate martini
review: What's not to love?  i love Bailey's Mint Chocolate, and the vanilla vodka gave a subtle vanilla assist.  Thanks, Boomette!  Made for The Wild Bunch for ZWT8's visit to Britain.

name: apples with honey
review: An easy and delicious way to dress up apples. Served over a scoop of vanilla ice cream!

name: sambal oelek   condiment
review: Saving this one!

name: spiced indian burger  1
review: This was very tasty, I liked the extra moistness from the yogurt even though it made the meat cook darker in places on the outside more than I prefer. Made for ZWT 8 by one of The Wild Bunch

name: spring green salad
review: This was quite a simplistic salad, and we all liked it. Made as written but allowed a variety of dressing to be used by the family - DH used raspberry viniagrette, I used a lime viniagrette and DD used buttermilk ranch. Will make this again as it is a change from our normal spinach salad or romaine salads with so many extras. Sometimes it's good to get back to basics!  Made for ZWT8 and the Herbaceous Curvaceous Honeys.

name: spicy indian burger 2
review:
A very flavorful burger, I especially liked the cumin and corriander. I skipped the flour step.
Made for ZWT 8 by one of The Wild Bunch

name: roasted  new potatoes with lemon horseradish
review: Gosh, these were good! I cooked them in the oven and they were perfect. I served them with salmon and a tossed salad. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8.

name: welsh chipple and bacon pie
review: This is very good. I especially enjoy the crust. I made this into individual pies.

name: everyday bread  french bread  abm bread machine
review:
I was looking for a recipe for my new baguette pans and thought of your French Bread. Came out spectacular; they gobbled these us and asked for the recipe. Thanks Angie.
Rita

I know you have had good reviews, but I always enjoy getting them. I 've been looking for a nice French Bread recipe for my ABM. Love this one and made a couple of small breads and 4 large buns for paninis. Followed the recipe except I used onecup whole wheat flour; I did add water, but I seems to do that for every recipe.I love the crust, the texture. Will be making this one againa and again. Thanks. I included a pic of my prize.
Rita

name: martha s spicy sweet chicken wings
review: Can you say "killa" wings?  These were great. I mixed up the "sauce" last night and marinaded them overnight - though my sauce came out more like paste and was not really pourable!  Not sure why...but I massaged the sauce all over the wings through the bag. I took them out of the fridge when I got home before putting them in the oven, to bring them close to room temperature. Baked them as directed and was worried they were getting a bit too charred after 35 minutes, so turned my oven down to 325 and flipped them all over. I think I could have doubled the vinegar sauce, as I was not able to liberally coat the wings, so next time I make these I will double that portion. DD didn't want anything to do with them, but ended up eating more of them than DH or me!  Just goes to show you should not judge a wing by its color! These were pretty charred looking, but the meat was tender (not dry) and they were spicy - though it was a delayed response...my mouth was a bit on fire by the time I finished my portion. Thanks for posting this keeper - nice variation from my regular wings, and sure to impress your wing buddies. Made for ZWT8 and the Herbaceous Curvaceous Honeys.

name: muglai chicken
review: Reviewed for ZWT8 visit to India. I used chicken breast fillets cut into smaller, thinner pieces in place of the thight, but otherwise stuck to the recipe as written. This was an easy and very tasty Indian chicken dish.Seemed like a long list of ingredients but came together very easily. I added the bay leaves with the cardamon pods (not stated in the instructions) Great recipe that I would happily make again. Photo also to be posted

name: creamy ham casserole
review: My family gave this 3 stars.  It was good, but it lacked the "WOW" factor that I was hoping for.  I did add some extra cheese to the top.  If I make it again I may try the optional crushed croutons on top.  That maybe the added umph I am looking for.

name: tandoori marinade
review: Wonderful marinade recipe. Such an easy recipe and such wonderful, tasty and moist chicken. My whole family enjoyed this marinade used on chicken breast fillets. Photo also posted. Reviewed for ZWT8

name: lamb korma
review: This was really yummy! The flavors were well rounded,and the sauce was rich and creamy. I cut the cayenne in half as I was serving people who really don't like heat, and they loved it.  The ingredient list looks long, but this went together really fast.  To save a bit of time, I quartered the onions and then tossed them into the food processor along with the garlic and ginger (cut in small pieces) and let the machine do the chopping work for me.  I used pork shoulder this time, just to try something different, but I'm sure I would love it with lamb as well.  Made for ZWT8.

name: lemony radish salad
review: I very rarely give low-star reviews but for this recipe...well, I really wanted to like this salad because it was so simple, but it just didn't work for us. DH and I both agreed that the lemon overpowered the radishes or cancelled out the radishes - there just wasn't much flavor for whatever reason. This just seemed to need a little something else to make it pop. I tend to agree that some thinly sliced onion might bring up the flavor a notch or two. We did have leftovers so I will add some onion to it and see how that works out. Thanks for posting - made for ZWT8 and the Herbaceous Curvaceous Honeys.

name: sandra s key lime pie
review: Colleagues loved this - only problem is people are asking me to bring pie in all the time! Really couldn't be easier either....

name: diabetic bombay chicken
review:
Light, diet-friendly, easy dinner. I sprinkled those wonderful curried almonds on top of the chicken when served, was the right time? With so many ingredients and so many steps, it would help to put the ingredients in the order to be used. As for the brown rice, I buy a quality brown rice and soak it prior to cooking, and cooked it with defatted broth from Recipe #369106 (which provided great-tasting chicken).
Made for The Wild Bunch for ZWT8's trip to India.

name: mushroom masala
review: Reviewed for ZWT8 visit to India. Loved these mushrooms. I think next time though I might tone down the red hot chilli powder (crushed red chillis) a little though. Having said this thoug, I really enjoyed this dish. Photo also to be posted

name: carrots garam masala
review: Reviewed for ZWT8 visit to India. Loved these carrots and they made a tasty, quick and simple vege side for our dinner tonight. Photo to be posted

name: gobi ki sabzi  dry cauliflower curry
review: This was really good. I like cauliflower, but it can be kind of bland. This really woke it up, and made a very pretty dish to put on the table as well. The blend of spices worked really well. I used a couple of roma tomatoes from the garden, cherry tomatoes cut in half would probably work well, too. I sliced the onions thinly, instead of chopping them, which I think looks better on the plate. Made for ZWT8.

name: citrus infused strawberries
review: This was such an easy dessert to put together and was the perfect ending to a great meal. Such a simple way to serve strawberries, yet so elegant. I really enjoyed my strawberries and will definitely be serving this recipe again. Photo also to be posted. Reviewed for ZWT8.

name: fried pineapple rice vegan
review: What a terrific tasting rice dish!  I loved all the flavors and it couldn't look any prettier.

name: indian appleous 500
review: Amazing! Amazing! Amazing! The blend of spices worked really well with the chicken and apples, and the coconut milk. Nothing was overwhelming, but you could still taste everything very well, which is just awesome! Will be making this again!

name: 007  martini
review: Classic martini, got to enjoy the taste without feeling knocked over.  Perfect.  DH looks more like Bond to me right now.  Made for The Wild Bunch for ZWT8 for its trip to Britain.

name: the black and black
review: Something different - just subtly sweet, so only for people who normally like stout. Very good!

name: onion salad   indian inspired
review: This was pretty good - though my onions were not that sweet and I thought that they would be. I sliced the onions very very thin, as we like them, and I think that made it work for us. I will experiment with this salad - maybe as a side on a relish tray. Sweet onions will definitely bring this up a notch - I will get some and revisit my review. Quick and easy to make - could not get much simpler. Thanks for posting - made for ZWT8 and the Herbaceous Curvaceous Honeys.

name: indian spinach salad
review: Reviewed for ZWT8. Great salad and loved the Indian flavours through the very tasty dressing. I used baby spinach leaves and mango chutney. Couldn't source any golden raisins (they are very hard to get here) so used sultanas as a substitute.Using gluten-free ingredients, this was suitable for my gluten-free lifestyle. Photo also to be posted.

name: roast chicken with lemon  honey and rosemary
review: I made this tonight using 2 split chickens and it was fantastic!  I put a rosemary sprig under each breast, drizzled the sauce over top, and placed cut lemon slices over top with chopped rosemary leaves and salt and pepper.  I omitted the shallot, and basted the chicken half way through cooking.  I also baked it part of the time using convection so it was nice and crisp.  This was fantastically delicious....will make it again!

name: vegetarian biryani
review: I really love this rice recipe. I thought it would be heavy, because of the potato mixed in, but it wasn't. And this a bit on the spicy side, but I kind of liked it that way. I thought the spicyness was fitting was for this kind of recipe.

name: vanilla sugar scones
review: Wow, I think the fresh vanilla bean did these scones some wonders! That and the sour cream, making the scones moist. I love how these came out, and they were so good warm. They last very well over a period of a couple of days.

name: indian style pumpkin soup
review: An easy pumpkin soup to make, though I thought it was lacking in flavour. The ingredients list coconut milk and then the instructions say to add the coconut cream. I think the Korma paste I used must have been really mild as I think I could have doubled the paste and would like to use maybe chicken stock instead of the water to give extra flavour. Photo to be posted

name: spiced pudding cake
review: So tasty I almost chucked my diet out the window!  DH had second helpings, with a BIG smile on his face.  Served with a dollop of Recipe #485591, this was scrumptious, it could lead to a proposal.  Yeah, that good.  Once cooked, it's almost as if the cake is sitting in a moat, so there is gooey stuff to pour over the cake.  The cake itself was not overly spicy, and would not be confused with gingerbread during tasting.  Don't be surprised if the plate is licked clean. ETA: This was even better the second day! Made for The Wild Bunch for ZWT8 for its stop in India.

name: kittencal s jumbo bakery shop blueberry sour cream scones
review: Devine...especially served with Devonshire cream.

name: saffron rice
review: Excellent, all the flavors came through, with a slight fruity finish from the sultanas.  This would be best with a plainish entree.  Made for The Wild Bunch for ZWT8 for its trip to India.

name: hannah s cucumber tea sandwiches
review: Dainty, delicious and impressive!

name: classic strawberries and cream
review: A lovely simple strawberry dessert. The Grand Marnier cream was perfect. Reviewed for ZWT8.

name: spicy garbanzos
review: This smelled so delicious while it was cooking...but it was waaaayyyyy too hot for my wimpy tastebuds!  DH loved it, though he commented as well, "This is really hot!"  Very easy to make and since DH was so pleased, it is something I will prepare again...just not sure why this came out with so much heat - I followed the recipe as written...but I guess that's why they're called "Spicy Garbanzos" :)   Thanks for posting - made for ZWT8 and the Herbaceous Curvaceous Honeys.

name: blt   p  bacon  leek  tomato and potato  soup
review: Yum. I really enjoyed this soup and so did my kids; DH is not a fan of soups with too many veggies.. I added green onions and a bit of onion instead of leeks, omitted the bay leaf since I am not keen on the flavour and instead added a splash of beef broth and used fresh tomatoes instead of canned. Made for ZWT

name: the better butter chicken
review: This was a good dish to cook for a weeknight dinner. Not quite butter chicken for me, but a good enjoyable dinner with Indian spices. I used ground chilli powder (not Mexican chili blend) which is very hot....so just used 1/2 the amount stated. Photo also to be posted

name: mango ginger lassi
review: Very good! I used agave syrup in this, and light mango nectar. I really enjoyed the zing of the ginger in this. Thanks for posting! Made by a fellow Honey for ZWT8

name: classic saffron rice
review: These few, very quick, additions make a big impact on plain rice. I used veg broth and cut back on the water just a bit since white basmati is usually 1:1.5 - worked well and tastes nice without being overpowering.  Using fresh onion would make this a 5 star for me, but of course it wouldn't be as quick and easy as it was.

name: bakewell tart cocktail
review: Yum! Very drinkable for so many different alcohols in one place, lol. I also used Godiva Liqueur in place of the chocolate syrup. Sorry, no photo, since all my photo-ready glasses needed to be washed (didn't think anyone wanted to see my cheapie plastic cup). Thanks for posting! Made for The Honeys for ZWT8

name: spring green salad
review: Really a very nice salad - no muss, no fuss. I forgot to pick up croutons, so we skipped them, but really enjoyed the combination of flavors. I mixed some spring greens with some chopped iceberg, as I had less green lettuce than I thought. No matter, it was a tasty treat! Thanks for sharing, sofie-a-toast!

name: indian rice
review: This was a perfect rice side to serve with any Indian style main meal. I used basmati ricefor this recipe. Photo also being posted. Reviewed for ZWT8 tour of India.

name: thai stir fried vermicelli  pad wun sen
review: Very tasty Sue.  Thank you.

name: almond ice cream  dairy free
review: I really enjoyed this frozen treat. I agree with the other reviewer, that it does not have a creamy texture like ice cream, but I enjoyed the flavors. And when you cannot have dairy then your options are limited. To stay dairy free, one might try adding some coconut cream to the mixture to help with the texture. Made for Veg 'n Swap tag.

name: reduced fat alfredo sauce
review: I made this and it  was fantastic and perfect for my Baked pasta.

name: stuffed buns   chicken or paneer
review: These were great!  I made 1/2 with paneer, 1/2 with chicken.  I used a bit more cumin and garam masala than called for- maybe 1/8 teaspoon of each. These had a very nice flavor, and a little residual heat that stayed with you after each bite.  The chicken and paneer versions tasted distinctly different, but both were wonderful.  Three of us scarfed down the entire recipe for lunch, we liked them that much.  I'd like to try to freeze these, they'd be great in brown bag lunches.  Made for ZWT8.

name: bombay rice and peas
review: Easy, tasty, somewhat spicy, but not fiery.  Made brown rice the day before after soaking for 2 hours, then used chicken broth in a rice cooker, so today it was a piece of cake to make this recipe.  I love that this makes a huge pot of vegetable rice, I'm freezing my leftovers.  Made for The Wild Bunch of ZWT8 for its trip to India.

name: bombay barbecued chicken
review: This was a nicely spiced chicken dish, and I'm glad I tried it. Due to inclement weather, I used our indoor grill, so I didn't get great grill marks. However, this was a very moist breast, and the spice was just 'different' enough. Served with rice and a green salad, this made for a tasty dinner from another land! Thanks for sharing, Nif.

name: scrambled eggs with scallions and mushrooms
review: Delicious veggie combination in this! I cut this down to 1 serving (2 eggs), so I used 2 mushrooms, half of a serrano pepper, 1 green onion, and a whole small tomato (I love tomatoes in scrambled eggs). I served this with a warm piece of naan. Really enjoyed the mushrooms here, and will definitely be making this again. Thanks for posting! Made for The Honeys for ZWT8

name: kilt lifter  cocktail
review: This one left me a bit off-KILT-er, puckering from the lime juice and definitely impaired from the scotch and Drambuie. So I took an off-KILT-er photo for you.  Made for The Wild Bunch of ZWT8 for its visit to Britain.

name: killarney fudge pie
review: Luscious and decadent, I will definitely be making this pie again! Very rich and lovely with the pecans, it went together easily and was soon scenting my kitchen of chocolate. I could hardly wait to try, and I did sprinkle a touch of Cyprus sea salt over the slice, as I've been experimenting with salt/chocolate combos. Too wonderful - thanks so much for sharing, Dienia B.!

name: chinese roast chicken
review: Awesome! Beautifully moist and tender and I loved the aroma and taste the sesame oil gave the marinade. The little bit of left marinade was too good to go to waste so I watered it down and added flour to make a light gravy.

name: cool cucumber relish
review: So easy - we liked this a lot.  Agreed with twissis that it could use a touch of sweetness, so I added a bit of raw sugar.

name: classic strawberries and cream
review: Perfect and simple, what more could one ask for? I used Amaretto for the liqueur. I accidentally added the sour cream from the get-go, but everything whipped up just fine in the end. The flavored cream complements the berries beautifully. Thanks for posting! Made for The Honeys for ZWT8

name: grilled fillet steak with herbs
review: I cooked my steak on a cast iron grill pan under the broiler for 5 minutes.  That's all there was to it.  I didn't even have to turn it.

name: easy moong dal  mashed yellow split peas
review: I love most dal dishes, and this was great.  Not only is it really flavourful, considering how few ingredients there are, but it is simple to prepare.  It definitely took mine longer to cook than indicated; they weren't fully cooked through after 30 mins boiling, but I still added everything together and let it simmer with some extra liquid until the split peas were fully cooked. The only thing I changed was to only use 1/2 a lemon, I found it tangy enough for me.  Thanks Cookgirl!

name: easy cheddar walnut bread
review: This was a very nice, crusty bread however, I may have over-mixed it, as it was very crumbly. I did enjoy the savory flavor, and the crunch from the nuts. I'll make this again, and be very conscientious about the food processor. Thanks for sharing, FLKeysJen!

name: bombay spiced cashews
review: These were good, if a little strong for my taste. I have never really experienced curry and I think that I would reduce the curry by half, as I found it just a tad overwhelming. I rubbed some of the seasoning off, and was able to enjoy them more. I'm glad I tried these cashews, and DH has been eating away at them also! Thanks for sharing, Dreamer in Ontario.

name: chapatis  indian or kenyan wholewheat flatbread
review: I am not sure how to rate this one, so I am skipping stars and just adding a review. I had a lot of trouble with the dough; the first time I mixed it up using equal parts white wheat and whole wheat flour the dough was so wet I couldn't work with it. I decided I must have measured in error and tried again using all whole wheat flour and...the same thing. This time I just added as much flour as it took to be able to even touch the dough, but even then kneading wasn't going to happen. Given that other reviewers haven't had this problem I still suspect user error! The end product (after much cursing in the attempt to shape the dough LOL) was yummy, though, and my kids especially enjoyed them. I brushed the tops with butter after they came off the griddle to replicate my favorite Indian restaurant and they were quite tasty served with chana masala. I will definitely try again in the future. Thanks for posting, Nif. Made for ZWT 8: The Wild Bunch.

name: jeera rice
review:
We loved this rice veeeery much, who came perfect with a curry.
I was soo delicious that my DS reserved a portion to bring to school for lunch.

It's a 5 star recipe that only need an addtion to the directions: final addition of cashew nuts!

Thanks a lot for your recipe.

name: star anise ice cream
review:
What for a DELISH! I never thought to make ice cream with star anise, but this is really an incredible good recipe. I crushed the anise with the mortar and placed in a tea infuser. I heated the milk and cream mixture until boiling point, added the infuser, switched off the heat and waited until almost cold. After this I removed the infuser with the anise, heated again, added the egg until curd begins to form. I don't have and ice cream machine. I place the mixture in a metal bowl in the freezer. When ice begun to form I added the liqueur and broke the crystals with the fork. I repeated this step several times until a soft ice cream was formed. For this step sometimes (for other ice cream) I use the hand bender and it works well.
Thanks a lot for this recipe, I can't stand to offer this to my family this evening!

name: homemade english chocolate pudding
review: Other than the constant stirring time this was easy enough to make and tasted great. I used whole milk and chocolate chips. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8.

name: chicken   dumplings like grandma s  crock pot
review: This was very delicious and very easy to make. I did not use the chicken bouillion, just added a splash of chicken broth when the mixture got a little too thick. Instead of cooking chicken I used a package of /trader Joe's Just Chicken white meat chicken 12 ounce package and low sodium cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soups. I also added a package of frozen green peas 1 hour before the meal was completed..

name: tsr version of t g i  friday s black bean soup by todd wilbur
review:
TERRIFIC is all we can say,
Remember TGIF's...this soup MADE MY DAY!
Quick, delicious, healthy too!
HIGHLY recommended to you too!
For those in Australia, found black beans at Asian Grocery, TRUE!...vacuumed packed or dry, is up to YOU!
UPDATE: Made this again today! Got the WHOO HOO again is what I can say!

name: herb crusted fish fillets
review: I loved using the fresh herbs from my garden to make this. I used panko instead of the fresh breadcrumbs. I use a large swai fillet, which was not very thick so it cooked through in the pan without my having to turn on the oven. I did have quite a bit of the coating ingredients left, so I sliced some slender Asian eggplant, coated it, and also pan-fried that. It was a bit more fried food than I usually have but really turned out well - I might do this just with veggies another time. Update: I used the same crust ingredients - without the egg wash - with slices of veal liver - very very nice

name: carrots garam masala
review:
Loved these quick and easy, lightly spiced carrots. I intended to use the optional red chili powder, but instead I grabbed cayenne powder. It worked out fine though, we love the added zing that it brought to the dish. Thank you for sharing this quick and delicious recipe.
**Made for ZWT 8 India**

name: crempog  welsh leek and mushroom pancakes
review: I made this for breakfast this morning and had scrambled eggs on the side. It was very good and we thoroughly enjoyed it. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8.

name: chocolate chai latte cookies
review: These are a great bursting with flavor cookie that are very simple to make especially if using a stand mixer.  I used your "note" and used the swirled chips and used the individual spices as listed.  They are pretty sweet on their own so I did skip on the drizzle of icing and that made it easier to pack in lunches too.  I did not have any issues with the cookies being flat like the one reviewer - I really think it is based on the cake mix you use.  Some of the cake mix recipes you can use the cheaper mixes but others you can't and with this asking for a butter based cake mix I think you need a good mix.  Found and made during ZWT8.

name: taste of honey
review: WOW!  This is delightful.  I usually don't look for scotch drinks, but thought I'd try it with the honey and cream and boy is it nice!  **Made for ZWT8 2012**

name: indian marinade
review: A great marinade- super easy to put together and tasted delicious. I used chicken breast fillets, cut in half to make them thinner and marinated 24hours. Beautiful tender chicken with a mild curry marinade. Photo also being posted. Plenty of marinade for 4 chicken breast fillets. Reviewed for ZWT8

name: madras vegetable curry  vegetarian
review: This is what I would eat if I were a vegetarian. Very filling and satisfying.

name: sheila s famous mustard glazed corned beef and cabbage
review: Like magic! This three day process literally transforms the texture of the corned beef - more like ham with a deep delicious flavor. The glaze at the end makes it like corned beef candy! The recipe isn't as difficult as it looks - it is almost all cooking time, just 10 minutes actual work per day.

name: cumin spiced red lentil burgers
review:
We really enjoyed these spiced lentil burgers. I've never used red lentils before and found them to be lighter in taste than regular brown lentils. I made these as written with just a couple of changes. I was generous with the cumin, adding 2 tsp., and I substituted cilantro for the parsley because I thought that the cilantro would add more flavor to the burgers. Also, I used plain Greek yogurt for the sauce because I prefer the texture. The sauce complimented the lentil burgers nicely.
**Made for ZWT 8 India**

name: masala chai
review:
Delicious! I loved this yummy spiced chai. It was a nice change from the sweeter, spicier chai that I normally drink. My first 2 cups were warm, and I finished the rest off later in the day over ice. I actually think that I preferred it iced. It reminded me a lot of the Iced Chai Tea Latte served at Starbucks...only without the high price. I added about 4 peppercorns to the spice mix, other than that it was made as written. Thank you for sharing this wonderful recipe!
**Made for ZWT 8 India**

name: jack frost
review: This is a dangerous drink, it goes down so easily you might be tempted to have another.  DON'T.  Even if you can't taste the liquor in this delicious drink, it can still take you down.  Made for The Wild Bunch for ZWT8 for its trip to Great Britain.

name: ziti pepperoni casserole
review: Easy enough to make.  I added some leftover red, yellow, and green bell peppers.  Even with the added peppers, my family thought this was good, but lacking in flavor.  I got out the garlic salt, pepper grinder and parsley flakes for everyone to add.  Next time I will probably add some fresh garlic or Italian seasons to the mixture before baking.  This makes a lot! My box of ziti was a little smaller than the recipe called for but my 9 x 13 pan was filled to the rim.  If you have a small family, you may want to separate into 2 dishes, one for dinner and one for the freezer.  Served with fresh Italian bread on the side.

name: chicken curry with mango
review:
Wonderul easy curry especially for curry beginners!
I had to add frozen cilantro as at them moment I coudn't get fresh.
An other change was the use of only half coconut milk as what I wanted to use was the leftover of on other recipe. In any case this was perfect in this way as well.
Thanks a lot for your recipe.

name: spiced lemon rice
review:
This dish was more than welcome for my family.
The brigt yellow color and the lemon taste make of this dish a royal sidedish.
Highly recommende for any curry!

name: aviyal   indian mixed vegetable stew
review: I love the versatility of this recipe. You can use whatever vegetables you like or need to use up before they go bad. Easy and tasty.

name: berries  lemon curd cakes  rachael ray
review: De-lish! Perfect and simple, tangy and sweet! Glad I tried this; now I'll fix it for everyone! Thanks for sharing, JanuaryBride!

name: unstuffed stuffed curried eggplant
review:
A real good variation of the original stuffed curried eggplants.
I bought the ingredients I did'nt have at home as I wanted to know at it tastes.
I used the coconuts and I would use them again.
The list of the ingredients seems to be long, but it is really easy and doesn't require a lot of time.
All has gone and this is a clear message: yummy!
Thanks a lot for your recipe.

name: welsh lamb stew  cawl
review: We loved this wonderful lamb stew! I added a handful of frozen peas but otherwise made as directed. Very tasty, indeed. Thanks for sharing a great recipe. Made for ZWT 8.

name: chocolate chai tea
review: Smooth and delicious!  I did follow LIG's hint and strained the chai before serving and the beverage was wonderful.  Very easy to halve the recipe and have two wonderfully sized drinks.  Definitely do not skip on the salt - it makes everything just burst with good flavors.  I know I'll be making this more often this winter when the evenings get chilly.  Found and made during ZWT8.

name: snickerdoodle scones
review: OMG, these are delish!  I love scones and I love snickerdoodles.  I never thought to roll 'em into one!!  This will be revisited for sure!!  Thanks!!  **Made for ZWT8 2012**

name: potato griddle cakes
review: Very nice.  I chose these as healthier than mashed potatoes, and yet they provided a wonderful potato presence next to my Recipe#126865.  First I tried cooking with ghee in my All-Clad-style chef's pan; the batter stuck stubbornly to the pan.  So I switched to a non-stick pan with a little canola oil, which worked very well.  I chose this recipe partly because my new mixer has a food processing attachment and has a shredding plate just for potatoes for potato pancakes (how could I refuse!).  Next time I will also get some ligonberry jam to top them.  Made for The Wild Bunch of ZWT8 for its visit to Great Britain.

name: indian spiced coffee
review: Being the coffee lover that I am I was really excited to try this recipe.  It works out so well.  I used a dark roasted Sumatran coffee bean and made sure I brewed it a bit stronger than usual.  With that and the addition of these wonderful spices (especially love the nutmeg!) and using 2% milk worked out to be a very enjoyable beverage.  I love chai tea and love coffee more so this allows me the best of both hot beverage worlds!  Thanks Annacia.  Found and made during ZWT8.

name: indian cold coffee
review: YUM!  The only slight change was to sub in one cup of hot brewed coffee for the boiling water / instant coffee as I just don't ever have that on hand and mixed the sugar in that before allowing it to cool  This is a truly special cold coffee drink that takes minutes to make which is a great bonus!  Found and made during ZWT8.

name: baileys mint chocolate martini
review: This was very nice. I made it as written and enjoyed it a lot. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8.

name: chicken in white wine
review: This was very good.  I cut it down to just 2 thighs and 2 legs.  The meat came out very tender and juicy, and we really enjoyed the sauce over our rice.  I think I'd thicken the sauce next time, and add a few more herbs into it to boost the flavor a bit.  Overall, very good; and with a little tweaking- outstanding.  Made for ZWT8.

name: battered queenies with tartar sauce  manx scallops
review: The scallops were a 1 star and the tartar 3. The tartar is good, a bit basic but a nice flavor. The scallops were a lot of work and in the end a messy disaster. We thought the coating tasted like a cross between pancakes and doughnuts,  neither of which work with scallops. The batter came out very thick and I had to add more milk to get it to the point where I could coat the scallops. I used a deep fat fry thermometer and still the batter cooked so fast that if got very brown on the outside but the inside was still a bit moist. I tried adjusting the temp and it still didn't work . The texture was a bit like a pancake skin on scallops. They were inedible. Fortunately I cooked two small test batches so was able to save the rest of the scallops. Made for ZWT 8

name: indian spicy sour chickpeas with cauliflower
review: This was very good, and it makes quite a bit! I did reduce the oil a bit, and I omitted the cilantro since I can't abide the stuff (yep, I'm one of THOSE people!). I loved the inclusion of cauliflower in this classic dish. Next time I would like to try pureeing the tomatoes to make for a smoother "sauce". Also, it is totally reasonable to substitute garam masala for most of the spices in this dish (turmeric, clove, and salt excepted), which I did to make life easier. I did choose to omit the clove since my garam masala contained cinnamon and I thought that was close enough. Thanks for posting! Made for ZWT 8: The Wild Bunch.

name: nora ephron s bacon hash
review:
Deeeeelish!!!
Whacked a fried egg on top, just to be decadent.......a fantastic start to the day!!
Made for PRMR.

name: deep in the heart of texas bbq rub
review:
Mmmmm...sweet,spicy and oh so yum!
If this is a taste of the LoneStar State I'll have a second helping please!!!
Made for PRMR.

name: jhat phat sabzi  bell pepper paneer
review:
This swells really Indian and it's very easy to prepare.
I'm lucky to have an Indian shop in town near the stations as for this recipe I really would use the suggested spices including the methi (fenugreek leaves witch I also used for decoration).
Changes: I diced the bell peppers in big pieces and added some coriander as I love this in the dish as well.
I wil do this again as my children loved it veeeeery much!
Thanks a lot for the recipe.

name: indian chai iced coffee
review:
Mmhh... I confess that I coundn't wait 2 hours (step 6). So I placed the coffee in the freezer and after 30 minutes it was cold enough and I could proceed.
I prepared this delish only for me,
Thanks a lot for all your wonderful and genial coffee recipes and variations!

name: golden lemon rice
review: This went quite well with our Indian chicken for supper. I love lemon rice and this recipe did not fail me it. It had a nice lemon flavor, not to tart but enough that you could taste the flavor. Plus it looked lovely. Made for ZWT8.

name: tomato and mushroom omelette
review: This is a very good omelet, I enjoyed the addition of mushrooms and tomatoes. I like when potatoes are added to omelets, it is like a full meal then. I can not have cheese so mine was made minus cheese and it still was very nice.

name: whipped dessert topping
review: Made this for the whipped topping called for in Recipe#485113.  You taste milk and sugar.  After adding the sugar, oil, and gelatin, it didn't whip very stiffly.  After the 15 minutes in the freezer, it had jelled.  It performed as needed in Recipe#485113, giving it a real ice cream taste.  Thank you for sharing this recipe, Dancer.  Will use again.

name: glitterrazzi popcorn
review: Everyone at the party liked this popcorn.

name: tutti frutti ice cream
review: Bollywood fun!  Why have plain mango ice cream when you can kitsch it up with crazy fruit and candy!  I used a can of lite fruit cocktail, but you can hardly tell it's there.  I added diced dried kiwi and dried strawberry and halved Tutti Frutti Jelly Belly jelly beans.  I topped it with more Tutti Frutti Jelly Bellies and multi-colored chocolate covered sunflower seeds, and added a gingersnap accompaniment.  I used sweetened condensed milk, and the full recipe of Recipe#80011.  Except for the candy, this is how our Indian friends told us to make ice cream.  It's very easy, requires no special equipment, and tastes great!  What more could you want!  Made for The Wild Bunch for ZWT8 for its trip to India.

name: tomato and coriander soup
review: Yummy!  I'm used to Italian versions of tomato soup; with basil and oregano, so this was a really different experience.  I liked the coriander and pepper flavors- they really made the tomato sing.  I can't help thinking though, this would be even more amazing with a grilled cheese sandwich :D  Made for ZWT8.

name: cranberry banana oat bread
review: We enjoyed this banana bread, I really liked the cranberries and the touch of lemon helped give them some zing. I was a little short of banana so used a some applesauce. I did add a tsp of cinnamon and used whole wheat pastry flour. Made for ZWT 8 by one of The Wild Bunch.

name: chicken potato pie    shepherds pie
review: This is really comforting comfort food.  I was feeling a little under the weather when making this, but eating it perked me right up!  I used gravy instead of canned soup, and added some mushrooms.  Thanks for posting!  Made for the Lively Lemon Lovelies, ZWT8.

name: welsh rabbit  rarebit    sort of toasted cheese
review: Decadent and delicious!! This took about 5 minutes to make and is a real feel-good recipe. I used an old cheddar and all the rest of the ingredients listed and it was great! Made for ZWT8. Thanks Karen Elizabeth! :)

name: kachumber salad   india
review: Right now my garden has an abundance of tomatoes, onions, and cucumbers so this recipe fit the bill. This is a fresh, tart salad with a little kick to it. Only thing when I make this next time I will skip the lettuce, I think I would enjoy it with more cucumber and no lettuce. I felt my lettuce got wilted and therefore wasn't attractive. Made for ZWT8.

name: rachael ray s italian chicken and dumplings
review: This is the real review. I got lazy and used a 8 ounce jar of prepared pesto instead of making the pesto as posted. Otherwise, we stuck to the original recipe. We love the recipe, we love gnocchi in all forms. Easy and delicious.

name: aftershock
review: Packs quite a wallop, very liquory.  But then, this is actually 2 servings of liquor, not one.  Made for The Wild Bunch for ZWT8 for its trip to Great Britain.

name: roasted potatoes and green beans
review:
Delicious! We loved these quick, easy, and flavorful vegetables. Roasting is my favorite way to prepare vegetables, so I am always on the lookout for new recipes using this method. I was a little disappointed because I had to make this without the mushrooms. I went to use my brown mushrooms and they had gone bad. Other than that, I made this exactly as written and we loved it. Thank you for sharing this wonderful recipe...it is definitely a keeper!
**Made for ZWT 8 Great Britain**

name: shandy
review: We found this nice and refreshing, the limeade added a nice touch without making the beer sweet. A good alternative if your wanting something with a little less alcohol than a regular beer. Made for the Celebrity Tour of Great Britain & Ireland for ZWT 8 by one of The Wild Bunch.

name: cheddar shortbread bites
review: These are really yummy!  Buttery, crumbly, and just a hint of heat from the cayenne!  A perfect little nibble with a pre-dinner cocktail or glass of wine.  I made the dough in the food processor, and it came together in about 10 seconds.  What could be easier?  I also used the roll into a log and slice method, which saved me the time of rolling out the dough, so other than chilling, I think these took a total of 20 minutes to make :) I'll look forward to trying these again, with other toppings.  Made for ZWT8

name: spicy burger
review:
Super easy, and super tasty.......
Made for 123Hits.

name: wee willie winkee peanut butter oatmeal cookies
review: Great chewy cookie!  I followed the instructions except I could not find whole wheat pastry flour so I used a combination of whole wheat flour and all purpose to keep that lighter consistency that the pastry flour would provide.  Excellent flavors, nice slight crisp on the outside and fluffy goodness inside.  I did use the option of adding chocolate chips and made the "mistake" of using crunchy peanut butter instead of creamy but that actually was an added bonus.  I received 50 nice little round cookies using a small cookie scoop.  Perfect for bagged lunches and just an afternoon treat.  So glad I found this during ZWT8.

name: shrimp in a spicy ginger cilantro broth   clean eating
review: I made this on the stovetop. Based on the previous review I reduced the amount of cilantro used for the infusion and added fresh cilantro for garnish to taste. I quite liked it - I think next time I will try it with chicken instead of garlic since I prefer this over shrimp.

name: asparagus with curry butter
review: This was a simple and tasty side dish I served with Salmon Tika. I used my cast iron frying pan and kicked up the heat to give the asparagus a little bit of char. The lemon and curry are great together. Made for ZWT  by one of The Wild Bunch.

name: open face cheddar broil
review: Delicious, I made these for breakfast and my family really enjoyed! Thanks for posting, made for ZWT #8 :)

name: eggplant curry  indian
review: Very tasty, although mine was pretty spicy because I forgot to seed the chiles before chopping them. I ate this with some naan (wanted rice, but didn't have enough time). I really enjoyed this, though. Thanks for posting! Made for The Honeys for ZWT8

name: chapati  indian flat bread
review: I must admit I was a little nervous to make this recipe as I had never tried my hand at a flatbread before. It was so simple and easy though, I'm glad I tried it. I'll never buy Chapati again! It went great with the Kheema I made for dinner and my family was suitably impressed with the warm home made Chapati. Thanks for posting! Made for ZWT 8 :)

name: british style cheese and onion sandwich for 2
review: This was just wonderful!  I used chives instead of scallions (had them in the garden), and then toasted the sandwich on my Griddler.  The cheese was oozey and yummy; and the combination of flavors in the filling just made the sandwich rich and wonderful.  I used homemade whole wheat bread, and 2 slices of bacon for 1 sandwich. Thanks for satisfying my craving for grilled cheese in a new and yummy way!  Made for ZWT8

name: red lentil and chicken soup   indian style
review: We liked this soup, but thought it could use a touch more flavor.  I added a bit of cumin and paprika, and we really enjoyed it after that.  I also used my immersion blender to smooth it out before adding the chicken, which gave me the texture I was looking for.  I'm looking forward to enjoying the leftovers for lunch.  Made for ZWT8

name: indian raita  cucumber mix
review: A lovely raita- easy to make and used traditional ingredients. Reviewed for ZWT8 visit to India.

name: radish sandwiches
review: I had pink, purple and white radishes from the Farmer's Market and this recipe was a great way to use them! I made enough for 1 so I didn't bother blitzing such a small amount, and I liked the colours anyway! This was so good and I would make it again. Made for ZWT8. Thanks PanNan! :)

name: chocolate banana chocolate chip bundt cake
review: Very chocolatey, very rich.  Mine turned out crumbly, when I sliced it.

name: smoky blt vegetarian
review: I had some good quality blue cheese on hand and what a perfect way to use the last of it up! The rosemary mayo was awesome and the flavours of this sandwich blended so well together. Delicious! Thanks for posting! Made for ZWT #8 :)

name: homemade lemon curd
review: Haha, I had an open jar of storebought lemon curd in the fridge, and after tasting this in comparison to that one, I tossed the remainder of the storebought jar because it tasted artificial to me! This did take a long time to thicken up, but I think it's because I had turned the heat down too much. Once I increased the heat a bit, it thickened up pretty quickly. I used most of this in Recipe#450649 by gailanng (which it was lovely in, I might add). So fresh-tasting, and pretty simple to make, too. Thanks for posting! Made for The Honeys for ZWT8

name: nimbu ka chaval  saffron rice with lime
review: A nice and tasty exotic rice.  I made this with brown rice and just cooked it about 5-10 minutes longer in the water (until nearly tender).  Other than that I made it as written.  I think a tad less lime juice would be ideal.  And I mean just a tad.

name: stir fried won tons with szechuan sauce
review: Great wontons with a delicious spicy sauce. I am allergic to shrimp, so I did substitute that ingredient with ground chicken but otherwise followed the recipe.  I taste-tested the sauce with the 2 teaspoons of chili paste and decided to go ahead with your suggestion to use 1 tablespoon.  I was not positive on the folding procedure for the won tons and found a great photo tutorial at angelfire dot com (folding wontons),  Will definitely be making these again.

name: stilton stuffed baked pears
review: Delectable and delightful, this dessert is so tasty! I made one of these, using a Stilton cheese with apricots and the rest of the ingredients listed.  Made for ZWT8. Thanks Nancy's Pantry! :)

name: judy s salmon for one
review: We are back to blistering heat, no a/c, and I could not face turning on the oven, so I did this in a small skillet. My fillet was not quite to thick, so I did not use a lemon slice, but opted to add some lemon juice towards the end. The combination of sweet jam with the salmon was interesting - I'd never had anything like this and it was quite nice. Cooking in foil would have preserved more juices, but it was good even without that. Quick to make, an added bonus.

name: fruit kheer  indian fruit   yogurt pudding
review: I don't know what to make of this, the flavors are like WOW!  It is sweet and savory.  Fruity and spicy.  I like it.

name: easy baked macaroni and cheese
review: I really enjoy surprising DH, in a good way, of course. I had this in the oven when he returned from DS's soccer practice last night, and he professed his doubts about it, stating 'It's hard to beat that 'delux' blue box.' OH, THE HORROR! (he grew up on that...not me.) Anyway, MommyDiva's mac-n-cheese made a believer out of him! We really enjoyed this although I reduced the recipe by half, as there were only 2 of us eating it, at the time. I surely won't mind the leftovers! Thanks so much for sharing, Mommy Diva!

name: garam masala chicken
review: This was very to prepare and had a great flavor. A friend of mine from India gave me some garam masala to use for the meal and it was great. Made for ZWT8

name: manchester tart
review: Pretty sweet, but I enjoyed the combination of the raspberry, coconut and custard together. I used a storebought shortbread crust that I put an eggwash on and baked per package instructions. I used Bird's Custard Powder, but having never tried it before, I'm not sure I made it correctly. I followed the instructions given in this recipe, but they didn't match up with the instructions on the canister. After I removed the custard mixture from the heat, I had to toss it in the blender to get rid of the lumps that I couldn't get to dissolve. Then I returned it to the pan over the heat, and continuously whisked it, and then it finally became homogenous and more thick. I may have needed to cook it even longer, because the chilled custard on the pie was still somewhat loose, but I think that's my own fault for taking it off the heat too soon. No matter, it still tasted very good. At first I thought that the custard wasn't going to be sweet enough, but I'm glad I didn't add extra sugar, because the other elements of the pie were plenty sweet. Very good, thanks for posting! Made for The Honeys for ZWT8

name: restaurant style onion chutney
review: How awesome to find a simple chutney recipe that takes very little time to put together yet produces such wonderful flavours! We loved this recipe and served it with chicken kebabs. The taste was just terrific, no need to buy chutney when you can make it so easily. Thanks for posting! Made for ZWT #8 :)

name: lemon drop trifles
review: Lovely trifle! For some odd reason, I couldn't find lemon drops anywhere (I tried 4 different places), so I had to sub in some Mexican Selz candy that tastes like lemon-lime soda -- tasted fine, but not as pretty as real yellow lemon drops would've been (these candies are whitish-clear). To offset the white candies, I grated some fresh lemon zest over the trifle as well. I didn't want to fill the fridge with a bunch of breakable glasses of trifle, so I just made one in a little individual-size dish for me, and put the rest into a large glass dish. I used Charlotte J's Recipe#177724 for the curd, and limoncello for the liqueur. Sorry, the pics don't do this justice, but very yummy all the same! Thanks for posting! Made for The Honeys for ZWT8

name: rumbledethumps  scottish mashed potato and veggie casserole
review: What a terrific side dish! I had a little bit of left over savoy cabbage and also a little bit of kale so i used them both. Very tasty and easy to make and my whole family enjoyed this. Thanks for posting! Made for ZWT #8 :)

name: apple and pistachio salad
review: We loved this salad for a nice light summer lunch. The crunchy pistachios and tart apples are a wonderful combination and the dressing was to die for! Thanks for posting. Made for ZWT 8 :)

name: jhat phat sabzi  bell pepper paneer
review: By far the spiciest Indian recipe I tried during ZWT8, it was spicy but not harsh, and I went back for seconds.  (Note that I generally avoid extreme spiciness.)  My panir refused to stay in a neat cube, particularly after soaking in water, but that did not affect the taste, I don't think.  (I had used Recipe#425229 to prepare the panir, and next time I would add another step to form the panir in a neat rectangle in a glass container and weight it down before using it for this recipe.) Made for The Wild Bunch for ZWT8 for its visit to India.

name: lemon raspberry pancakes
review: These have a very nice flavor I really liked the lemon and raspberry together. I used frozen raspberries and they area around them was a little less cooked than I like so I would prefer fresh, breaking them up a bit helped improved this, though it didnt' help the color.  My DH enjoyed his with just butter , I liked a little whipped cream with the very last few fresh raspberries from our bushes. Made for ZWT 8 by another one of The Wild Bunch!

name: kheema with potatoes and peas
review: We loved this dish, it was not something I had tried before but even my picky daughter enjoyed it. I served it with home made Chapati and we had a feast for dinner. Very easy to make and a great blend of flavours. Thanks for posting! Made for ZWT 8 :)

name: apple and pistachio salad
review: Tasty crunchy salad, one of my faves! I really enjoyed the zing from the curry and cinnamon. I did reduce the recipe to 1 serving and enjoyed it for a light lunch. Thanks for sharing, Cookgirl!

name: onion bhaji  indian onion fritters
review: Loved these Bhajis. Easy to make and and a good blend of spices included. Served with raita for a delicious started to an Indian meal. Reviewed for Zwt8 tour of India. Photo also to be posted. These are gluten-free provided the spices used a gluten-free

name: curly locks  special  strawberries  sugar and cream for 1
review:
We had a lot of fun doing a berry tasting. We tried all the variations, I sliced or halved the berries and and then sprinkle a slice with an individual topping and tried it first naked and then with cream added. I was suprised how much I liked the pepper and smoked salt.
At the end we tried a slice with everything that was quite good. My favorite combos were salt, pepper, cinnamon, and cinnamon, mint. I don't think this was quite how this was supposed to be eaten but we enjoyed the experience! Made for ZWT 8 by one of The Wild Bunch
whole mint leaves - 4 star
fresh basil (just a few thin strands!) - 3 star
cracked black pepper (very light sprinkle!) - 5 star
ground cinnamon (very light sprinkle!) 4 star
ground cardamom (very light sprinkle!) 3 star - but my cardamom is old it could go up :)
smoked salt (very light sprinkle!) 5 star - I used 7 Wood Smoked salt I purchased at Sugarpill in Seattle - it smells like a campfire in a can!

name: indian roasted cauliflower
review: I wouldn't pass up any roasted veggie, and this one was certainly no exception! I really liked the turmeric in this (well, except for the really tenacious bright yellow stains that it left on my fingers and the pan, but whatever, lol). I actually added more turmeric than was specified in the recipe, and I was glad I did. I think I cut my florets too small, so they got pretty soft before I could get them to brown, but they were still very tasty. I definitely want to make this again, but cut them larger so they brown. I found myself just snacking on this out of the pan, it was so good. Thanks for posting! Made for The Honeys for ZWT8

name: cinnamon tea toddy
review: This is a lovely drink that would be great on a cold winter night, also would be a drink to serve at a winter holiday party. But it was in the 80's and we still enjoyed it while watching a pre-season football game - a sorta of warm up on all counts - lol!

name: indian rice pudding with fruit
review: Excellent dessert and so easy to make. I worried about the rice not cooking enough but it was done perfectly at the end of cooktime. I added some cinnamon as well and stirred the fruit right in the pudding when it was finished, saving a little bit to put on top. I used peaches as they are in season right now. I loved it! Thanks for posting. Made for ZWT 8 :)

name: reshmi kebab  chicken kebabs
review: This was awesome! What a tasty dish and not nearly as complicated as I at first thought it would be. A terrific blend of flavours, I served this with an Indian Rice for a terrific meal. Thanks for posting! Made for ZWT #8 :)

name: roasted apple marmalade
review: Easy to make and full of flavour! We loved this recipe, and as suggested, served along with pork, yum! Thanks for posting! Made for ZWT #8 :)

name: earl grey oatmeal  for zwt 8
review: Really good oatmeal. Halved recipe. Very tasty, thanks for posting! Made for The Honeys for ZWT8

name: caerphilly and tomato salad
review: Oh, this was so good! I used purple, orange and red cherry tomatoes from the Farmer's Market which added some nice colours. The Caerphilly is very crumbly so it was almost impossible for it not to fall apart when cutting it. This was the first time that I tried that cheese and it's very good! The dressing was really nice and would be good on any salad. Made for ZWT8. Thanks threeovens! :)

name: paneer   indian cottage cheese
review: As written, the recipe produces an unsalted soft cheese that reminds me of yogurt.  I did not weight my curds while they drained, but I allowed them to drain twice as long.  I used several layers of cheesecloth, which turned out to be a mistake as I had strata of cheese between the layers.  My second photo shows my panir after I cubed it (and shows how much remained trapped in the cheesecloth).  By the time I cooked it for Recipe #482753, it had the consistency of cottage cheese -- not appealing in looks, but it did the trick for the recipe.  Next time, I would put the finished cheese in a square glass container and weight it down to make a consistent rectangle of cheese easy to cube.  At any rate, I ended up with a little over 1 cup of panir from 1 liter of milk.  This is a recipe you need to play with to find the perfect consistency for your needs.  Made for The Wild Bunch for ZWT8 for its trip to India.

name: salsa pronto
review: This is so easy and just delicious. I added extra garlic and doubled the cilantro. I won't be buying salsa anymore after trying this recipe. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8- Zingo.

name: granny mac s mac and cheese
review: Mmmm...unbeatable..!!

name: basquet of eggs baked omelet
review: I trimmed back this recipe for one, and it was quite a generous serving. I liked that it used the potatoes as sort of a bottom crust, then just pop in the oven to finish off.

name: fresno french toast
review: I now have a new method to use to make French Toast.  Loved the crispy outside and the fully cooked insides!  My DS had me make some with the cinnamon and some without (not his favorite spice - gasp!) and both worked well.  Absolutely perfect recipe!  So glad I found it during ZWT8.

name: kipper s sandwich for 1 dictated by    tasty dish
review: Such a simple recipe that worked great on a crumpet! I used English cheddar and a nice strawberry jam. Made for ZWT8. Thanks Cookgirl! :)

name: chocolate bailey martini by bistro bond babes
review: Very nice dessert martini, the vodka did not overwhelm, and the chocolate syrup was an able supporting player.  The Bailey's was magnificent!  Next time I would use fudge sauce instead of the chocolate syrup.  Made for The Wild Bunch for the ZWT8 Beverage Dart Board.

name: mango wedges wrapped in serrano ham
review: We had these for our lunch, what a nice change from a sandwich. The paprika adds an extra punch to the mango. Made for ZWT8.

name: triple hitter muffins  toddler muffins
review: Tasty treat for my son and I both! Love that I am at least getting SOME vegetable in him as he has started with his picky phase.  I made them as mini muffins and will store leftovers in the freezer for a quick snack.

name: chelle s zucchini bread
review: This bread is just delicious! It's moist and has lots of flavour and the browned top has a nice crunch and isn't chewy. I really like that you use a good amount of vanilla and I skipped the cloves due to personal taste. Made for ZWT8. Thanks Mommy Diva! :)

name: mexican grilled chicken
review: This was soooo easy and very tasty. Even my extra picky friend enjoyed the flavors on this chicken. I tossed all of the ingredients into the mini processor, and let it rip. This is definitely a keeper!  MAde for ZWT8

name: a very proper english custard
review: Such a creamy and decadent dessert. My family really enjoyed this, especially with some berries we purchased yesterday. And it is much lighter than I thought it would be, but I guess that's what happens when you enjoy an English dessert.

name: strawberry salsa sundaes
review: Sure did love this salsa sundae! I cheated and ate mine for breakfast! Loved the bite from the jalapeno and the tang from the lime; very complimentary to the mixed fruit.So delicious! Next time, I may use vanilla ice cream instead of the yogurt. And I may even get DS to try this! Thanks for sharing, Starrynews! :)

name: heirloom tomato salad with buttermilk dressing and blue cheese
review: OMG, if one more review disappears on me! Grr! Anyway, this was positively delightful! I didn't use the sliced shallot in the salad, because the shallot in the dressing was plenty strong enough for me. Other than that, made as written. Thanks for posting! Made for The Honeys for ZWT8

name: creamy scrambled eggs with fines herbes
review: Terrific scrambled eggs! I used parsley, tarragon and chives. They had such a creamy texture and the flavor of the fresh herbs really stood out. Great breakfast. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8.

name: iced mint and cucumber gin
review: Delightful cooler, but some adjustments are needed.  i scaled this back to 1 serving, but ended up with 2 tall glasses of the cocktail, so I would adjust the number of servings for the recipe.  The recipe calls for a very large amount of mint leaves to be placed on top of the drink; usually 1 sprig would suffice.  Alternatively, the mint leaves would be placed at the bottom of the glass and muddled before pouring in the blended drink, and I think that would add more dimension to the taste.  One serving of this recipe calls for only 20ml or 0.67 fl. oz., so this is a very weak drink when split between 2 glasses; that didn't disappoint me at all, as I enjoyed the cooler's taste and prefer not to get snockered.   Made for The Wild Bunch for ZWT8 Family Picks.

name: easy seafood cocktail sauce
review: Very nice!  As written, it has a bit of zip, but isn't crazy-spicy.  I'll add more horseradish and Tabasco next time for a bit more heat.  Went great with the fresh Dungeness crab I had for lunch.  Made for ZWT8

name: mexican coffee  caf mexicano
review: Wow! The cinnamon gave it a sweet kick to the Mexican coffee, in every sip! Absolutely wonderful! Definetely a keeper of a recipe.

name: garlic button mushrooms with breadcrumbs
review: I cut the recipe down and it made a delicious snack for one. I enjoyed the tang of the lemon juice with the garlic, my only changes were to slice my mushrooms and to used dried bread crumbs. Thanks for a great recipe! Made for ZWT 8 Family Picks by one of The Wild Bunch

name: chapati  indian flat bread
review: Very good taste, even with such a simple ingredient list.  I admit, I let my ABM knead the dough.  Madhur Jaffrey says people keep the little balls kept damp in the refrigerator and use them as needed.  So I made one for a test, and will see how the refrigerated chapati (I covered each layer of balls with a damp paper towel) works tomorrow.  I'm not used to rolling out dough, so please excuse my practice chapati (it still tasted fine.)  Made for The Wild Bunch for ZWT8 Family Picks.

name: om nom nommers chocolate chip cookie
review: Yum yum, Om Nom Nommers! Really enjoyed this drink take on a chocolate chip cookie! My choices were the cookie dough vodka, the creme de cacao and vanilla bean ice cream. My garnish was a rather large cookie, which was good, despite it's size! ;-) I used a smallish punch cup to serve, as I knew even my pony shot glasses would be too small. Thanks for sharing, FLKeysJen, what may become a tasty nightcap for me. Very indulgent!

name: om nom nommers chocolate chip cookie
review: Delish!!! I made the non-alcoholic version, using white and chocolate milk, chocolate chip cookie dough ice cream and had it with some yummy mini cookies! What a treat! Made for ZWT8. Thanks FLKeysJen! :)

name: mexican black beans
review: Great recipe! I made it as written and thoroughly enjoyed these beans. We had enchiladas and rice to go with them. What a delight. Thanks for sharing. Made for ZWT 8.

name: soft ginger cookies  biscuits
review: These are yummy; they are delicately flavored and not too sweet. I tried to cut the chunks of ginger tiny so as not to overwhelm, but DS and DD still declared these were too "spicy" LOL. I used Smart Balance for the butter and all white whole wheat flour, and the texture was still great. I did reserve about 1 T of the sugar (for a half batch), and when I scooped the cookies I dipped the top of each one in it for a nice crunchy top. Thanks for posting! Made for ZWT 8: The Wild Bunch.

name: creamy cheese enchiladas
