review: Very easy to put together! I used egg roll wrappers instead of wonton wrappers.

name: walnut blackberry bread
review: This makes a lovely bread, perfect for sharing. I had to bake mine almost 20 minutes longer, so next time I think I would reduce the temp to 325, as I used a glass dish. The crust was pretty dark, but not necessarily hard and it tasted great! Made to share on a shopping trip with friends, I will certainly make this again to share with others. Thank you for sharing, too, Deb!

name: rosemary and orange chicken breasts
review: Boy, this recipe needs more reviews! It's amazingly flavorful  and quick and easy too. I'll be making this one again

name: aussie hamburger
review: Very good burger.  Texture reminded me more of meatloaf than a hamburger, but the flavors were really good.  I didn't have any beetroot, but other than that I made the recipe as written.  Made for December 2012 Aus/NZ Swap.

name: caramel coffee cream parfaits
review: Rich and decadent - the combination of caramel sauce and coffee ice cream was delicious.

name: steak wine marinade
review: I had an opened bottle of red wine that I needed to use up.  I made this marinade for some skirt steak DH had in the freezer.  I let them marinate 48 hours and DH cooked them on the grill.  He gave it four stars.

name: 1 minute chili cheese burritos
review: I love refried bean burritos and these were not only quick to make, but yummy.  I used mild picante sauce and fat-free flour tortillas.

name: slow cooker weeknight chili cook s country
review: Cooks Illustrated sends me a weekly newsletter and this was where I found this recipe.  This went over really well with the family.  The bacon makes a really nice touch!  I would do this one again!  Thanks for posting....as I would surely have done so!!!

name: easy broccoli   pork chop dinner
review: Excellent pork chop dish.  I don't have minute rice, so I cooked long grain rice in my rice cooker with the chicken broth.  I sauteed the onion and steamed the broccoli and added it to the rice.  To make it more diabetic friendly, I used sugar-free honey substitute in place of the maple sugar.  I also added a little crushed red pepper flake.  Tender, juicy, flavorful pork chops on top of a bed of delicious rice.  I will be making this often.  Made for December 2012 Aus/NZ Swap.

name: chinese noodles and vegetables
review: Oh my goodness this was good. I decided to use a wide variety of veggies that I had on hand ncluding, mushroom, gr and red peppers, broccoli, sugar snap peas, and regular coking onions. I also added in some sesame oil, fresh ginger and a little bit of chicken soup base. We loved this recipe. While I did add to the recipe ingredients, I folowed the basic recipe. Thank you so much for posting this recipe.

name: a breakfast yogurt parfait  granola
review: Really good and easy parfait.  I used Yoplait Light vanilla yogurt, Special K Cinnamon & Pecan cereal instead of granola (because I didn't have any), and a few slices of banana on top.

name: bermudian rum cake
review: The flavor of this cake is awesome.  I love the slight orange flavor in the cake.   The crumb of the cake is on the spongy side though.  Not sure if it is just me.  Still great nevertheless. Oh, and glaze is to die for.  Thank you for sharing your recipe.

name: pineapple wine cooler
review:
We really enjoyed this refreshing wine cooler. The soda added just the right amount of carbonation. I used regular Sprite ( I just can't do the diet stuff) and a nice Pinot Grigio white wine. This goes together so quickly with ingredients that I always have on hand. Thank you for sharing this delicious drink!
**Made for 2012 Football Pool**

name: frango  moda do alentejana  chicken with potatoes and ga
review:
This was a wonderful chiciken recipe.
I'm glad I have a lot of rosemary in the garden and for this reason I had to try this one.
It's a very easy but tasty recipe that I can recommend to all families!

name: easy cheesy chicken   pasta veggie skillet
review: I made this recipe on 12/5/12 for the " Simple And Relaxed December Dinner Fare " event in the Food Photo Forum. Except for leaving out the mushrooms,( I don't care for them )the recipe was made exactly as written. This recipe doesn't take long to make at all, and if you use leftover chicken the time to make would be even faster.My SO and I both enjoyed the taste,but felt like it needed a bit of " something " . If this is made again, a bit of garlic powder maybe added. " Thanks for posting and, " Keep Smiling :) "

name: spinach twice baked potatoes
review:
I had about 6 ounces of frozen Spinach and was looking for a way to use it, and came across this recipe. Except for using 3 potatoes,the recipe was made as written. Now I don't like spinach,but when it's mixed in with something as good as these potatoes I could eat it with no complaints. :)
Thank you for posting a very good recipe, and " Keep Smiling :) "

name: pork and cider stew  a crock pot recipe
review: Just wanted something different in the crockpot !  Did take more than 15 min to prepare, but flavors were all on the "go-together" list.  1 cup of liquid was not nearly enough -- added at least 1 more cup after 5 hours.  Turned out a tad sweeter than our usual preference, but has potential for tweaking.  Thanks for posting, Taste Tester.

name: oatmeal cranberry cookie mix
review: Such a pretty gift jar! I haven't prepared the cookies yet, I needed a shower gift and took these. Everyone thought they were so cute,and begged for the recipe. Will report back when I have a chance to make it again and acutally bake them. I'm putting this jewel in my holiday idea cookbook. Made for newest tag. Addition Dec. 8, 2012... these cookies are so very good, I added a handful of white chocolate chips ..yummmmmmmm.

name: fondant potatoes with garlic  fondant de pommes de terre
review: These potatoes are nice enough to serve for company. They are nice looking as well as great tasting. I sprinkled dried  rosemary as thats all I had. Loved the garlic flavor!! Thanks for sharing. Made for Football Pool 2012.

name: easy peanut butter blossoms
review: Great recipe for a quick, easy to make cookie. I followed the recipe as written and they turned out perfect. A good recipe for the kids to do for a Christmas tray or to set out for Santa. Thanks for sharing. Made for Football Pool 2012.

name: sweet potatoes with pecan praline streusel
review:
i made this for thanksgiving and WOWWWWW. delish. Hubby is a non believer in sweet tateres but he was delighted. Will certainly add this to our must have for holidays.
YUmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmyyyyy. Sorry no pictures, the dish was comsumed the minute it came out of the oven.

name: rita s deviled eggs
review: At first I thought these were a bit too potent. However, they did mellow overnight, and I enjoyed them more the next day. Some guidance about the amount of salt would have been helpful. I will probably not make these again (commercial horseradish sauce is full of awful ingredients, and I don't use it enough to bother making my own). Thank you for the recipe, though.

name: brown rice with feta cheese
review: I had printed the recipe off a while ago so I didn't know who the author was!!  Silly me....I was not surprised when I realized it was from Kittencal.  The year is not out yet, but this would definately be in my top 10 recipes of the year!!!  Take the time....the mushrooms make the dish!!!  I probably used 6 large mushrooms (so definitely over 1 cup)  and sauteed them in 1 T butter and a good splash of white wine.  I also added a good shake of hot sauce!  Devine!  It turned out creamy....very much like a risotto!  Take a bow, Kitten....great posting!!!

name: best ever pumpkin pie
review: 10 Stars!  very creamy, delicious and easy .  I didn't use the extra 2 Tablespoons of sugar. Thank you for sharing the recipe.

name: pan release  professional pan coating  better than pam spray
review: I used this on 9 inch baking pans for a cake I made.  The cake released ok but there were a few spots on the bottom of the pan where the cake did not release.

name: kolokythsoupa  greek pumpkin soup
review:
This was really excellent!
My daughter told me that the house was smelling wornderful!
The recipe is perfect as roasting spices and vegetables this gives a special and rich taste to the soup. Also the yogurt addition worked well: important is not bringing it to boil!
Thanks a lot Mia it was a pleasure using my pumpkins from the garden for your soup!

name: austrian raspberry shortbread
review: I love this recipe.  It bakes up well in a glass 9 x 13 inch pan or as others have said, cut the recipe in half and bake in an 8 inch or 9 inch pan. You can also add 1 teaspoon vanilla extract or 1 teaspoon lemon zest to the shortbread dough.

name: meat salad  berlin
review: OMG this is so delicious and so authentic. My parents were from Germany and my mother always made something like this, especially with any frankfurters and wurst she had in the refrigerator. I love this with fresh rye bread. Thank you for posting.

name: instant gingerbread coffee
review:
I thought this was very tasty, however, I didn't think it tasted like gingerbread. Although the pumpkin pie spice has ginger in it, I felt the recipe needed more ginger to live up to its name.
Made for the Australian New Zealand Make My Recipe Reunion tag.

name: tender beef smothered in stilton cheese sauce
review: Yummy!  The Stilton cheese sauce really brings this steak up a notch.  The steaks were tender and juicy and the sauce was delicious with just enough tanginess from the Stilton cheese.  Easy to make and elegant enough for company.  Made for December 2012 Aus/NZ Swap.

name: deli cracker dip
review: I spread this on a crusty baguette which I lightly toasted and then broiled it to melt the cheese. My teenage daughter declared it "one of the best things she has eaten".  I made it as indicated but I think I'd like it with a bit of onion or garlic added so I'll try that next time.  Thanks Debber!

name: raisin spice cookies  ww
review: Since it's the holidays, I went ahead and did the glaze and a little bit of sprinkles! These cookies are like soft ginger cookies, very good. I had an open can of pumpkin puree and used that instead of applesauce. Very good!

name: hellmann s parmesan crusted chicken  low fat version
review: I gave this recipe 5 stars! This chicken is so delish! Just for my FYI: I used the shredded Parmesan Cheese. I made very minor changes to the recipe. I added some garlic & onion powder, plus some salt and pepper to the mayo mix. Baked the breasts about 5-10 minutes longer as I was preparing other things. We so will have these again and I plan to making these for the people I care for! Thanks for posting one of the best recipes!

name: weekend cookers famous baked beans
review:
We loved these sweet, smokey baked beans. When I originally looked at the ingredient list, I thought that 2 TBSP. of liquid smoke seemed like an awful lot. I went ahead and made the recipe as written, and am I ever glad that I did. The smoke flavor was perfect and really added a lot of flavor to this recipe. I loved the ease of preparation, with ingredients that I always have on hand. Thank you for sharing this wonderful recipe...it is definitely a keeper!!
**Made for 2012 Football Pool**

name: fresh greek pasta salad
review: Aussie Recipe Tag: I loved this recipe! Such flavor and fresh ingredients! I couldn't get enough of it - I think it will be a new addition to our Christmas dinner this year as well

name: simply german potato salad
review: I love German potato salad, but I have to admit that I don't make it often...that will change since I found this recipe.  This was so easy to make and satisfied my craving for a delicious German potato salad.  I couldn't find Simply Potatoes with Onion so I used a bag of southern-style cubed potato hash browns that contained red and green peppers and onion which made making this dish even easier.  :)  Made for Make My Recipe Reunion Tag Game.

name: make your own sweetened condensed milk   homemade  substitute
review: I admit that I did not think this recipe would be similar in consistency to condensed milk, but it certainly is.  I added a tsp of vanilla to give it more flavour  but as written it is still good. Thanks for the great "substitution" recipe.

name: rosy cinnamon apples for 2
review: Super easy recipe and the syrup on the apples was very good.

name: perfect fried pork chops
review: On 12/9/12 I was looking for something different to do with pork chops.So, I did a search and came across this recipe and decided to try it. Since it was just my SO and myself the recipe was reduce for just two chops. Other than that,the recipe was made just as it was written. I really enjoyed it and my SO gave it a " Good Solid 4 " and coming from him that's a big compliment. I served this with Recipe #78028 and steamed broccoli which made this a very good meal. Thanks for posting a recipe that will be made again. " Keep Smiling :) "

name: most excellent mexican rice
review: This certainly is most excellent! I like the addition of cumin. I did not have beef broth and used chicken broth instead, I am sure it will only be better with beef broth and will try that next time I make it.

name: butera s baked potato soup
review: This was really a great soup! Baking the potatoes made a big difference in the flavour, much deeper. Very simple to put together, we had this for a very filling meal along with some crusty bread. Thanks for posting :) Made for Aussie Reunion Tag!

name: thai clear soup with sweet and sour chile
review: This soup is awesome, super and very authentic! We truly enjoyed it. Only comment I will make is that the soup is very light and would either be great as a 1st course or together with another dish. Or you could add glass noodles for more substance. I will for sure be making this again, thanks for sharing!

name: refried beans without the refry
review: This has got to be the easiest and healthiest way to make 'refried' beans without any loss of flavour. You just plop everything in your slow cooker and walk away. Mine were done after 6 hours on high, and they may have been done even sooner, I only checked them at the 6 hour mark. Just super!

name: stuffed celery sticks
review: Just learning to like blue cheese and enjoyed this quick, easy, healthy, tasty snack!

name: classic fresh prawn  shrimp  rolls
review: Delicious! It had a nice tang from the sweet chili that worked really well with the prawns.

name: green split pea and bacon soup
review: I had to omit the bacon, because of some health issues, but this soup was just fine without it. I used chicken broth and added a bay leaf, some peppercorns and some thyme to the soup as it was cooking as well - I find that those enhance any vegetable soup. The lemon added a lovely bright note, quite nice.

name: mom s cocoa powder brownies
review: I chose this recipe specifically because it said they were NOT cake-like brownies.  Unfortunately, the second I took them out of the oven and dropped the sides of the Perfect Brownie Pan, I could see from the texture that there was too much egg in this recipe to produce chewy brownies.  I'm afraid I couldn't eat the whole brownie. My kindergartener and her friend thought they were fine, but I still ended up throwing out at least half the batch.  I made a double recipe to fit the pan I was using, but that's been done many times without altering the results.  I'm sorry I just can't agree on the texture of these; I'm a brownie snob according to my DH.  :)

name: spicy bean turnovers  with variations
review: I made the spicy bean filling and we thought it was really good.  Using a pre-made pie crust makes these go together very quickly. I made the salsa/sour cream mixture for dipping.  I did have leftover bean filling and I spread it on a plate, topped it with cheese and microwaved until the cheese was melted.  Served with tortilla chips and it was inhaled. I will be trying the bean filling in burritos too.

name: german spritz with variations
review: This recipe makes good cookies BUT the cookies press is very important. If you have a badly designed one, like I do, you will probably feel quite frustrated before the batch is complete. Even if you only make a half batch, like me. The dough is easy to mix up, though pretty sticky. A wide mouth cookie press would be easy to load and save on frustration. (Mine is less than 2 inches diameter inside.) Thank you for sharing this recipe with us. I will use it again after I buy a new cookie press.

name: cream of chicken soup   when you don t have canned   substitute
review: I used 1/2 cup So Delicious coconut milk (unsweetened) and less dried onion flakes.  I recommend melting the butter, adding the flour, cooking for a minute.  Then slowly adding the milk and broth with the spices and onions.  I think that's the traditional way of doing it.  Made this for a Chicken Swiss recipe in the crockpot.  Thanks!

name: beans in coconut sauce  maharagwe ya nasi
review: Delicious! I cheated and used canned dark red kidney beans and canned crushed tomatoes. I love the sweetness of the coconut and the savory from the tomatoes, garlic and beans. My daughter's BF is from South Africa and he is always looking for recipes from that region. I am pretty sure he will love these too. Made for Photo tag.

name: chex party mix just like nanny used to make
review: I made this on 12/11/12,but due to lack of items on hand, the recipe was slightly altered. They are as follows: 3 cups each of Corn and Rice Chex,1 1/2 cups goldfish crackers,1 cup of slightly crushed waffle shaped pretzels,and a 14 ounce can mixed nuts. For the seasonings: 1 1/2 Tblsp. Worcetershire sauce, 6 Tblsps. stick margarine 1 1/2 tsp. smoky flavored seasoning salt, 3/4 tsp. garlic powder,1/2 tsp. each of the onion and chili powder. And I left out the bite-size garlic chips. And the dry ingredients were mixed in a large bowl, And after melting the margarine, all the seasoning were mixed in well, then poured over the cereal. But instead of using the microwave, everything was poured into a 9 in. x 13 in. which had been sprayed with a cooking spray. Then it was baked at 325 degrees for 45 minutes and stirred every 15 minutes. Even though this isn't the Original 1956 version of the Party Mix, it was still very good. Thank you for posting a recipe that will be made again, and " Keep Smiling :) "

name: swiss chicken casserole  crock pot
review: Making this now for the 2nd time.  Family loved it first time, with the bread crumbs.  Now, I am trying cooked rice.  I can never fit 6 chicken breasts in my 5 qt crockpot.  I also use homemade cream of chicken soup and I put the bread crumbs/rice on the bottom.

name: veronica s easy spanish rice
review: Just a note, I made this for dinner but all we had was brown rice so that is what I used.  I didn't care for it at all.  So if you are wanting a five star result don't stray from the recipe.  I didn't think it would make that much of a difference, but next time I will not stray!!

name: spiced matzalan meatballs
review: Yum! Beautifully spiced and was perfect served with greek yoghurt and lettuce wrapped in a tortilla.

name: bourbon  rum  balls  no bake cookies
review: I ended up making these twice because of a stupid mistake. Probably nobody but me will do this, but I might as well confess. First of all, vanilla wafers are not sold in Japan, where I live. I decided to substitute a different kind of crisp cookie. The first time, I bought cookies at a neighborhood bakery. Several people have given the weight of the cookies, so I thought it would work. The cookies were in little bags with a small pouch of dessicant. Well, long story short, I luckily tasted the mixture left in the bowl after making balls. What was that hard stuff? Yes, it was beads of silica gel. Oops. So anyway, I started again today. I do think I learned something from the first experience (besides not using ingredients not called for, especially if they are inedible.) So I toasted the pecans and chopped them separately because I wanted some crunch. I broke up the cookies in the food processor, added the cocoa and powdered sugar and transferred it all to a bowl. I then cautiously added the liquids and stirred in the nuts. This time I used packaged Langue de Chat cookies, which didn't have dessicant. Although I was worried about the mixture getting sticky, it was perfect with the amounts given. I used white rum. I have tasted these, and they seem quite good, but do need some time for the flavor to develop. Thank you for sharing this recipe with us.

name: easy 7 up no funnel cake
review: This recipe didn't work out for me either.  I only made one at a time and my electric fry pan has a light that goes out when the oil reaches the set temp.  The first one I poured as directed and it was soggy and greasy in the middle.  The second one I poured more like a funnel cake and turned up the temp slightly.  That was too crispy.  We picked at them but I gave up at that point and didn't make anymore.  My 7 up may have been a little flat.  Could that be the cause of my poor results?

name: pot roast with dill pickles
review: When I saw this recipe it reminded me of Polish cooking so I just had to try it. Everyone loved it. I doubled the amount of stock just to make sure the pan doesn't burn and used Greek yogurt instead of sour cream 'cause it's what I had on hand. I might let it cook an extra hour next time and see how tender it can get. Thank you very much.

name: orange coconut date squares
review: These are so very easy to make.  Perfect for this busy time of year.  I baked them in a glass pan, so lowered the temperature to 325*.  It took an additional 15 minutes to set completely, but that's not a problem.  I did find them a tad on the sweet side, so next time I'll cut them into smaller squares.  Thanks Elly for the wonderful recipe.

name: irish omelette
review: I believe that I used too much of the mashed potatoes as mine was a bit dry. I also sprinkled on some marble cheddar cheese because the omelette kind of fell apart when I flipped it. So, besides my mistakes with this recipe, it did have a nice flavour and I would attempt it again! Made for Went To The Market tag game. Thanks Baby Kato!

name: perfect chocolate brownies
review: Excellent brownies! I've been making these since 2009, but I didn't realize that I hadn't reviewed them.  This is one of my go-to recipes!  I use coconut oil/butter mix instead of shortening to make it healthier, too.

name: pork chops with seasoned tomatoes
review: This was a very good and easy to prepare dish, just right for December when you don't have the time to cook. Thought it could use a little more seasoning, otherwise quite good.

name: garlic sun dried tomato pasta
review: We really loved this pasta. Everyone kept going for more, so that was great. I reduced the amount of oil to 1/4 of a cup and used whole wheat medium shell pasta to make it a bit more figure friendly. Thank you.

name: cuban mojo
review:
We are a garlic loving family. So even though this recipe has plenty, I added a little extra ;0) I used it to marinade chicken, which we grilled. It was really enjoyed by all. I am so glad because I was a little worried it would not. When I got to step 4 it says: :Stir in the sour orange juice, water, oregano, cumin, salt and pepper." There wasn't any mention of water in the ingredients so I didn't know if I should leave it out or add it. Or how much water to use if I did add it. So I took a chance and left it out all together. I was worried that it might end up too strong because of this, but it turned out fine. Served with grilled veggies.

Read more at: http://www.food.com/recipe/cuban-mojo-413552?oc=linkback

name: florentine breakfast wraps
review: Yum, a delicious, healthy and filling way to start the day! Great combination of flavors and I especially enjoyed the addition of Greek yoghurt and jalapeno.

name: southwest vegetable saute
review: While DH and I really enjoyed these veggies, DD did not.  I guess we will save this recipe for those nights we are home by ourselves.  I used mexican blend cheese and some asiago on top because that is what I had on hand.  Served with grilled chicken.

name: gorgonzola butter
review: I made this as written except for the Tabasco. I can't believe how good it was on a slice of rosemary & olive oil sourdough bread that I warmed in the oven. I had it with a bowl of homemade chili. Thanks for sharing. Made for Football Pool 2012.

name: hungarian goulash
review: This is a good dish, but make sure that you cook the beef long enough so the meat is tender!   I did add mushrooms and used about 1/4 cup of wine to de-glaze my pot.  I found there was a lot of liquid so I had to add about 1/2 cup of flour mixture to thicken it up.  Next time, I might try this in my crock pot!

name: main dish chickpeas with harissa
review: This dish was extremely easy to prepare, and I like all the ingredients. It seemed to me, however, to be lacking something, perhaps to give it more substance. It was quite interesting to try. Thank you for sharing this recipe.

name: sauerkraut tomato soup
review: Good comfort food. Tagged in everyday forum and so glad I did. Nice combination of flavors, we will cut back on the tomatoes next time. Just person taste. Thanks for sharing.

name: mashed sweet potatoes with coconut milk
review: These potatoes were amazing! I used the microwave to precook, which was very convenient. (I accidentally overcooked the potatoes, which was my own fault because I didn't check them carefully.) The only thing I would change next time would be to grate the ginger rather than mincing, just so it would mix in better. I used full-fat coconut milk. This was so rich and luscious that it tasted like there was butter in it. I will definitely make this often! The only argument I have is that this *must* be 2 servings. No way I could have served this to 4 people!

name: colossal cookies
review: I made these for my cookie exchange this year. I used white chocolate chips, mini hersheys kisses and some heath pieces. They turned out really good with a nice chewy texture.

name: avocado on toast with bacon and maple syrup
review:
My only complaint is that you haven't been screaming about this recipe from the rooftops, and bringing my attention to it way before now Pat!!
I loved it....and I need more of it!!
Made for Aus/NZ Recipe Swap#71

name: kumara  sweet potato  and ginger mash
review:
Yum!! These sweet potatoes are absolutely delicious. I normally add brown sugar,butter, cinnamon and a pinch of ginger powder to sweet potatoes, but the fresh ginger was a wonderful surprise. It compliments the sweet potato so well and adds a little zing along the way. I am a ginger lover and found that I couldn't stop eating this stuff. Delicious!! Thank you for sharing this fabulous, easy recipe...it is definitely a keeper!!
**Made for Football Pool 2012**

name: roasted tomato soup
review: Wow! This soup is amazing. It was so easy to make and the taste and texture is perfect. It tastes like there is cream in it but is much healthier without. I didn't have any garlic or fresh herbs so just sprinked some dry spices on the tomatoes and onion before roasting. I will make often!

name: chili seasoned potato wedges
review:
This is so good, that I've actually made it twice....the second time I cooked them on a baking tray on the trusty WeberQ with the hood down - fabulous!
Made for PRMR.

name: russell s quick chicken skewers
review:
What a great quick fix dinner, that is just delicious!
This worked out brilliantly after a day at work, and allowed me to relax in the last rays of the sun clutching a glass of wine instead of slaving over a hot stove....cheers Peter!
Made for Aus/NZ Recipe Swap#71

name: stuffing for the adventurous  cuban style
review: Me encanto...one of my favorite recipes of 2012! I used a little more than one cup of stock. So delicious and colorful, with no butter!

name: most amazing portabello  egg and veggie baked breakfast
review: One of my favorite new recipes of 2012! I used yellow squash, red onion and green chiles...so delicious. The leftovers heated in the toaster oven for breakfast the next day (with a new fried egg) were just as good or even better!

name: puppy chow or monkey munch
review: I gave this recipe 5 stars! OMG! These taste just like the store brand Chex Mix Muddy Buddy's! Just delicious! My family loved these! I made these for guys I take care of as a special treat! I'm hoping they enjoy them! Thanks for posting! Christine

name: wildcat hot pizza dip
review: Loved this dip and I had to make another batch because it was gone so quickly.  I sliced up baguettes and we piled the dip onto the bread slices instead of dipping them.  Will definitely be making this often!

name: teresa s peanut butter chews
review: I gave this 4 stars. My family really liked these. These taste like peanut butter fudge! I made these as gifts to give to some guys I help take care of! Hope they enjoy them as much as my family did! Thanks for posting Christine

name: chicken breasts with lemon and fresh rosemary  crock pot
review: It's magic how the delicious lemon sauce appears...poof...out of nowhere! Think this would be good without the paprika - will try with just the lemon and rosemary in the future. Nice easy recipe!

name: sprouts  bacon and figs
review: This turned out pretty well (I slightly over-caramelized it, which was totally my fault). I had figs that were chopped, and still used 1 c., which turned out to be too much. I didn't use the olive oil because my bacon was a bit fatty. The presentation was good for people who are afraid of Brussels sprouts. Doesn't look like them at all, and they tasted good.

name: vegetable burger soup
review: On 12/17/12 I needed something quick and easy for mine and my SO's dinner, and decided to try this recipe. Due to what was on hand a few changes had to be made to the recipe, 1 14.5 ounce can of Italian Style diced tomatoes were used instead of the mushroom and garlic tomatoes. Only used an 8 ounce can of tomato sauce, 2 1/2 cups of water,1 packet of onion soup mix. I did  use the full amount of ground beef,which while browning about 3/4 th. cup of finely diced celery was added. The meat while browning was also seasoned with a bit of smoky flavored seasoned salt and ground black pepper. Also used about a cup of leftover mixed vegetables. After the first 15 minutes, I let it simmer for at least another 20 minutes on a low boil. And I'm really glad that I did, it just seemed to make the flavors of the soup to be more intense : ) . My SO and I both give this recipe a " Good Solid 4 ****'s ". Thanks for posting a recipe that I'll make again. " Keep Smiling :) "

name: fiesta burgers
review: These were ok, but I don't think I would make them again. They completely fell apart when I cooked them under the broiler. The grill would have been completely out of the question. They were also a bit bland. Of course, I didn't use the optional horseradish. I also didn't add the salt or pepper. (How do you add seasonings "to taste" when they are in raw meat?)

name: seasoned sirloin steak bbq sandwiches
review:
What a fantastically quick and flavoursome sandwich....this really hit the spot as an after work quick fix that delivered comfort and taste instantly.
No Havarti here, but used Colby which we thought worked well.
Another winner Doug-thank you!
Made for PRMR.

name: perfect easy microwave rice
review: This rice was good, but it could stand for some improvements!  My rice was sticky, so I would wash it first to get some of the starch off.  2) the rice was a tad undercooked, so I would cook the rice for another 3 minutes, then rest for 2.   3) the cooking time was actually more with this method than stove top cooking, so you are not saving any real time.  I used beef broth and a couple dashes of hot pepper sauce which gave it a nice flavour.  This was fun to try, but I don't know if I would come back to this one again

name: bavarian mint coffee creamer
review: I did a test run of the recipe as written as I plan to include it in my Xmas goody baskets.  I felt that the cocoa taste was too much and the mint wasn't quite enough. So I played with it on the second batch. I ended up with 1 C non-dairy creamer, 1 C confectioner's sugar and 1 tsp peppermint but left the cocoa the same.  For me, that was better. All in all a really nice recipe for gift giving. It smells wonderful too.

name: chicken   wild rice salad
review:
I had one similar at Sweet Tomatoes and loved it. I made the recipe without the nuts and added
some thawed frozen peas and some finely chopped red onion. It was wonderful. My husband loved it. It is great with leftover chicken. Thanks, Carole in Orlando

name: almond and sugar powder
review: Aussie Swap#71: This sugar mix is awesome - I used it on my homemade almond bread (I usually use sliced almonds and raw sugar) but this was a nice sweet treat - made a yummy crust to it! Thank you for posting it!

name: perfect sugar cookie glaze
review: I really like how this glaze hardens so you can stack the cookies without messing them up! I used it on Recipe #56407. I tried tinting it blue but because my vanilla was brown it make it kind of a weird color. The next batch I used clear almond extract and let if white. We thought it showed off the sprinkles better anyway. I'll definitely use this recipe again!

name: tropical punch slush
review: Aussie Tag Game: Made this for our office party and it was a HUGE HIT! Thanks Tristine - I cannot wait to make this for Christmas Day!

name: tortellini with brown butter and sage sauce
review: A gourmet tasting recipe with minimum effort. I used chicken tortellini for a one pot meal that not only was very satisfying but also let me use up all of the sage I purchased for holiday cooking. Thank you.

name: pork schnitzel with creamed leeks
review: Recipe#71: OMG - this was heavenly!! I love schnitzel and creamed veggies and these leeks were outstanding! So easy to make!!

name: authentic meat loaf
review:
OK, I TOO was concerned re how MOIST the meat mixture was too!
But my doubts were alleviated once it was cooked too!
Used 8 ounces beef mince, 8 ounces (combination of chorizo mince)100 grams to 400 grams pork mince and that gave it the taste it did need!
This makes for a GREAT feed!
Without the AUS/NZ recipe swap #72,
I might not ever come across THE MOISTEST meatloaf I EVER have expereinced worldwide too!
PS I reckon this will be even better tomorrow when it has a chance to settle too...Let it sit for 15 minutes when it came out of the oven, used a silicone rectangular tray, no oil, turned it over, then turned it over again, so the tomato salsa topping was on top
Hope my little hints and tips help other people to try this GREAT recipe WHOO HOO!

name: eggplant  aubergine  parmesan  easy
review: Finally! After countless tries of cooking eggplant I finally came out on top. I totally agree with another reviewer that breading is overrated. I used fresh mozzarella and pecorino romano and it was to die for! Cheesy tomatoey goodness. Thank you for helping me overcome one of my top culinary challenges.

name: pork chop rice casserole
review: Before making this on 12/19/12, I was reading part of the review from Lainey6605 about adding some seasonings. After mixing together Golden Mushroom Soup (just a personal preference) to the rice and hot water, about 1 teaspoon each of garlic powder and oregano were added then poured into a greased baking dish. Also while the chops were browning, a bit of Smoke Flavored Seasoned Salt was added to each chop. Then all was covered and baked at 375 for about 35 minutes. I really enjoyed the flavor from this, and my SO gave this a " Good Solid 4****'s " and coming from him that a very big compliment. Thanks for posting a recipe that will be made again, and " Keep Smiling :) "

name: ranch dressing and dip mix
review: Aussie Recipe Swap#71: LOVE LOVE LOVE this mix! It was so easy to assemble, had all the ingredients on hand and it makes a perfect Christmas gift! Thank you!

name: algerian adess   traditional lentil soup   stew   family recipe
review: This is a great winter dish for me, and works wel in a family that loves lentils. I found this to be more of a stew than a soup, but no one really minded that.

name: skillet  mediterranean chicken
review:
I have been VERY naughty today!
LOVE the ease and simplicity of the recipe ok!
I always like to use up what have on hand on the day!
What I did...used Canned 2 400 g diced tomatoes, added 2 teaspoons mixed herbs, 1/2 cup red pepper marinated slices drained and washed too, had 2 large mushrooms which I sauteed in 1 cup white wine when adding the rest of the ingredients on the day!
My intentions were honorable, did not mean to do!
I would make this recipe again and maybe add marinated artichokes drained and washed and top with feta for that bit of OOMPAH too! WHOO HOO!

name: southwestern quinoa vegetable casserole
review: Delicious and so easy - the only thing that took time was chopping the jalapenos which you can skip by using "hot" RO-TEL.

name: corn and cherry tomato salad
review: This is a fresh and easy salad to make. I used fresh tarragon, which worked very well, as I love fresh tarragon.

name: chocolate chip biscuits aussie style
review: *Made for Australia/NZ Swap #70*  The ONLY cookie I made for the holidays !  Not at all like my usual choc-chips, but a new Go-To --- very tasty and the DGKs really enjoyed them !  Thanks for posting, mummamills -- and my apologies for such a late review.

name: clay pot sesame chicken
review:
OUTSTANDING as can be!
Is the very first time have done Clay Pot Cooking!!!! HOW E-X-C-I-T-I-N-G for ME!!
I was a little worried would get dried out,
But when it was finished, WHOO HOO I did shout!
OK, I diced the chicken JUST BECAUSE was what I wanted to do!
This recipe now inspires me to do a LOT more Clay Pot Cooking, so THANK YOU! WHOO HOO!

name: broccoli cheese quinoa soup
review: Most of my family members loved this recipe. We added extra cheese, and didn't add salt as suggested. Next time we won't puree all the broccoli, so some of it says chuncky.

name: jewish pound cake
review:
Made this again for long-distance friends stopping by. Pretty fool-proof - and VERY quick and easy !

Saw the review earlier, and made the cake according to directions -- used KA BLACK cocoa -- gave a lovely chocolaty color. Definitely NOT sweet, but a more airy, light texture than the usual pound cake. Got to use my new scraper-beater, which worked so well ! This was so easy to put together and baked perfectly in 54 minutes ! Will be a repeater for sure. Thanks for posting !!

name: baked tortellini
review: The concept of this recipe sounded really good to me, however for me personally, I have decided I don't like fontina cheese. DH, DD and GS however loved the dish so much that I am giving the recipe 5 stars. Thanks for posting this as I know I will be making it again. And I plan on trying it with a combo of Gruyere and aged extra sharp cheddar. Made for Veg 'n Swap tag.

name: refreshing sweet potato salad
review: A nice variation of potato salad. I peeled, diced and simmered the sweet potato until it was done, as did not want to use the oven just for this. I had no yogurt, so in the morning I took my kefir grains and dropped them into some heavy cream. By the time I got home, I had a lovely mascarpone-thick cream with a slight tang. I did use rather more red onion, as there were no hot peppers of any kind, and did add some red pepper flakes. The fresh pepper would have been a nice addition. This was served with hamburgers, and I have to say, I think I preferred it warm - it was not as appealing to me when I had it chilled this morning. That or at room temperature. Just a personal preference.

name: microwave chocolate mug brownie
review: This was really easy and tasty quick treat!  I liked it a bit better than the cake in a mug recipes. Thanks for posting!

name: peppermint candy cane bark
review: 5 stars for ease, 4 stars for taste.  Such a simple treat to make.  Perfect way to use up the extra candy canes and make a tasty addition to the Christmas goodies we give to friends.  Merry Christmas!

name: honey mustard chicken salad
review:
This recipe has everything for summer.
Fresh, light and so tasty.
The dressing goes so well with everything and this makes for a lovely lunch on a hot summer's day.
Wonderful, easy and delcious recipe. Thanks Buzymomof3.

name: sausage breakfast gravy  for biscuits
review: My husband made this for breakfast this morning and it tuned out great! He used reduced-fat sausage and fat-free half and half and it was still rich and delicious. Thanks for posting!

name: fattoush   lebanese bread salad
review: Very nice and authentic salad. I also added some baby greens for a light lunch. Thank you.

name: briana s zesty spaghetti sauce
review: Nice zesty sauce.  To make the sauce even quicker than written, I adjusted for an electronic pressure cooker.  The only other changes I made was sub'd italian sausage and red wine.  Also added crushed garlic clove.  Tasty recipe, thanks for sharing.

name: tiny tacos  low fat
review: *Made for Australia/NZ swap #70*  These were really fast and easy !  VERY addictive !  I had doubled the recipe and served them with drinks and a few other nibbles, but these were ALL gone in a flash.  One of the guests followed me into the kitchen "to refill the plate" !  SORRY !    I topped the taco sauce with a small dollop of sour cream, just for a cool sensation.  Will keep this on the repeat list -- thanks for posting, Crafty Lady 13 !

name: masterchef stroganoff
review: *Made for Australia/NZ Swap #70*  Prepared following the directions, but used a package of stew beef and sour cream.  Due to not using tender beef, I let it simmer a few extra minutes, and served it over mashed potatoes.  Lovely comfort food on a cold windy night !  Thanks for posting, Chickee -- will be fixing this for company !!

name: white pizza or pizza blanca
review: I made two of these pizzas for my christmas party last night. I sauteed baby bella sliced mushrooms and bacon pieces with the onions and garlic. I also added some fresh spinach leaves on the top before adding the cheeses. I debated adding some alfredo sauce but am glad I didn't as it wasn't needed. I also used pre-baked thin pizza crust and made them several hours before the party. It turned out very flavorful and they were gone quickly. I am going to make again for christmas eve. Thanks for posting!

name: 4 salad dressings
review:
Creamy Dressing:
Wonderful dressing to serve with salad.
Pat this is just so simple to make, and so fantastic to serve on a hot night over your favourite salad.
I followed the recipe to a tee and it was just what was needed, the whole family tried it and loved it.
Thanks Pat.

Citrus Dressing ~ Lovely , so quick and easy to make and tastes sweet with a hint of a tang.
Not too much oil in it either, which we loved. Thanks Pat.

name: italian pignoli cookies  cookie mix
review: These are very good and the almond paste keeps them nice and chewy. I only rolled one cookie in pine nuts for the photo op. The rest of the batch I left plain. These cookies are super easy to make too. I mixed them with a fork in the beginning and then used my hands as I don't have a heavy duty mixer. Made for Make My Recipe Reunion in the Australian New Zealand forum.

name: creamy cheddar fondue
review: I had trouble with this recipe but maybe it was my cheese?  It was very thick and really stringy.  I added some milk to smooth it out. The taste was very rich.  If I make this again I would definitely add a bit of garlic.

name: imperial chinese restaurant sesame chicken
review: This recipe made quite a nice dinner for me, but I've decided not to give a star rating because I think I strayed too far from the recipe. I did use the basic idea of coating and frying chicken breast strips and putting them in sauce. I added a lot of vegetables - onion, carrot, shiitake and precooked bamboo shoot. I sauteed the vegetables first with the ginger and garlic, which I increased, and mixed in the sauce ingredients. I then fried the chicken, with potato starch, rather than cornstarch. (The two are very similar.) I used a bit more starch, but could not get a crisp crust, either. Then I put everything together, with sesame seeds sprinkled on top. The chicken was tender and moist and the sauce was pleasantly tangy. Thank you for sharing this recipe with us.

name: nutella biscotti
review: These are perfect!  Easy and very tastey!  I used mini chocolate chips, otherwise I followed the recipe exactly.  Thank you for posting!

name: meatballs in hungarian sour cream gravy
review: This is the exact recipe I've been searching for awhile.  I make meatballs in mushroom gravy for x-mas and have tried several different recipes.  I think what makes this recipe stand out is the onion soup mix, paprika & worcestershire sauce.  I've also tried a variation where I add beef gravy for the water/boullion and mushroom soup or yogurt for the sour cream.   Sometimes I will also add dried onions &/or roasted garlic.  Amended for cooking in a slow cooker.  Great recipe, thanks for sharing.

name: oven crisp chicken wings
review: I wouldn't say that these were crispy but we liked them. We dipped them in hot sauce once they reached the table.  Next time I would reduce the butter and I would drain the fat part way through the cook time, then I think they would be crispier. Thanks Marie.

name: raspberry swirl cookies
review: I LOVE these cookies! I always look forward to my sister-in-law making them every year for Christmas.

name: martha stewart s baked eggplant  aubergine   parmesan
review: Maybe the best eggplant parmesan I ever tasted!  I also liked it because the eggplant was baked, not fried in a bunch of oil.  I also used extra bread crumbs (fresh whole wheat) and more egg.  I halved the recipe and ended up with one extra meal for lunch between the two of us.  Thanks!

name: chocolate dessert cake
review: This is a really easy cake to make and uses common ingredients without the need for gluten-free flours/starches. the cake rose while cooking but settled down in the refrigerator to about 2cm high (just unfer an inch). Thick, dense and rich- delicious served with custard. Would also be great with some whipped cream or thick yogurt. We enjoyed this cake for my daughter's 16th birthday family get together. Photo to be posted later (my camera has a flat battery at the moment). Made for Make my Recipe Tag Game in the Aus/NZ Forum

name: cinnabon clone frosting
review: Delicious ... this would be great over Grands Cinnabons as a way to improve them!

name: tulip fairy s family christmas cake
review: My first attempt at a British fruit cake and we enjoyed it very much! Once I got the batter made, I realized my pan wasn't quite big enough and had to split it between two pans, and ended up overbaking a bit, but only the edges suffered, and they were easily trimmed off. I used all of the different dried fruits I had on hand and they worked very well. I also added in the end of a bottle of kirsch and the end of bottle of Grand Marnier with the brandy. I liked it well enough to experiment with making a real decorated Christmas cake next year! Thanks for posting!

name: spicy potatoes w smoked gouda  bacon   onions   9
review:
Wow...did we ever love these potatoes!! This is such an easy dish to prepare, but has lots of wonderful flavor. We loved the combination of the spices, bacon, and smoked gouda cheese. To add a little extra flavor, I used some of the bacon grease, instead of the butter, to cook the onions and spices and to brown the potatoes. I made this in a 12" cast iron skillet which gave the potatoes a nice, brown finish. I crumbled the bacon over the potatoes and sprinkled the cheese on top as directed. I popped the pan under the broiler until the cheese was melted...yum!! Thank you for sharing this fabulous recipe...it is definitely a keeper!!
**Made for Football Pool 2012**

name: linda s twice baked potatoes
review: Absolutely delicious!  I served these with my prime rib dinner on Christmas and will be putting them  on my menu next year.  I substituted onion powder for the green onion, and have to say they were even better reheated the next day!

name: green chile corn muffins with chile and lime butter
review: This makes a very dense batter so I thinned it just a bit with more milk. I used canned, chopped green chiles and only used about 2/3 of a small can. Next time I'd use the entire can. The chili powder is the most pronounced taste and I'd like to get more of the chiles. Made for PRMR tag.

name: candy cane popcorn crunch
review: This tastes awesome & looks really festive!  I loved the ratio of white chocolate to candy cane - the mint wasn't overpowering.

name: fruited baked squash
review: Great recipe! I loved the combination of fruits along with the ham. I only used one squash so adjusted the ingredients also using less ham than called for. We really enjoyed it and will make again. Thanks for sharing. Made for Football Pool 2012.

name: baked ziti from cook s illustrated
review: This was fabulous! I made my own Alfredo sauce; this is a keeper. Thanks for posting this one. Sorry I took so long to post this review.

name: 7 up cranberry punch
review: Really good!  I wasn't sure how the cinnamon would meld with the diet 7-up but it worked.   Turns out a really pretty pink.  Not a drop was left at our Christmas Eve Open House.

name: disney s french toast
review: This is a different way to do French toast - tasty!  The liquid mixture was the perfect amount for the whole loaf of bread but I only used about half of the cinnamon-sugar mixture.

name: strawberry balls
review: Really tasty little cheesecake bites!  Easy to make, too.  I rolled in coconut because that's what I had on hand.

name: spicy pretzels
review: These are really good if you like spice as they have a real kick!  I did use 3/4 pound of pretzels & think I should have used even more than that.  There was excess spice mix left in the pan when done baking.

name: pumpkin spice krispie treats
review: Great change from the ordinary!  I prefer my rice krispie treats to be chewier so I will add more marshmallows next time.  I also found the spice to be really subtle so I will increase that next time, too.

name: kittencal s italian melt in your mouth meatballs
review: Fabulous!  Really tender & flavourful!  I pre-baked & then kept warm in pizza sauce in the crockpot - served as an appetizer at our Christmas Eve Open House.  All 4 dozen meatballs I made were gobbled up!

name: nutmeg log cookies
review: These cookies look really nice but I found them to be too dry with not a lot of flavour.

name: lemon tea cookies
review: Really pretty little cookie!  Nice & tender but I would prefer the actual dough to be a little sweeter.

name: all purpose blueberry sauce
review: Perfect!  I was a little concerned that the sauce would be too tart but it definitely wasn't.  I made to serve over French Toast on Christmas morning.  However, I would make this for an ice-cream topping, too.

name: extra moist  lemon  sour cream and vanilla pound cake
review: So excellent! I didn't use the glaze. No need!  The crumb was soft, light, fluffy,  tender,  moist and the cake rose so high.  I baked it for 1 hour 20 minutes .  Thank you for such a wonderful recipe.

name: reese s peanut butter cake
review: Really good, quite easy!  I just made a horrible mess when cutting this (at room temp) - the chocolate still cracked like crazy!

name: toblerone shortbread cookies
review: My new favourite shortbread recipe!!  I actually found this on the Kraft Canada web site.  The only difference I made was to blend the sugar to a superfine texture.  Very tender cookie with the surprise of Toblerone!

name: the better butter chicken
review: A very tasty dish. I measured out most of the ingredients in the morning, so that it was quick to put together. I also added some cubed potatoes to lighten up the protein load in this dish, reducing the amount of the chicken. Perhaps a little more spice next time.

name: cherry jewel bars
review: Really pretty Christmasy square!  I used red & green maraschino cherries, as a personal preference.  I was skeptical about everything holding together with such few ingredients but it did!

name: allrighty then scrambled eggs   paula deen
review: Really nice fluffy way to make eggs - the cheese is a nice touch.  This recipe was part of our Christmas morning brunch this year.

name: 5 star bars
review: These were good but I think they should have been baked in a 13X9 pan as they were very, very thick.  I also only used half the icing as it was thick enough.

name: memphis barbecue sauce
review:
A really simple sauce to throw together- but with fabulous results.
We liked the heat in this, but next time would cut back a little on the mustard ( but then I did use a mixture of English and American mustard).
Used this on chicken, but can't wait to try it on ribs.
Another triumph Paula- thank you!
Made for Aus/NZ Recipe swap#71.

name: asparagus cream soup
review: Since it was a raw nasty day and I had frozen asparagus in the freezer, I decided to make this soup. I thought it was also a good way to get my GS to eat vegetables. I used 1 cup heavy cream and 2 cups whole milk. I'm glad my chef trained DD was here as I had no idea about the process of tempering an egg and probably would have messed up that part. All and all it was an easy soup to make and I like the touch of having the asparagus tips in the soup. I feel that the soup would benefit with the addition of garlic. Made for Winter Photo tag.

name: my tasty tasty venison   pork chili
review: Tasty, tasty indeed! Well worth the time to measure out the 28 different ingredients. I agree that it is best to make the chili, then let sit overnight in the refrigerator for the deep flavors to develop. (A bonus is that the fat rises to the top so you can literally take it off and throw it out.)

name: busy day pate
review: It's possible that this could be easier, but I doubt it!  The flavor is excellent, as well.  I used the mayo-horseradish combo.  Thanks for posting!  Note:  Mike Kingston is a character in Joanne Fluke's mystery novels about Lake Eden, Minnesota.  This recipe appears in her book, "Sugar Cookie Murder."

name: smokin   chicken kebabs
review:
These made for a very tasty dinner- simple marinade with a lovely flavour.
A great recipe for those lazy summer barbecues-thanks BK.
Made for Zaar Stars.

name: coconut peaks
review: Yummy! I made these in no time and loved that there were so few ingredients. I think that I would use unsweetened coconut the next time. Also, I didn't have lemon or lime zest so I used a splash of lemon juice. It actually made the cookies a little bit runny so I wouldn't do that next time! These are great and I made 16 of them. Made for Went To The Market tag game. Thanks Deantini! :)

name: dilly s onion rings
review: These are wonderful, easy pickled onion rings.  They go very well with the tomatoes.  I also tried them with sliced avocado--again, they were excellent.  Thanks for posting.  Note:  Ellie Kuehn is a character in Joanna Fluke's mystery novels.

name: braised boneless short ribs
review: Delish!! We used bone in (because that's what was on special this week). Made just as directed. When I saw it was Doctors recipe, I knew we'd love it, right on again.

name: costa rican hearts of palm salad
review: This was fantastic. The mustard blended nicely with the bland hearts of palm and zesty dressing. Made for ZWT and will certainly make again.

name: buttermilk bread abm
review: Nothing to say but EXCELLENT!!! Great with soup on these cold days. It was a hit at Christmas dinner with my whole family. Thanks, Carole

name: cut out cookies
review: Yummmmm.  Cut out cookies are a tradition at our place during the holidays. The 3 year old great grandaughter says "these are the best cookies she's ever made". We've added it to our must have for the holidays.

name: prairie fire dip
review: Very good! Made for our holiday party and get great reviews. Great flavor and easy to prepare especially for the hectic holiday time. Made for tag! YUMMMMM

name: just like tony packos cabbage rolls crock pot   copycat
review: This was very good. I used a pound of Jimmy Dean Hot Sausage and it was very good. It was easy to make, in fact the hardest thing to do was cook the cabbage. I used Muir Glen Fire Roasted Tomatoes and did not use the butter.

name: kachumber salad   india
review:
A wonderful light salad that is perfect for a hot summer's day.
I used cherry tomatos and iceberg lettuce, I did leave out the chillI and the tangy flavours were really wonderful although not spicy, I might add just a little chilli next time to see the difference, although we are not really chilli lovers in this family, so it will interesting to see if the family comment, as they really loved this salad without the chilli anyway.
Great salad Baby Kato. Thanks so much for posting.

name: oven roasted broccoli with parmesan  low fat
review:
What a wonderful and different way to serve broccoli and so easy also.
I did not use the chilli, but the the parmesan and garlic are so yummy.
This will be made many times over the winter...Thanks Crafty Lady for an easy and wonderfully different way to serve brocolli.

name: ranch roasted potatoes
review: Great flavour!  However, there was way too much oil which made the potatoes burn on the outside before they were cooked all the way through.  But, definitely worth fiddling with the recipe.

name: soup a l oignon   french onion soup
review: Excellent recipe for onion soup! I made it today to have tonight when we toast the new year! However, I did sneek an early taste. It is very rich tasting! I used 5 sweet vadalia onions for a sweet and savory combination. Tonight at midnight I will serve it with gruyere cheese on an Italian baguette broiled in the oven. Yum!  Made for Please Make My Recipe Reunion, 12-31-12 tag.

name: scalloped spinach
review: I'm not sure I drained my spinach enough, because mine turned out extremely wet. It also took longer to cook than I expected, even at 400 degrees. I used a mixture of cheeses and didn't use the breadcrumb topping.

name: broccoli gratin
review:
What can I say "Chesse and Broccoli" ..... They just go together so well, and this recipe is no exception. Lovely sauce and toasty breadcrumbs, just make this wonderful.
This made for a lovely side dish for our roast.
Thanks loof.

name: bbq oysters with ginger
review: Yum!  A real smart way of cooking Oysters, Thanks for the recipe Pete.

name: sage meat loaf
review: I made this for mine and my SO's dinner on 12/28/12. I did add some seasoned salt and a bit of garlic powder as I was mixing together the rest of the ingredients. I never use a loaf pan when making meatloaf, it's just always free-formed. But the baking time was " Spot On ".. I do think that the amount of sage was just right and the leftovers made a very good sandwich. Thanks for posting and " Keep Smiling :) "

name: prune and proscuitto rolls
review: These were a tasty little morsel - intended for this evening, but I had to sample. I did have a technical problem - my prosciutto was on the dry side and perhaps sliced a shade thick - it really did not want to wrap around. I buy prosciutto at several different markets, and next time will look for a somewhat moister ham sliced more thinly. I would like to experiment with soaking the prunes in port - I think that would add a nice layer of flavor to these.

name: easy potato and corn chowder   crock pot
review: We loved this chowder! I fixed this as the recipe directed, but found that I had to add 1 1/2 cups of chicken broth after 4 hours. It was starting to stick to the bottom and get to brown on the sides. The addition of the broth made it just right and the flavor was delish! Thanks, Carole in Orlando

name: skillet sauteed corn
review: Nice change-up for corn!  And it was just as quick as boiling or microwaving frozen corn.

name: green chili won ton soup
review: An interesting soup, not an unqualified success. I like all of the components of this soup, and I think a little tweaking will make the soup more to our liking. The cumin was a bit overpowering, to our taste, and I would definitely reduce the amount. I added a bay leaf to the chicken as it poached, took out the thighs and then added the cumin etc. I did not have fresh or dried cilantro. Next time i would add only the white part of the green onions and hold off the green parts until just before serving. I did hold back the spinach and added it very near the end, as I don't like the spinach overcooked.

name: bacon wrapped smoked gouda stuffed chicken breasts
review: Delicious & great presentation!  I need to practise my rolling technique but the recipe was quite easy other than that.  (I cheated with 2 or 3 toothpicks in every breast - lol)

name: spanish potato omelet  tortilla de patatas
review:
Yummy! We really enjoyed this quick and easy omelet. I only had 3 pieces of bacon, so I diced up a couple of pieces of leftover ham and added that to the pan. Also, I added 3 TBSP. of milk to the eggs when I whisked them together before adding them to the pan. I cooked this in a 10" cast iron skillet, so after adding the eggs to the pan I put the pan in the oven at 350 degrees for about 10 minutes or until the eggs were set. I served this with sour cream and salsa for a delicious, filling breakfast. Thank you for sharing!
**Made for 2012 Football Pool**

name: dr  oz s tangerine weight orade
review: I'm a bit ambivalent about this - I had hoped to really, really like it. It's ok. I know I would like it better if I sweetened it, but that's a bit counterproductive. The tangerine seemed to add a bit of bitterness to the drink - not bad, and I did drink all of it, but not what I was hoping for. I am wondering if it might not work better if I could zest the tangerine, although that might not be so easy to do. I need to get more tangerines to try this again - perhaps I should strain the tangerines out after they sat overnight in the tea? I'll be interested to hear others' experience with this.

name: potato bake with garlic and rosemary
review: Delish! I really enjoyed the addition of the rosemary to a traditional au gratin potato dish. I used regular cheddar and low fat milk. I made a single serving and wanted to eat in less than an hour so I sliced and microwaved my potato for 3 minutes with a little butter then added the sauce and baked for 30 minutes at 400. It came out just right the potatoes were cooked through and the flaver permeated the entire dish. Made for PRMRT.

name: kittencal s soft and tender pull apart garlic rolls buns
review: I made the dough in my bread machine.  Did not need to add additional water or flour to the mix. It was the perfect texture.  Great garlic flavor.  I added chopped parsley to the garlic butter that was brushed over the top of the rolls when they came out of the oven.  Gave the rolls a nice color.

name: foolproof pie dough  with vodka
review: I made a half recipe so that I had one 9" pie crust. I was looking for a recipe that uses both butter (for flavor) and shortening (for flakiness).I will use this recipe again.

name: super duper sweet potato salad    no mayo
review: Delicious salad- I saw your photo and just knew that I would have to try it .........very glad that I did too !  Definitely a salad that I will enjoy again. Sorry that I didn't get a photo for you. Reviewed for December 2012 recipe swap in the Aus/NZ forum.

name: sausage rolls
review: 5 stars for  an easy and great sausage roll recipe. Made these for my daughters 9th birthday morning tea today and these were appreciated by all my guests who had a big night out celebrating New Year's Eve. Made as written but I did add some very finely greated carrot to the sausage meat and sprinkled over some sesame seeds. Easy to make and so much better than the bought/frozen sausage rolls. I used sausage meat purchased from the butchers. Photo sldo being posted.

name: avocado and mandarin orange salad
review: Prepared this ahead for company of 6.  Did use just 1/2 cup salad oil, and combined all ingredients as directed.  We served family style, with lettuce in one bowl and fruit to follow, with dressing.  It was very tasty and most appropriate with a VERY spicy shrimp dish.  However, Next time, I would serve as I prefer, by tossing greens with the dressing before topping with fruit mixture.  Also, I think white balsamic wine vinegar would help carry the fruit flavors better.  Thanks for posting,KLHquilts.

name: balsamic and brown sugar roasted carrots
review: Yum! I cut this down to a small serving ( one large carrot cut into sticks) and added a couple of slices of onion. To reduce cooking time I splashed them with olive oil then microwaved for a couple of minutes. I put them on foil and added the rest of the ingredients then roasted for 10 minutes at 450 degrees. They came out perfectly cooked, my only regret was making just a single serving. Made for PRMRT.

name: quick italian parker house rolls
review:
I love quick and easy recipes like this one that you can whip up quickly, with very little effort. I could only find Grand's Jr. biscuits at my store, so these rolls turned out fairly large. Also, I ran short of Italian dressing, so for the last few rolls I melted a little margarine and added some Italian seasoning to it. I dipped the biscuits in the seasoned margarine and proceeded per the recipe directions. The rolls turned out great using both methods. We enjoyed these rolls with our minestrone soup. Thank you for sharing this fast and easy recipe!
**Made for 2012 Football Pool**

name: brown sugar meatloaf
review: Moist and delicious.  I only used 1/4 cup of sugar and it was perfect. Also, the next time, I would put the sugar/ketchup on top of the mealoaf instead of being on the bottom.  Other than that, this is a keeper recipe.

name: matthews gingersnap cookies 2002
review: The spice combination is excellent. As the poster mentions, baking can be a little tricky. Well, I was using a new oven, so got one batch a bit overdone. Will be more careful in the future. The dough was quite sticky, and I think it will be a good argument for the purchase of a set of cookie scoops. Thank you very much for sharing this lovely recipe with us.

name: bread dipping oil   garlic   herbs
review: I made this for New Year's Eve.  It was easy and good.

name: chicken and veggie pie with phyllo top
review: This is really good! I made my own veggie mix consisting of carrots, onions, a bit of green onion, celery and green pepper. I had to quickly add the phyllo top otherwise there would have been nothing to cover up, because I couldn't stay away from it. The filling would also be great in tartlets.

name: warm and cozy bottom round roast crock pot style
review: I loved the sage in the spice mixture! Great flavours and a really nice combination of spices.  I added carrots and potatoes to the bottom of the crock pot for a complete meal. The gravy was delicious too.  I will definitely make this again, thanks Connie!

name: graham cracker oatmeal crust
review: Really appreciated this recipe! Hubby wanted a low fat pudding pie for Christmas dessert, but I really don't like the store bought graham cracker crusts! They break so easily b/f I can even use it! This recipe was a life-saver. I used low fat cinnamon crackers & pressed the crust up the sides as well as on the bottom of the pie plate. I needed to bake it for 10 min, not 7 to get it crispy enough. I DID have a little problem w/ it being a tad crumbly, but no complaints. I used the "rolling pin" method to crush the graham crackers (worked great) & I think I needed to get the crumbs a bit more fine. Thanks AGAIN!

name: mint chocolate chip cookies
review: We really enjoyed these soft, minty cookies.  I could not find creme de menthe chips or chocolate chunks in my local stores, but I did find Hershey's chocolate mint chips so used 2 cups of those instead. I also used mint extract since we don't think it tastes like toothpaste, LOL. These are very pretty cookies and I plan to add them to my Christmas cookie list.

name: chicken pineapple stir  fry
review: Cut up some colored peppers, green onions and edamame for the vegies ..... quick, easy and tasty

name: leg of lamb boneless greek style
review: I made this last night and DH is still talking about it. We have a wonderful German butcher and got the leg of lamb from him. The roast is moist and so flavorful. I served it with Rice Pilaf and Roasted Brussel Sprouts. I am going to make this a Holiday tradition, but if DH had his way, it would be a weekly meal. Thanks for posting this recipe Dib's.

name: herb roasted chicken with vegetables
review: The vegetables were good, but the chicken itself was amazing. Moist, tender and full of flavor. Mine only needed an hour and a half to be perfectly done. Thank you.

name: soba soup with spinach and tofu
review: I am nott leaving a star rating on this because it isn't a poor rating due to the recipe.  This is more of just a friendly warning or suggestion to other cooks wanting to make this even though they can't find all the ingredients.  We couldn't find Dashi so after reading other reviews I decided to make it using stock.  I went with low sodium chicken because of the sodium content in the soy sauce.  To anyone else out there considering doing this, DON"T  I wasn't happy with the flavor of this at all, nor was anyone else in the family.  Just one of those things, sometimes you can make substitutions with great success and other times.......well not so much.  Next time we go somewhere near an Asian Market, I will be sure to pick up some dashi.  I can't wait to try this as written. It sounds so good.

name: naan bread croutons
review: WOW! Delicious! As a rule, I tell waitresses to hold the croutons when ordering a salad! But I will be making these little gems for all of my salads at home! They would be an accent to any salad or soup. I just ate them plain as a snack. Made for Photo tag.

name: lemon curried lamb chops
review: prepared by our chef in training daughter for New Years Dinner and was excellent

name: dirty shrimp in butter beer sauce
review: This dish was prepared by our daughter for New Years Dinner and I believe she followed the recipe as is and it was spectacular.  Will be making again for sure

name: lidalou  drink
review: This drink sure was a bright spot on a cold day. I've been meaning to make it forever, but one or another of the ingredients kept disappearing! It's been a coon's age since I 'layered' a drink, and I believe the Midori should go first, as it is the heaviest liquor, but it sinks, so no big deal. You will need to mix this up a bit, otherwise you will be drinking whatever is on the bottom, through your straw. Thanks for sharing a taste of the islands, Boomette!

name: spicy potato dosadillas  vegan
review: This is very,very good. It does tastes like a dosa and DH loves dosas. I loved the recipe and the ease of using tortillas. Really a great recipe. I served it with chutney and lime pickle.

name: debbie s crock pot chili
review: I made this chili last night and my family loved it!  I didn't have time for the crockpot, so just cooked on top of the stove for about an hour instead.  I left out the tomatoes since the kids don't like to see them in their chili and just added a little water to compensate.  I love the texture that is created by blending one can of beans - makes it more saucy.  I also liked the spice combination.  Will definitely make this again.  Thanks for posting!

name: my favorite steak marinade
review:
This is such an easy marindade.
DS and DH enjoyed the flavours this marinade gave to their lamb chops.
I followed the directios but only marinaded for half the time listed, due to time...... but they both said it gave a wonderful flavour to the chops. I used the b.b.q. to cook them and they had such a wonderful color to them when cooked.
This recipe will be used again Acadia....... for sure.

name: omani spice mix
review: Even though I've seen these spices in other cuisines, for some reason they are absolutely delicious in this combination and proportion.  I used it to season cauliflower and sweet potato chunks I was roasting.  I stirred it into some rice also.  Then I stirred it all together.

name: easy falafels
review:
I never had traditional falafels and never prepared these myself.
I knew they are usually deep fried, but I really don't like the smell of the hot oil in the house and so I opted to try this recipe.
They turned out perfect, not to dry, not sticky and perfectly baked in the oven.
I still had some sauces leftovers from our "foundue chinoise" which were a superb combination with these falafels.
My family loved this dish very much and will prepare falafels for sure again.

name: cake mix banana bread
review: Very versatile recipe which is yummy and moist!  I used a spice cake mix with my 3 large overly ripe bananas and this was a hit!  Skipped on nuts due to preference.  Can't wait for another slice with a bit of butter.  Thanks for sharing.  Found and made for I Recommend Tag Game.

name: cosy ham and bean soup
review: This is a keeper! Easy to put together and full of healthy ingredients and tasty goodness!

name: spanish noodles and ground beef
review:
It came as a great surprise to me, but this was actually better the next day.
My noodles took a lot longer to get soft--about 45 minutes--and I had to add more water twice. It also seemed to taste a little bland, even though the cheese I used was extra-sharp cheddar.
But when I took the leftovers out for lunch today, I found that the flavors had blended beautifully, and the noodles now had just the right amount of tenderness and firmness.
The purpose of the recipe is probably to make a quick, kid-friendly meal, but if you make some, try saving a bit overnight. That's when this dish really blossoms.
Made for ZWT 5

Update: This recipe works very well in an electric skillet.

name: bittman cabbage salad
review: I cook for someone with special dietary needs so I had to modify this recipe to suit her diet. I used water in place of the oil, regular balsamic diet, honey mustard and splenda not sugar. This salad got rave reviews. Thanks for the recipe

name: easy cheesy ham chowder
review: Who was it that said that eternity is two people and a ham? I've made great inroads on that New year's ham, but still had some left and came across this recipe. I did not use the bacon, sauteed the onions in a bit of butter, did not use the corn (Mr Grumpy is opposed to corn), added additional potatoes, some finely chopped celery and sliced carrots to compensate. Used less cheese, but used sharp cheddar. This as a very delicious soup on a cold day. Half the recipe left just a few spoonfuls in the pot, but we like large portions of soup.

name: easy to make butternut squash soup
review: Lovely soup. Quick and easy and fat-free, excepting for the yogurt. The yogurt and freshly grated nutmeg really made this soup extra tasty. Photo posted. Made for January 2012 recipe swap in the Aus/NZ Forum.

name: old fashioned sour cream sugar cookies
review: The most disappointing sugar cookie recipe I've ever tried. First, the dough is very sticky even after refrigerating overnight. Make sure you use plenty of flour (or 1/2 flour and 1/2 confectioner's sugar) to roll them out. Second, they puff up so much that it totally obliterates the design on our cookie cutters. If the flavor made up for it, I wouldn't mind so much, but we thought they were rather blah. A few of us thought they were kind of like a white cake, but my husband said it was like eating a biscuit. I definitely would not bother making these again.

name: roasted russet slices with sherry
review: This is a very tasty recipe, but then how can you go wrong with potatoes cooked in wine and butter? I only used one russet potato as there were only 3 peeps eating them. I used freeze dried parsley since the bunch I had in the hydrator were spoiled. I think it worked out fine with the freeze dried parsley, just won't be as vibrant in the photo. I think next time I make, I'll add onions too. Made for Photo tag.

name: ground turkey chili for people who hate ground turkey
review: I am very happy with how this turned out.  I took the advice of several reviewers and doubled the amount of spices.  I also added about 1/8 t. ground cayenne pepper.  I also subbed black beans for the kidney beans.  Very good.

name: chocolate cinnamon rolls  adopted
review: This review is based on the cinnamon rolls being something worth eating, without regard for health benefits. That was my intention in making them. They are not awful. They are just not very good. I'd say three and a half stars, rounded down in this case for disappointment. I was concerned, when I realized how little sugar is used in the dough, but I decided to follow the recipe exactly this time. Although yeast doughs tend to be less sweet than quick doughs, this is too extreme, especially when considering the cocoa. Live and learn, I guess.

name: pasta with courgette and walnut sauce
review:
This is really lovely pasta dish.
I swapped the walnuts for macadamia's but everything else was as per the recipe and we really enjoyed this.
I also served the leftover cold next day as a pasta salad and it was just wonderful.
Thanks Kathy, I am sure I will being making this again.

name: sheila s chicken milanese
review: I love recipes like this...fresh tasting and easy to put together. I added a bit of cooked quinoa to the salad and it was fantastic. This is going to be the first recipe in my best of 2013 cookbook!!

name: berry  berry good muffins
review: Yum! I just made this and wanted to review them right away. Delicious! Moist and flavorful - I used blueberries, raspberries and blackberries, added a touch of cloves and allspice along with the cinnamon. I used about 6 T of melted butter instead of a full stick. Thanks for posting!

name: quick bbq zucchini
review:
I used fresh herbs for this and mixed just a touch of chilli to the herbs.
This was fantastic, with great flavours ..... even the zucchini hater of the family tried it!
So quick and easy to make on the barbie ........ I will be making this again for sure!
Thanks Peter.

name: too easy croissants
review:
I thought these came out GREAT!
The recipe is first rate!
I would NEVER have attempted to try and make!
And NOW I can PROUDLY say based on this recipe (thanks to Barn and Peggy too) that croissants today I DAD bake!!! WHOO HOO!

name: spanish potato omelet  tortilla de patatas
review: This is really good! I made it as written and it was just right. Thanks for sharing. Made for Football Pool 2012.

name: roasted fingerling potato salad
review: Fantastic potato salad- my family want to give you 25 stars....but we are settling for the 5 allowed. We used fingerling Potatoes (known as kipfler in Australia) and all fresh herbs for the salad. Delicious! Definitely a recipe that we will be making again. My youngest daughter doesn't go much on potato salad so we kept some of the potatoes just like big chips for her. Photo also posted. Made for January 2013 Recipe Swap in the Aus/NZ Forum.

name: tortellini ros  tortellini with tomato cream sauce
