Because I greatly reduced the red pepper it did need some other seasoning so I followed another reviewer's additions and added a little fish sauce , used chicken broth in place of water and added some basil at the end. I loved how easily this came together and look forward to enjoying it again. Made for Culinary Quest 3

name: lynn s favorite jerk chicken
review: I wasn't sure if we'd like this - instead we loved it! The spices add lovely flavor with none being overpowering. i used two types of vegetable seasonings one for veggies, one with some dried veggies in it I reduced the red pepper flakes quite a bit and it was still spicy enough and used less sugar , I marinated for about 1 3/4 hours. Made for Culinary Quest 3 for one of the Iota Eta Pi

name: chicken in red curry and coconut
review: A delicious and easy-to-make Thai red curry. To make it go a bit further, I added a small bunch of broccoli florets and several sliced mushrooms. I'll keep this as a go-to recipe for busy nights, but I will cut the salt in half. Both the fish sauce and red curry paste have a good hit of salt, so a whole teaspoon of extra is not really necessary. Thanks for posting. Made for the Culinary Quest 2016.

name: italian parmesan herb mix
review: LOVE this! Going to use it for edible gifts this Christmas. Great on pizza dough for bread sticks.

name: everything topping mix for bread and bagels
review: Really good! Maybe a tiny bit too much salt though.

name: five spice peanuts
review: Really good! I would just use a little more 5 spice powder next time.

name: napa nouveau pierogies
review: Quick to make and lots of vibrant colors... a very satisfying vegetarian dinner!

name: black bean and corn salad   dip
review: This was easy to throw together. I used fresh tomatoes and peppers from the garden. Next time I will add more garlic and maybe more tomatoes as well.

name: chicken tater tot casserole
review: I tried this casserole because I had sour cream, 2 cups cooked chicken, jalapeno monterey jack and tater tots to use use up. Unfortunately, I found it too salty and DH found it too cheesy! The addition of broccoli would have been really nice ...would have broken the salt and cheese problem perfectly. Sorry ...but in the end it wasn't enough for me to do again

name: savory thai sticky rice
review: I made half a batch of this yummy and easy-to-make version of sticky rice. Due to operator error (I was a bit heavy-handed with the soy and fish sauce), the final result was a tad too salty for my tastes, although my husband thought it was perfect as is. So advice to the heavy-handed. Go easy on the salty ingredients. In other words, follow the recipe!

name: pumpkin pie spice mix
review: Perfect for a small batch!

name: fresh pineapple salsa
review: Excellent and refreshing salsa that I made as written and served with baked fish. Thanks so much for posting. Made for the Culinary Quest 2016.

name: pretzel and mustard baked chicken
review: Good and easy. I actually used a honey mustard pretzel dip for the mustard. Great flavor.

name: freezer ready cornflake chicken fingers
review: Good and easy. Didn't freeze them, just cooked them that day.

name: thai dipping sauce
review: This dipping sauce is so good. It is spicy hot, but has depth of flavor. I used it with chicken.

name: thai pineapple salad
review: I liked this salad very well even though it is a bit on the sweet side. Next time I would add MORE green onions to contrast with the sweet fruit.

name: quick  n crunchy potato chip chicken
review: Good and easy. I used ruffles since I don't like flavored chips.

name: thai chili beef burger
review: The flavor of these burgers was delicious. I also didn't care for the texture with the breadcrumbs. The burger would be juicier (the way American's like) without them.

name: cheesy cracker chicken
review: Good and super easy. My kids loved them! I used Cheezits.

name: pistachio chicken strips
review: These are AMAZING! So flavorful. I added lemon zest and doubled the coating amounts.

name: twisted sisters creamy cucumber salad
review: I used fresh peppers and tomatoes from the garden. I didn't have a red onion so I substituted a sweet onion and it turned out great. DD kept picking the cucumber chunks out, so next time I may use three. This is a great summer salad that the entire family enjoyed!

name: easy chicken pad thai  without tamarind
review: Delicious! Pad Thai is one of my favorite dishes to order when I eat at a Thai restaurant, so I was thrilled to find an easy, delicious recipe that I could make at home. It goes together quickly and easily even though the instructions seem long. The flavors were spot on and I will definitely be making this again. The instructions call for chili but there isn't chili in the ingredients. I looked up the original recipe on About.com and saw that the ingredient list includes: 1 fresh red or green chili, sliced. So, I used a sliced serrano chili. Thank you for sharing this wonderful recipe. **Made for 2016 Culinary Quest - Thailand for the Pi Rho Maniacs**

name: peanut chicken saute
review: Delicious! We loved the subtle, sweet peanut butter sauce in this dish. It really complimented the slight bitterness of the bok choy. I love that it went together very quickly allowing me to get dinner on the table in a hurry. **Made for Culinary Quest 2016 - Thailand for the Pi Rho Maniacs**

name: breakfast in a jar
review: These are fantastic! I used three eggs whisked up in place of the egg beaters, two slices of deli ham chopped, and added some dried parsley. I made two planning to have the second one later, but I ate them both immediately!

name: breakfast apple english muffin rounds
review: Simple and delicious! I think next time I will try maple syrup instead of brown sugar.

name: red curry chicken with snake beans  long beans
review: This was really, really good. I think the kaffir leaves are what put it over the top. They are my new secret ingredient.

name: braised green beans  fassoulakia yahni
review: Such a simple and tasty way to make green beans a little different. Served with Greek-style lamb shanks and rice with spinach and feta.

name: greek style watermelon salad
review: I love watermelon salads very much and I really recommend to try this delicious recipe. I served this salad on a big serving plate layering the ingredients (topping with feta, herbs, vinegar and oil). Thanks a lot for offering us this great recipe!

name: rice with spinach   greek
review: Oh yum, oh yum, oh yum. I use a slightly different approach to steaming rice, so I put the baby spinach on top of the rice as it finished its steaming (off the heat). I then stirred in the lemon and nutmeg, and added the feta on top. Never, ever have I thought of adding spinach and feta to rice, and now I can't get it out of my mind. Great combo! Served with Greek-style green beans and lamb shanks.

name: lamb shanks with garlic and port wine   pressure cooker
review: I don't have a pressure cooker, so I made this on the stove top. I cooked it on low (covered) for about 2 hours. The sauce cooked down a bit so I did have to add some extra water twice (but no more than a cup in all). The sauce is fabulous and the shanks were oh-so tender. Served with two Greek-style side dishes—braised green beans and rice with spinach and feta cheese. Fantastic dinner. Thanks for posting.

name: greek garden salad for 2
review: With exception of the olives, Italian dressing and the feta, we used fresh ingredients from the garden. Served as a side to grilled fish.

name: easy greek salad
review: Wonderful, wonderful, wonderful salad. I made pretty much as written. I added a couple of chopped green onions because I didn't have quite enough red onion. You are absolutely right—the dressing makes this salad. I've been told I can make this again...and again...and again. Three of us ate all of this one.

name: marinated cucumbers  onions  and tomatoes
review: We used fresh tomatoes and mint from the garden. I made it late in the morning and let it marinate until dinner time. Pretty quick to throw together and very tasty. A nice light summer salad.

name: grilled salmon  bacon   feta packets
review: I used Aldi's Fit N' Active Ranch, low sodium bacon and fresh tomatoes from the garden. Other than the bacon pan, the clean up was a breeze. The adults liked this but the kids did not. We'll save this recipe for nights that the kids are not home.

name: broiled mahi mahi with parsleyed tomatoes and feta
review: Oh wow! This is a great way to make fish. Made as written, except that I grilled the fish for 4 minutes each side. The tomato sauce is superb. I spooned the sauce over the fish to serve. Forgot to add the feta before I did the photo.

name: healthy cucumber tomato salad
review: We used a sweet onion and cut the amount way back. We enjoyed it, but like Bergy, we all agreed we would like it better with a touch of dressing. Over all, a great summer salad, especially when cucumbers and tomatoes are abundant.

name: easy breakfast bake
review: Wow! I've never liked grits before but this is really tasty. My first four eggs sank to the bottom, maybe because I used a deep casserole dish. So once the casserole thickened a bit, I just cracked four more eggs on top. I think next time I might reduce the liquid in the grits, I had to double the cooking time to get it to thicken. Also, the leftover cheese sauce needed another 1/2 cup of milk or so to pour on the casserole after cooking. And I added some chopped parsley. Definitely a few kinks to work out in the recipe, but still a good one!

name: creamy crock pot macaroni and cheese
review: This was good but a bit bland. Loved how easy it was, so it could be a great holiday side dish, but I'd add in some additional cheese like maybe parmesan and Gruyere to punch up the flavor. Topped it with a bit of parsley.

name: broccoli potato casserole
review: This recipe needs a bunch of adjustments, but it'a a great starting point. I used an organic cream of mushroom soup and mixed it with chopped fresh broccoli (not frozen), rather than pouring it on top. This solved the problem of the broccoli not being flavorful, and helped keep it from being mushy. Sprinkled it with cheddar as said in the recipe. I used some really good instant mashed potatoes so it was really fast to make them, then stirred paprika and garlic powder into the potatoes as well as sprinkling a bit on top. This made it really flavorful! The whole family loved this and we ate it as a one pot meal, but it would be a good side for chicken, turkey, or ham as well.

name: creamy corn salad
review: This is a quick and easy to throw together summer salad. It doesn't even need time for the flavors to meld. The family enjoyed it. I served it with grilled sausages for a quick week night meal.

name: cheesy ham and sweet potato casserole
review: Wow, wow, WOW! This casserole is amazing! I think I'll skip peeling the sweet potatoes next time. The flavor was spot on and we will make this regularly. Used some good deli ham that was thin sliced rather than cubed ham.

name: herbed breakfast sandwich
review: Good and easy. I used butter, mayonnaise, and an English muffin.

name: greek lemon ice cream
review: Yum!! I love anything lemon. This ice cream was light, tart, and very refreshing. To boost the lemon flavor a little, I added the zest of one lemon and 1/4 teaspoon lemon extract to the yogurt mixture before putting it in my ice cream maker. It had just the right amount of lemon tang. **Made for 2016 Culinary Quest - Greece for the Pi Rho Maniacs**

name: grilled peaches with greek yogurt
review: Super easy and so good! I prepared this with autentic Greek yogurt, Greek peaches and Greek honey! I grilled the peaches on charcoals (after cleaning the grid). WONDERFUL result and great surprise for my familt! Made for "grill it up - Greek style" event.

name: creamy scrambled eggs in the microwave
review: I was skeptical that microwaved eggs could actually come out fluffy and creamy, but these really do! I just wanted a single serving, so I used 2 eggs, half a tablespoon of butter, and a generous splash of milk (plus the rest of the ingredients to taste). Simple, quick and tasty, exactly what I need in the morning! Thanks for posting! Made for CQ 2016 NYC for Team Iota Eta Pi

name: braised green beans  fassoulakia yahni
review: This was a nice side dish we all enjoyed. It was a nice change from plain green beans and went will with the grilled pork chops I served them with. Made for Culinary Quest 3

name: grecian style shrimp scampi
review: This was unusual but tasty. The rosemary was very dominant and might cut back on it a bit. I reduced the butter and oil and there was still plenty, it was very rich so after tasting the dish as written I added some fresh lemon juice, it gave the dish a nice tang that made the richness less overwhelming. I loved the feta with the shrimp and I loved dipping my bread into the mix. Made for Culinary Quest 3

name: greek feta burger
review: This was a great burger with so many flavors going on, my DH said he liked it better than the burger at our fav Tom Douglas restaurant which he loves! I didn't read the recipe right and ended up putting lemon juice and cucumber in the burger as well as in the yogurt mix. I was surprised by how much I loved the yogurt topping. I used a regular bun instead of sourdough roll. Made for Culinary Quest 3 for one of the Iota Eta Pi

name: simple greek beet salad
review: Oh yum, oh yum, oh yum! I bought 3 pounds of beets yesterday for $2, and I know how the other 2 pounds will get used. This recipe is excellent and oh-so easy to make. I had to laugh at your suggestion that peel the beets could be 'messy'. You should see my colourful hands. :) We're big fans of feta cheese so I added about 2 ounces of crumbled feta. This will become a go-to recipe. So many thanks for posting.

name: greek lemon chicken
review: I had two whole chicken breast that just happened to be attached to the test of the chicken, so I made this as a roast dinner. So slide the lemon slices under the breast and put a lemon in the chicken cavity. Scattered the onions and olives around the whole bird. The result was a sensational dish served with baked potatoes, corn on the cob and salad. Oh, and I used a homemade Greek seasoning from Annacia

name: butter dip biscuits
review: These biscuits came up quite dense. Not sure if I would make them again!!!

name: vichyssoise  potato   leek soup
review: We love vichyssoise and this is a lovely version. I made mostly as written. I was short one potato, so added a peeled and diced turnip in its place. The ingredients/instructions were the only source of confusion. Milk wasn't mentioned in the instructions. I thought the soup was thinned adequately with just the cream. So then I wondered if you meant the ingredients to say add a cup of cream or milk. You might want to clarify for novice cooks. Served hot because it's winter in Australia. Thanks for posting.

name: linguine with marinara sauce and meatballs
review: I thought the carrots were a great idea, but the meatballs were not my favorite. My husband liked everything though. Of course, he is not Italian. I would love to make this sauce again since it was so full of flavor and the carrots sweetened the dish.

name: blue aegean angel
review: I'm not big on cocktails or sweet drinks, but I was keen to try this for two reasons. It was a Greek recipe for the Culinary Quest and someone gave me half a bottle of Blue Curacao. So time to get out the tall drink glass and have a go. It is too sweet for my taste, but it would be perfect for those who like sweeter drinks. I think a couple of ounces of soda water would take the edge off the sweetness. Oh, and the colour is fantastic. To that end, I have posted two photos—one before stirring and one after.

name: pickled cluckerberries  eggs
review: My favorite way to pickle eggs. Best thing to do with that jar after the pickles are gone. My home canned pickles have garlic and dried cayenne peppers in them so I don't add extra since the flavor is already there.

name: tomato hummusoup
review: This is a really delicious soup. It combines two of my favorite things - hummus and stewed tomatoes!

name: a really good tomato recipe
review: I made this for dinner tonight with croutons from the farmers market and tomatoes from our garden. Quick and easy to put together. Our family couldn't agree on a star rating for this. My daughter didn't like it at all. My husband thought it was just okay and I really liked it.

name: shrimp baked with feta  ouzo and cognac
review: This was fabulous, Vic! I just happened to have bottles of both Ouzo and Metaxa on hand (y'know, from the last time we ended up in Greece? Lol), so I figured why not? Flaming the shrimp was a little scary because I'm usually too much of a chicken to actually flame anything in my own kitchen (I have a bad track record for accidentally starting alcohol fires at work), but it really did tame the liquor in this. I served this as part of a "surf and turf" dinner with some Delmonico steaks and Syracuse hot salt potatoes -- Greece by way of NYC? Thanks for posting this wonderful shrimpy dish! Made for CQ2016 Greece for Team Iota Eta Pi

name: grecian pork tenderloin
review: Yummers! This is an excellent way to prepare pork tenderloin. Very flavorful.

name: easy greek salad
review: This was fresh and delicious, we loved the feta and lemon together. I used all romaine instead of the spring mix. Made for CQ3

name: grilled salmon with fresh tomato
review: Had some fresh tomatoes from the garden that I used to make this. While we thought this was okay, we also felt it was a little lacking in something. It would be a great recipe to play with.

name: walnut rolls
review: Well, these were quite a roller coaster ride for me, lol! I messed them up, but didn't catch my mistake until it was too late, so I just ran with it. After I made my three rolls, I was out of the walnut mixture but still had another 9 sheets of phyllo left over. I went back and reread the recipe, and realized that I had misunderstood it and made each of my rolls with only three sheets of the phyllo instead of 6. Since there was no way I was unrolling the three rolls to add the extra phyllo, I just used the remaining sheets to make two other types of cookies: I made two rolls filled with cinnamon and coconut sugar, and I made a third roll filled with raspberry orange mango jam. The cinnamon sugar ones I cut into logs, and the jam filled roll I sliced just like the walnut filled ones. The cinnamon sugar logs were actually pretty good, but the jam filled ones were just way too sweet. They baked up pretty, because they spread into rose shapes once the jam melted, but I ended up throwing them away because if something is too sweet for ME, I know no one else will be able to handle them, lol. The walnut filled ones were good with just the three sheets of phyllo in them, but they were really fragile. I baked these for the full 30 minutes, but I think I could've shaved off a minute or two, because some of the bottoms were starting to get a little bit burnt at 30 minutes. I poured the syrup over the baked cookies, but it seemed to just go right through them to the bottom of the pan. I tried one of the warm walnut filled ones, and was kind of disappointed because they were super-sweet and kind of dry. I thought about it for a minute, and realized that what I needed to do was: 1. Keep spooning the syrup over the cookies, flipping them periodically so the syrup wouldn't just sit and make the bottoms soggy, and 2. Allow these to cool. After I got the syrup to start soaking into the whole cookies, I popped the whole pan into the fridge. Not long enough to chill them, but just long enough to make everything a bit less squishy and more cohesive. Once I did those two things, these became much more like the familiar texture of baklava, and it tamed the sweetness a bit. No getting around it, syrup-soaked phyllo pastries are gonna be really sweet regardless, but letting them cool first keeps the sweetness from being overly cloying. These definitely need a time out after baking to be their best selves. In the end, these tasted good enough to be comparable to the little Greek phyllo pastries on a tray that my mom buys for the holidays. Thanks for posting, sheepdoc! Made for CQ 2016 Greece for Team Iota Eta Pi

name: hot jam sandwich
review: This was a great start. I used slices of a sourdough loaf and added cream cheese. Also put a tiny bit of almond extract in the egg which went great with the raspberry. Next time I will add a slice of turkey!

name: tasty oatmeal the microwave way
review: Really good and easy. We used freeze dried cherries which worked great and tasted amazing!

name: cola burgers
review: Not ingredients I'd think to put in burgers but the flavor and texture were pretty good.

name: pumpkin cream cheese muffins
review: Really good. I want to try them with whole wheat flour next. Be aware that you need to check the muffins with a toothpick because the cream cheese makes the tops really white so they don't look done.

name: summer everything pasta salad
review: Really good. We did chunks for the mozzarella as well. I ended up adding a little more vinegar to the dressing. BIG amount so perfect for potlucks or large gatherings.

name: shrimp and asparagus stir fry
review: SO delicious! I've made it as written, but also subbed hoisin sauce when out of oyster sauce and, although it changes the flavor, it's still wonderful.

name: awesome bacon tomato dip
review: Football, wings and bacon dip! I served this with wheat thins and tortilla chips. My family seemed to like it better with the tortilla chips.

name: easy snicker pie
review: Very easy to make. It was good, but we felt it was missing something. It wasn't as rich as we had hoped it would be. If I made this again, I would at least add another snickers bar and try to chop them as fine as I could so they would be spread more evenly throughout the middle layer.

name: banana raisin bran muffins
review: Great recipe. Very moist and quick to make. I doubled the recipe, and added cinnamon and peanut butter chips. Delicious! Thank you for sharing.

name: the ultimate salmon fillets
review: We enjoyed this recipe. Not everyone in our family is a fish lover. The ingredients in the sauce is the main flavor that comes through instead of the fish. I served this with steamed broccoli and cheddar bacon bread that I got from the local farmer's market.

name: turkey pita sandwich
review: These are really good, though I'm not giving a star rating because I changed the recipe quite a bit. Our cucumbers got shoved to the back of the fridge and froze, so I skipped those. I used dried dill, lemon juice, and garlic powder in the yogurt. Then I used goat cheese instead of feta, and added some chopped pecans. Great way to use up leftover turkey or chicken!

name: guaranteed winner london broil
review: Great recipe! I seared it on all sides in my dutch oven and then cooked it in that for about 20 minutes.

name: snappy apple pie
review: Really easy way to make a rustic apple pie. Only thing I would change would be to add some salt sprinkled onto the crust, but other than that quite good and pretty.

name: jackie s apple pie crisp cookies
review: These are fantastic! I've never used butter Crisco but went with it. I would love to try these again with butter next time. I didn't have apple pie filling but had fresh picked honey crisp apples so just tossed them with cinnamon, nutmeg, all spice, sugar, and cornstarch to make my own filling. Everyone I've shared these with has LOVED them.

name: mom s waldorf salad
review: This was great!

name: apple turnip casserole
review: Not something I would have thought to make, and quite tasty. Went great with pork loin.

name: philly mashed potatoes
review: Our family loved this. I'm leaving the stars blank though because I used instant mashed potatoes and then stirred everything into that. It made it so easy! I also added some chopped parsley with the french fried onions.

name: 2 ingredient pumpkin muffins
review: Quick and easy to make. Dividing the batter into cupcake liners is what took the most time. Who knew something so simple to whip up would be so tasty to eat.

name: roasted cauliflower with garlic
review: I used one head of cauliflower because there were only three of us eating dinner. I didn't have any minced garlic so I used some Trader Joe's smashed garlic and also sliced up some fresh cloves (doubling the total amount called for) We all enjoyed it. I will definitely be making it again.

name: brussels sprouts pickles
review: SO good! Can't believe I hadn't thought of pickling these before. Just made a batch for the fridge.

name: pressure cooker beef and noodles
review: This flavor is incredible! Just make sure you use enough salt. It really makes a difference. Also, no need for mashed potatoes.

name: outback steakhouse style steak
review: AMAZING!!!!!!!!

name: lentil soup in 10 minutes  pressure cooker
review: So delicious! I didn't have savory but it was great without it.

name: italian potato  rice    spinach soup in pressure cooker
review: This was filling and amazing! We didn't even need the cheese.

name: pioneer woman fresh corn and wild rice casserole
review: Made this with rehydrated freeze dried sweet corn. SO good! And really easy.

name: chicken and dumplings   pressure cooker   instant pot   instapot
review: Flavorful, perfect dumplings. Really good and love how fast it is in the pressure cooker.

name: amy sedaris s vanilla cupcakes
review: Rating for cupcake only: I thought these had great flavor and were easy to make. Downside is that they did dry out very quickly and were pretty dense. I didn't read reviews or might have added the extra vanilla, but I still thought they were tasty.

name: grilled salmon
review: Ok, so I went a little overboard on the "to taste" ingredients. I had a sliver of red onion left in the fridge so I coarsely chopped it and sprinkled it on top. Next time I will know not to go so heavy on the other items. I served this with oven roasted asparagus and a five grain Italian bread with an olive oil dipping sauce. A delicious meal!

name: asparagus
review: I had to use dried thyme because we didn't have any fresh on hand. Still tasted great! It was quick and easy to throw together. I served it with grilled salmon and a five grain Italian bread with an olive oil dipping sauce. An easy and delicious meal!

name: soft pumpernickel bread  abm
review: Good, easy. I took it out of the Abm, made two small loaves, and baked for about 17 minutes. Used more molasses and a bit of cocoa for color. Very nice dough to work with.

name: basil pesto
review: Really good pesto. This was my first time making pesto and the family loved it. I used walnuts in place of the pine nuts. Fabulous, thank you!

name: french onion pork chops skillet
review: This is a simple weeknight meal. I think Swiss cheese would be good on this too. Thanks for the recipe.

name: salmon and asparagus in foil
review: What an easy way to make dinner. I used a garlic pepper, sea salt blend and put a little directly on the salmon as well as on top of the asparagus. I don't think it would have had enough flavor other wise, so I am glad I did. Clean up is so easy with this because of the foil packets. I would definitely make this again.

name: jack o lanterns
review: So cute and easy! We used a pub cheese spread, all natural olives, and 21 grain bread so it was a pretty healthy snack. We also added broccoli stems for a stem. My one and three year old kids loved using a glass to cut out the circles, spreading the cheese, and making the faces.

name: boston market meatloaf by todd wilbur
review: I haven't had the Boston Market version to compare, but I found this rather bland with a weird texture. Next time I will use my own seasonings, and a little less tomato sauce.

name: tsr version of applebee s honey grilled salmon by todd wilbur
review: AMAZING! We used skin on salmon fillet and just broiled it for 5-8 minutes. Really wonderful sauce.

name: yam  n butternut squash mash
review: Fantastic! The whole family loved this.

name: quinoa winter salad
review: This recipe is a good start but needed some additions as it was a bit bland. I used a sweet potato because my acorn squash ended up being flavorless. After making the quinoa, I made a dressing with salt, pepper, olive oil, and apple cider vinegar to pump up the flavor and then it was perfect!

name: apple slab pie
review: We LOVED this pie! The slab style makes it easy to serve a large group. We had fresh picked honeycrisp apples from a local orchard, and loved the sweet/tart taste of them in the pie. If you prefer a sweeter pie filling you will want to add sugar, but this was just right for us.

name: sweet potato gratin
review: REALLY tasty and easy!

name: mashed brussels sprouts with parmesan and cream
review: The whole family loved this. I could eat the entire casserole dish by myself.

name: bread stuffing   nothing compares with this
review: This was good. I used a no name herb stuffing mix since my store didn't have Pepperidge Farm.

name: apple cranberry crisp pie
review: The taste is great but I could tell I'd have some problems with the texture if I didn't make adjustments, which is why I'm not doing a star rating. I used dried cranberries that I plumped up with a bit of boiling water, then drained. That way they sweetened the filling slightly and didn't release liquid. I also used an extra apple and used ground oats in the filling which really soak up the liquid well.

name: flourless brownies  sugar free  low carb
review: Made this for a birthday celebration for someone on a restricted diet. Followed the recipe exactly. They didn't look like the picture at all, very flat. I felt horrible. Everyone took one bite and that was it. I won't make these again.

name: skyline chili dip
review: I couldn't find skyline chili down here so I used some leftover homemade chili. I used low fat cream cheese and did include the optional onions. I did the microwave option, but the cheese didn't melt after two minute. I had to put it in an additional two minutes. Next time I think I will bake it in the oven. Served with tortilla chips for dipping.

name: apple pie nachos lite
review: These are incredible! I used real whipped cream and left the apple peels on, but other than that followed the recipe. Really cute and very tasty.

name: bonnie s sweet potato pie  low fat  no sugar added  recipe
review: This was really easy to make. Not giving stars because I used regular sugar and cream cheese so I can't speak to the flavor as written. But it was good for us!

name: kentucky bourbon fudge
review: Really good. Be aware it tastes like bourbon, not chocolate, which was great!

name: peanut butter pumpkin pies
review: Just okay. The muffin tin needs to be greased as they totally stick, and then the crescent rolls get soggy as they sit.

name: apple stuffed acorn squash
review: Really wonderful recipe!

name: val s cranberry salsa
review: This is AMAZING! Great with crackers or chips.

name: hot roasted turkey mountain  hot turkey sandwich
review: I added a lettuce leaf to make it feel more like a sandwich. I tried with and without a top piece of bread. Definitely better with just one piece!

name: spicy party shrimp
review: These were pretty good. I'd definitely increase the horseradish and hot sauce next time though.

name: light and fluffy pumpkin pancakes
review: Yum! Nice balanced flavor. I freeze pumpkin in half cup portions so used it all. I used 2Tbls brown sugar and a couple top of white sugar, 1/4 cup of flour was whole wheat pastry, I'd use more next time. I increased the cinnamon and didn't use nutmeg because I was out. I followed another suggestion and spread the batter a bit so no problem with undercooked. I

name: chipotle chicken mac and cheese with bacon bread crumbs  rsc
review: So SO good! I used leftover turkey in it. It is pretty spicy since I left the seeds in the peppers. Fortunately my toddler and preschooler love spicy, they just exclaim "HOT!" after every bite!

name: pumpkin creme caramel
review: I chilled these 6 hours but not overnight, and had some trouble getting them out of the mold. The flavor was fantastic though!

name: date cookies like awrey s
review: These are quite tasty. I felt the cookie mix needed a bit more butter or less dry ingredients, so I will reduce the flour and oats a bit next time, but the cookies were delicious.

name: nana s pa dutch potato and bread filling
review: Really good! Not giving a star rating because I used instant mashed potatoes made with the chicken stock, milk, and butter. But everything else was the same and it was a great combo of mashed potatoes and stuffing.

name: hazelnut pumpkin pie
review: My husband LOVES this pie! The crust is fantastic. I was a little nervous about the creamer because it smelled terrible, but the flavor was great. Definitely lighter and fluffier than we were expecting, but excellent.

name: leftover turkey   enchiladas
review: This was fantastic! We had a lot of leftover filling but will gladly use it in burritos. Best way to use up turkey!

name: tuscan white bean   spinach soup
review: Fast, easy, healthy, forgiving for subbing ingredients. I left out the Rosemary in favor of oregano and cut down the quantity of pasta and used smaller pasta. Would be just as good without pasta or with some crumbled Italian sausage or diced chicken. My husband asked for crumbled pancetta in it next time. Keeper recipe for sure.

name: peanut butter marshmallow pie
review: Froze it overnight. Fantastic!

name: unbelievable pumpkin fudge brownies
review: I used Ghiradelli double chocolate brownie mix, and added a teaspoon of pumpkin pie spice. These were good, very dense, although the peanut butter was kind of funky. Maybe because I used natural peanut butter, it got clumpy and dry on top. But it tasted good!

name: peanut butter pumpkin cookies
review: These were really cute and so easy! My kids had a blast helping to make them, and everyone loved eating them.

name: kentucky derby dessert
review: AMAZING! Followed the recipe exactly. Best pie I've had in a long time. Definitely making this again.

name: turducken roulade
review: Oh my gosh, this is AMAZING! I just used cornbread and wild rice, and sprinkled each layer with creole seasoning. Everyone loved it!

name: best broccoli salad
review: I left out the bacon and used light mayo and it was still delicious!

name: swiss chard and turkey au gratin
review: Very easy and tasty. I used kale instead of chard since I have it growing in my garden.

name: baked brie with mango chutney
review: This is amazing! Used an Indian ginger mango chutney and marcona almonds. Great with crackers too.

name: herb crusted chicken bites
review: Great flavor, really easy.

name: kims bite size sandwiches
review: These were good. We did turkey and cheddar. Really easy.

name: mushroom puffs
review: These are amazing! I added blue cheese which was a great addition.

name: chicken tahini salad with pine nuts on mini pita rounds
review: This was good but needs a bit more seasoning than written. I used bagel chips instead of mini pitas since I couldn't find mini pitas.

name: garlic tomatoes   for the tapas bar
review: Very good. I halved the recipe and used rosemary instead of thyme.

name: shrimp wonton cups
review: These were quite tasty. Used round wrappers instead of square.

name: asparagus with prosciutto
review: These are SO good!

name: simple corn casserole
review: This was wonderful and sweet. Our kids called it corn cake!

name: apple  gouda and turkey wrap with bacon
review: This wrap made a very tasty, light, and healthy lunch. I really loved the salty/ sweet combination of the apple and bacon. I used a garden spinach herb tortilla, honey roasted turkey, gala apple and spring mix for the baby greens. Loved it! Thank you for sharing. **Made for 2016 Football Pool**

name: olive pesto bread
review: This is wonderful! We did half black olives and half kalamata. The raw garlic is pretty strong but once you roast it in the oven to melt the cheese, it mellows the flavor. Definitely going to become a regular tapas menu item for us!

name: garlicky parmesan bread dip
review: We really like this recipe! I used 1/2 teaspoon of garlic powder. We love how versatile it is. We like to eat it cold with veggies, or hot with bread or crackers.

name: vanilla coffee creamer
review: This turned out well. I used vanilla powder instead of extract so no clumping issues.

name: cheddar shrimp nachos
review: Perfect! The recipe didn't say to chop the shrimp, but we did, into about 3 pieces per shrimp. It was SO delicious! The kids loved them too.

name: bacon crescents
review: Really good and really easy. We re-hydrated dried onion for a softer smaller texture.

name: chilean empanadas
review: Made exactly as written. Good, tasty, a little different, a hit. Needed to cook for longer than indicated in recipe.

name: cucumber  pomegranate and goat cheese appetizers
review: These are amazing! I used a baguette and added a sprinkling of salt and fresh ground pepper.

name: southern greens with a kick
review: This was SO good! I thought I didn't like Southern greens until I tried this recipe. Fantastic flavor. I used kale from my garden.

name: easy stove top macaroni   cheese
review: I deviated from my regular homemade mac and cheese recipe to try this, and it didn't turn out well for me. I tripled the recipe because I have a large family, and maybe that created an issue. I purchased a higher grade sharp cheddar, and it didn't melt into a smooth consistency. If I were to make this again, I was try a sharp American or another cheese that melts better.

name: oatmeal   banana pancakes with pomegranate syrup
review: These were wonderful! I made them as written, just added some pomegranate seeds sprinkled on top because they're so pretty. Really special breakfast.

name: chicken enchilada ring
review: AMAZING!!! I used taco seasoning in place of the Pampered Chef seasoning.

name: easy  delicious   low carb taco soup
review: My husband is on a very strict low carb diet & he misses soups. This recipe hit the spot for him! I cut the recipe in half, used my own taco seasoning for the spices, had to leave out the onion AND cream cheese due to his diet restrictions--and used low sodium chicken broth. I let it simmer for a good 10-15 minutes. he really enjoyed it; thanks so much!

name: ham  cheese and mushroom turnovers
review: Very good!

name: breakfast egg rolls
review: These were SO good! Made them as written and served with a bowl of salsa for dipping. A huge hit at the party.

name: ruth s white bean and ham soup
review: Made as written, good soup. Next time I'll add a couple garlic cloves and maybe some thyme or rosemary.

name: marvelous leftover hash
review: I had a lot of trouble getting it to stick together without burning, even cooking it on low. Maybe I should have used extra oil as well.

name: crockpot ham  simple
review: This is super easy and really tasty. I actually used a pressure cooker instead of the slow cooker setting and it was done in under an hour. Love it!

name: honey mustard sprouts
review: Really good, simple recipe. I sprinkled with additional dill to serve.

name: holiday leftovers pot pie
review: I liked it. Definitely had to cook longer. Nice creative use for holiday leftovers.

name: ham and cheese frittata
review: Tasty and easy. I added a little fresh thyme as well.

name: merry mountain trail mix
review: This was good, more like a granola.

name: spicy healthy taco bean soup
review: What a wonderful recipe! I had to change it up since it would have made too much--I left out the northern beans & diced tomatoes. I used mild Rotel, low sodium pinto beans & my own taco seasoning. It was a delicious recipe & came together so easily. Thank you so much for sharing!

name: slow cooker beef bourguignon
review: This was good. I used fresh thyme and bay leaf and added garlic powder to the beef flour coating. I also added additional salt when it was done cooking. That's probably what was needed for the commenters who have said it tastes bland. I used a really good cab for the wine. I actually made it in the pressure cooker and love that it was done in under an hour with the texture of slow cooking.

name: couscous and pomegranate salad
review: Delicious and beautiful! I didn't want to hunt down harissa for just one recipe so I made a similar paste with sriracha, cumin, garlic powder, caraway and coriander. Great spark of heat with the sweet apricots and tart pomegranate seeds.

name: crockpot sliced cranberry pork roast
review: This is such a simple and flavorful pork roast. I subbed brown sugar for white and pomegranate juice for cranberry juice since those were what I had on hand. I also cooked it for 30 minutes in my Instantpot on the meat setting. Moist, tender, and so delicious!

name: mediterranean chickpea latkes
review: These are amazing! I didn't find them salty, maybe that's from the brand of chickpeas? It is definitely a milk flavor with a wonderful hint of rosemary that kicks in after you swallow. I topped them with sour cream, pomegranate seeds and fresh mint.

name: tarragon chicken casserole
review: This is AMAZING! I think I will try including some vegetables in the dish next time I make it.

name: warm chicken and white bean salad  diabetic
review: Really unique and tasty. I recommend leaving the garlic in. I also used fresh red peppers and green beans.

name: gingerbread coffee
review: Very good flavor.

name: asian style chicken salad
review: Holy moly! Best salad I've had in a long time. SO much flavor!

name: gingerbread cake  spicy
review: WOW! That's the first thing and everyone who's tried this gingerbread has said after taking a bite. Wonderful complex flavor, fantastic texture. I could seriously eat the whole cake!

name: weight watcher easy cheesy eggplant casserole  3 ww points
review: I loved this recipe!!! My first time trying eggplant. I read instructions on how to cut an eggplant but did anyone try peeling it beforehand?? I had to peel off the outer edge before eating the dish but perhaps that's a personal thing. I used low fat ricotta instead of cottage cheese,& added spices to jarred spaghetti sauce. I did have a small serving of whole wheat spaghetti with it the next day but it reheated wonderfully. Thanks so much for sharing!

name: sweet cottage cheese latkes
review: These are tasty. The lemon zest makes them wonderful!

name: panera bread s bistro steak salad
review: Good and easy. Used a soy marinated flank steak.

name: green   yellow squash  linguini  w  shrimp scampi
review: So great! I used a spiralizer and it made it really fast to make the noodles.

name: roasted sausages  peppers  potatoes  and onions
review: True comfort food! I used sweet Italian turkey sausage and red potatoes. I just roasted everything together for about an hour and it turned out beautifully. So tasty! I will definitely be making this again!

name: bacon wrapped garlic asparagus bundles
review: I added extra garlic to this, as I do with every recipe because we love it. Everything else stayed the same. My bacon needed to cook longer than the stated time. My family would have liked the bacon even more crisp, but the asparagus would have been over done if I left it in any longer.

name: soft peanut butter cookies
review: I love this recipe! Delicious cookies. I added peanut butter and milk chocolate chips to the 2nd half of the batch. Otherwise followed the recipe exactly. Thank you for sharing. I will make these again!

name: hot chocolate float
review: SO good! Dinner and dessert in one!

name: potato croquettes deep fried
review: This is a good base to play with. I made as written this time. I think it would be good with leftover mashed potatoes, and actually mix the green onions or chives into the potatoes.

name: moscow hot chocolate
review: AMAZING! My new favorite hot cocktail.

name: st  louis style toasted ravioli
review: Never had toasted ravioli before. Love that I can freeze them and reheat for a last minute company appetizer. These are so good.

name: crock pot spinach stuffed pasta shells
review: This was only okay for us. I tried adding some fresh chopped bail which helped a little. I usually make my own red sauce so it probably just wasn't flavorful enough. I'd try it again with homemade sauce and more cheese on top.

name: red wine crock pot roast
review: Too much wine flavor without much else. Needed some garlic and herbs to balance it out.

name: crock pot shrimp and artichoke dip or crab and artichoke dip
review: I really liked this. I used crab AND shrimp, with double the amount of crab. Gave it a great seafood flavor.

name: crock pot lamb shanks
review: Really good recipe. Browned in my Instantpot and lamb chops instead of shanks. Great flavor, wonderful over mashed potatoes.

name: castillian hot chocolate
review: Amazing rich sipping chocolate. Really good with a splash of Amaretto too!

name: crock pot honey ham  oamc
review: Good and easy. I used a pre sliced ham, cut end down.

name: ww  2 points   caramel apple salad
review: This is SO good! I used 1/2 a package of a small butterscotch pudding. And I mixed it right into the cool whip and then layered it with the apple and pineapple to make more of a trifle. It made a pretty dessert.

name: chocolate fudge brownies
review: Super chocolatey. Love it!

name: chocolate chip cookie baked oatmeal
review: Quite good. Definitely more baked oatmeal than chocolate chip cookie, but wonderful flavor. I used a whole egg instead of the Egg Beaters.

name: diabetic best ever low fat baked chicken
review: Really good chicken. I used spray olive oil instead of the margarine, and Italian breadcrumbs in place of the herbs. This is a great recipe to switch up spices or herbs for different flavors.

name: heart shaped dried cherry and chocolate chip scones
review: Wonderful! Best scone recipe I've tried.

name: berry crisp   weight watchers core recipe
review: We liked the recipe, but it's definitely not amazing. It's really more of a baked oatmeal than a crisp. The top got a bit crunchy, but was still chewy too. I was fine with the texture but it won't be crisp-like without a fat like butter or oil. I also only used about 1/2 cup of yogurt after reading the reviews, and just a couple tablespoons of the pudding mix. The flavor was good to us.

name: the best crock pot barbecue ribs
review: The sauce was a little thin, but they had good flavor. Even my husband who really doesn't like ribs had a second helping.

name: chicken tortellini soup with mushrooms and spinach
review: Used a bunch of Italian seasoning and some salt and pepper in place of the Mrs. Dash.

name: apple crumble  gluten  dairy and egg free
review: I used coconut oil, and flaked coconut. Pretty good.

name: sweet potato  yam  casserole with marshmallows
review: This turned out really well, but I had to make a couple of changes for it to turn out. I used 2 29 oz cans of yams (total of 58 oz) but the same amount of all the other ingredients. Except marshmallows. I had a 10.5 oz bag but really only used about half of it. I truly have no idea how you could cram a full 16 oz of marshmallows in this. I used a 2 qt square pan. The flavor and level of sweetness was perfect with these changes. I have never made this dish myself before so thank you for posting. I think that having a center layer of marshmallows is unique based on others I have tasted. It worked really well and I would do it again.

name: moist and tender turkey  or turkey breast
review: Here's another testamonial to this being the most moist turkey I have ever had. I was drawn to this recipe due to its simple ingredients and rave reviews. How could a turkey breast that only has butter, chicken broth and mayonnaise and isn't brined be really good? I followed the instructions and also doubled up on the gravy ingredients, as suggested. I deleted all of my other roast turkey recipes because this is the only one I'll use from now on.

name: gingerbread
review: I loved this recipe!! For a household of two (sometimes one, if my spouse is cutting down on carbs), these 2 mini loaves fit the bill. I followed the recipe exactly except I used 3/4 tsp cinnamon & 1/2 tsp ginger. Was soft & moist & tasted wonderful. I have had problems in the past with gingerbread loaves being a bit dry, lacking moist texture &/or getting stale too fast, so I am hoping none of these problems occur with this gem of a recipe. Wrapping it up tight in plastic & hoping for the best; thanks so much for sharing!

name: red lobster cheddar bay biscuits  copycat
review: Had to leave out the Accent seasoning due to allergies. Other than I followed the recipe. Made eight biscuits that everyone enjoyed.

name: olive mozzarella chicken bake
review: The flavor of this was really good but the dish ended up a bit runny. I didn't flour the chicken so if the flour thickens it that could have been a factor (or just Walmart breasts being full of water). Took a bit over 30 minutes in the oven and I used a thermometer (overcooked a bit through no fault of the recipe or thermometer. I was so brain-dead that when the thermometer beeped I forgot to take the chicken out of the oven.) I used a 24 oz jar of Barilla Tuscan Herb pasta sauce, which the jar says is 2.5 cups. I used a can of mushrooms that was 7 oz (drained weight 4 oz) so I am not sure if that was as much as intended or not. I also added a tiny bit of fresh mushrooms with the onions and garlic. My olives were whole but small so I halved them. I also followed the suggestion of using seasoned salt instead of plain salt.

name: the best browned beef stew ever
review: Very tasty. Keeper recipe

name: dark triple chocolate cake
review: I baked it in round cake pans so I could make a big layer cake for a friend. She wanted a super chocolately cake like one she'd seen in a bakery. The sour cream gives is a great texture. I frosted with a fudge frosting and covered the sides with chocolate I melted, spread really thin, and then cracked into pieces once it was hard.

name: breakfast banana split
review: This was so great! My 2 and 4 year old were super excited to assemble it themselves, and devoured it together. We used plain Greek yogurt.

name: eggs benedict wrap
review: I really wasn't impressed with these. Made them exactly as written and thought the sun dried tomato flavor was too strong, and the hollandaise sauce wasn't very flavorful.

name: southern eggs benedict
review: This was a really lovely dish. I cut the recipe in half as well and topped each with a single jumbo shrimp. I added a sprinkling of chopped parsley. The dish was really wonderful but a couple changes I would make would be to season the grits with some Creole seasoning, and make sure to salt and pepper the poached egg.

name: the realtor s red velvet brownies with white chocolate icing
review: Really good!

name: couldn t be easier slow cooker bread
review: This was super dense and heavy. Also, used a 1 lb coffee can but it was too small for the amount of dough. Maybe with a 3 lb can?

name: chicken  rice  and spices bake
review: Wonderful recipe. Next time I will add salt to the rice, and add in some veggies like peas or broccoli.

name: grilled cheese on the grill
review: Love the smoky flavor from grilling these.

name: omlet casserole in a crock pot
review: Great recipe, really simple. Love that I can adapt this with whatever I want.

name: loaded oatmeal cookies  paula deen
review: I followed the recipe and didn't make any substitutions or variations. My cookies were a flat, greasy mess. I did taste them, and the flavor was good. But, I would be embarrassed to serve them because of what they look like. I didn't bother with the glaze because of how the cookie turned out. I was making these for a cookie swap and needless to say, I won't be taking these.

name: fudge crinkles  a great 4 ingredient cake mix cookie
review: Making cookies for a Christmas party cookie swap tonight. First recipe was a major fail, tasted good but looked horrible. Now I am short on time and still in need of cookies for tonight. So glad I came across this. I had everything on hand. They were quick and easy to throw together and baked up beautifully. They taste good, too! Next time I may try the adjustments that were posted in another review based on a recipe on the side of the cake mix box as my mix was just a tad on the greasy side. Thanks for saving the day!

name: girl scout samoa cookies  copycat
review: These taste really good, but you only need half the amount of topping. I'd also dip the bottoms in chocolate next time as they need more chocolate.

name: healthier mexican chicken casserole
review: Really simple, really good. Topped with fresh cilantro.

name: easy slow cooker chicken dinner
review: This was wonderful. I used one cup of chicken stock and 1/2 cup of white wine. I cooked it in the instant pot for 35 minutes and sauteed it in a little oil in the pot before cooking it.

name: low carb cilantro tortillas
review: I wanted to like these, but the taste was pretty chalky, like protein powder. They also tear really easy and were hard to cook, even after pressing them in a cast iron press. I finally froze my last few and cooked them frozen. But the taste was so unpalatable for me that I had to throw most of them away. I would try this again with a mix of other flours (chickpea, flax, etc).

name: layered mexican salad
review: Good and easy. Made a half batch. Definitely not good for leftovers as it gets soggy.

name: crock pot lentil and sausage soup
review: Wonderful recipe! I made it in the instant pot for 25 minutes on the soup setting. SO good!

name: kid pleaser vegetarian manicotti
review: This recipe was a bit confusing. There didn't seem to be enough filling, and the ingredients say 2 cups divided but the directions say to mix it all together. I did one cup in the filling and one cup in the pan but I think it needed two full cups in the pan. Also, I used 4 cups fresh baby spinach which I don't think was enough once I chopped it up. The ingredients didn't specify fresh, frozen, or 4 cups before or after it's chopped. Giving it three stars because the flavor was still good!

name: crock pot  ham   cauliflower chowder
review: This was incredible! The hot sauce (I used tapatio) really makes the flavor. Only issue is the 3 TBS potato flakes weren't in the ingredients list.

name: copycat olive garden minestrone soup by todd wilbur
review: Wonderful! Huge hit at our house.

name: german chocolate cake with coconut pecan frosting
review: I used a couple deeper cake pans for two layers rather than three. I also drizzled some chocolate ganache and used a little chocolate frosting leftover from another recipe to top it off. Make for a really pretty presentation! Flavor of the cake was pretty good. Not the best I've had, but still good.

name: topsy turvy cake
review: Quite good. Made it in my instant pot on the slow cook setting. Sugars were left out of instructions so I mixed them in the batter and that worked well so I'm going to submit a correction.

name: cow spot cookies
review: Kids love that they have cow spots. Flavor was just okay. Wonder if you could make it with actual milk and white chocolate instead of the melting chocolate.

name: chicken piccata   giada de laurentiis
review: We love lemon juice so liked it tangy. Definitely a family favorite.

name: authentic no refrigeration bakery frosting icing
review: The frosting holds up really well. I definitely prefer the flavor of buttercream, but it was nice to be able to have the Frozen cupcakes I made sit out for hours without worrying about them. I made a half batch and realized it was still way more than I needed, so I bagged up half of it for later, and then colored the rest blue to use on the mini cupcakes.

name: sugar free double layered chocolate pie
review: Thank you so much for this amazing recipe! This was our Christmas dessert :-). I used real sugar for the sugar substitute. I used a 1.5 oz sugar/fat free pudding mix that required 2 cups milk to make it (according the back of the box). So I'm not sure about the box amounts that the recipe asked for! I spread the rest of the whipped cream on top of the cream cheese layer (had about 1/2 the carton left). I also made my own crust. I chilled it for almost 2 days & it doesn't taste low fat/low sugar at all! Thanks again!

name: chocolate toffee graham treats
review: Very rich and delicious. Easy to make. Good with vanilla ice cream. I wish I had tossed some chopped pecans on top. Or added a handful of white chocolate chips for a marbled effect. I think I prefer the version made with saltine crackers though. I missed the saltiness.

name: apple cider vinegar dressing
review: New favorite dressing at our house! Have used it on a salad of mixed greens and orange sections, and also drizzled it on the greens before rolling up a wrap of salmon, cucumber and greens. A versatile dressing - thanks PaulaG!

name: egg muffin sandwich
review: So glad that you posted this here. Great breakfast that we have made for many, many years - Grandpa originally taught the grandkids how to make these. Thanks Devon S.

name: carne de cerdo guisado  browned pork strips
review: This is an outstanding recipe! It is amazing how this simple combination of ingredients could result in such a flavorful dish. I have travelled to the Dominican Republic for work and have enjoyed their cuisine - flavorful without the heat often overly associated with latin american food. Sabroso!! We will make this again. Thank you Chocolatl - you will be missed.

name: santa fe pasta   shrimp
review: I had to make some slight changes to avoid a trip to the store and it still turned out great. Instead of one red bell pepper, I used muticolored sweet Italian peppers, a sweet onion instead of a red pepper, Trader Joe's smashed garlic instead of minced, dried cilantro instead of fresh, Mrs.Dash instead of seasoning salt, fat free half and half and whole wheat angel hair. I wouldn't hesitate to make it this way again. Both DH and I enjoyed it.

name: asparagus and brie open pastry
review: This was pretty good. I'd add more cheese next time.

name: chickpea pot pie
review: Not a fan. The texture was weird with the noodles, and it was pretty flavorless to us.

name: old fashioned beef pot pie
review: This was fantastic! We skipped the cheese and french fried onions on top to keep it a bit lighter. The flavors were wonderful. The whole family loved it!

name: individual chicken pot pies with puff pastry
review: Really good, individual servings were fun.

name: garlic redeye steak marinade
review: I marinated steaks over night using this recipe. My pepper wasn't very hot. While I didn't eat any, my family felt it was okay but didn't have much flavor. If I made this again, I would have to do some tweaking to make it more to my family's tastes.

name: just like loaded baked potatoes casserole
review: I made these for dinner tonight. I didn't make any changes and made the recipe as written. I didn't eat any but my family seemed to enjoy them. They gave them 4 stars.

name: mrs fields authentic  brownie recipe
review: I'm surprised to be the first reviewer of this recipe. I really liked it. I think brownies made with cocoa turn out more chocolatey than brownies made with melted chocolate. Just my experience. I followed the recipe directions very carefully so as to not overmix. For my oven the 32 minutes was a little too long. Next time I will start checking the brownies at about 25 minutes so that they turn out more fudgy than the onces I made today. I have lots of tried and true brownie recipes and now this one will join the list.

name: cuban lobster tails
review: I can't believe I haven't reviewed this yet! I've been using your recipe for a few years now, and whenever DH asks for lobster tails, this is what he's talking about. I don't have an outdoor grill, so I just de-spine the tails and slice them down the middle so I can flatten them out a bit for more even cooking, and then I grill them on my Cuisinart tabletop grill. They're spicy, but the orange and chipotle is fabulous in this! This is actually what's on the menu for our NYE dinner tonight. Thanks for posting, and sorry for not remembering to post a review until now!

name: italian seasoning   old sub sailor
review: Flavorful blend that made great use of the herbs and spices already in my pantry. So glad to run across this gem of a recipe! Thanks Chia!

name: weight watchers vanilla pound cake
review: This is AMAZING!!! I cut the recipe in half to make 2 mini loaves (baked for 25 min). I used 2 egg whites, not three but cut everything else in half. It was so very good and I especially loved the almond extract flavor. I made some chocolate frosting to go on top. Thank you so much for sharing!!!

name: coffee and soy sauce roast beef
review: I made this for dinner tonight. I followed the recipe and didn't make any substitutions or alterations. I added baby carrots the last 45 minutes of cook time. DH said the carrots were ok, but not to make them again. No one liked the gravy. But, everyone liked the beef. If I make this again, I will just serve the beef, forget the gravy and make separate sides.

name: baked red velvet donuts
review: I thought these were a little dry, but I may have overmixed them. Flavor was great! I used the icing and topped with some sprinkles. Icing ingredients are not listed in the ingredients section so make sure you have those on hand!

name: pizza pot pie
review: Really a casserole, not pot pie. Used a different pasta style and fresh mozzarella. Pretty tasty.

name: crab cakes with chardonnay cream sauce
review: The crab cakes themselves were just okay. I had to add another egg to keep them together. But the cream sauce was wonderful!

name: curd rice
review: This was so good! I ordered all the seasonings from Amazon since I've never used them before. I wish there were a few more specific instructions. Not sure how much salt and sugar to used because I didn't know how it is supposed to taste. So I used 1 teaspoon of salt and two of sugar. I also wasn't sure if the seasonings were supposed to be fried on high, so I did medium high heat. I used Greek yogurt, and basamati rice, and ended up using 4 cups of rice since I had extra and wanted it less soupy.

name: tex  mex pot pie
review: This was fantastic! I used only 1/4 cup of cheddar to make it a bit healthier. The whole family loved it.

name: cheesy jalapeno corn casserole  slow cooker
review: Very sweet, but good.

name: best israeli hummus
review: Topped with paprika, dill, and parsley. So perfect for an easy dinner spread with pita, carrot sticks, olives, and feta.

name: triple chocolate cookies
review: My friend recommended this recipe to me after he had made them 3 times in a weekend. I made the recipe as written except I went very light on the coffee granules. I only used about 1/4 teaspoon of coffee granules. I knew I wanted a very subtle coffee flavor. It worked out well. I baked the cookies for 10 minutes and then let them sit on the baking sheet for about 3 minutes before moving them to a cooling rack. I baked 6 cookies for now and then shaped the rest of the dough into balls and froze them for another time. This is a great cookie.

name: sage pork
review: I made these for dinner tonight and was pleasantly surprised when DH gave them 4 stars. With the minimal ingredients, I really expected him to complain that they didn't have much flavor. But, he said they were good and didn't even reach for the salt and pepper shakers.

name: weight watchers   ice cream  sandwiches del
review: What a wonderful little snack!!! I had to use what I had on hand: low fat cinnamon honey graham crackers, sugar free strawberry jam & whipped cream from the can :-). I think it takes a few hours to freeze so it's good to make them beforehand. Thanks so much!

name: spinach frittata
review: Great combination of flavours, it turned out really well. I didn't bother to precook the spinach, just sauteed with the onion and that worked out fine. I was also a little shy on parmesan cheese, so added more chevre. My cast iron is not the easiest to get something like this out of so I quickly poured out what was in the pan, gave it a wipe and lined with a disc of parchment - the poured everything back in and gave it a stir before putting it in the oven for about 15 minutes (that's how I was able to get the full disc of the fritatta out as you see in my photo). I can slice and wrap up now and have some delicious bagged lunches. This would be a nice party food - will definitely make again.

name: weight watchers easy  tasty frozen pie
review: Oh my this is simply wonderful! I used a low carb banana creme pie yogurt & it was so delicious!!!

name: noodles   herbs
review: First time I made these my family thought they were a little on the bland/dry side. This time I kept the amount of egg noodles the same and simply added a little more butter and heaping measurements of the spices. Much better reviews, four stars!

name: dried apricots with blue cheese
review: I have made this several times and it has been a hit each time. They are easy to make and can be made ahead of time, so no last minute rush. I did not bother toasting the nuts after the first time, and they tasted fine.

name: honey and cheese sandwich
review: We don't use processed cheese, but this was really good with cheddar left over from a sandwich tray.

name: french onion burgers
review: Okay these would totally fall apart on the grill, but worked great in a rimmed baking sheet under the broiler. I think mine didn't fall apart because I didn't chop the mushrooms but left them sliced. They ended up being really flavorful from cooking in their own fat on the sheet pan.

name: weight watchers italian turkey burgers
review: This recipe is AMAZING!!! I did not use the tomatoes or basil; used a whole wheat sandwich thin as well. I scaled the recipe for a 4oz burger (for one person)--used 1/8 tsp onion powder for the onion, 1/8 tsp garlic powder for the garlic powder. I crushed the fennel seeds in a small bag with a rolling pin before adding it to the meat. Put a small slice of cheese on it & served with light mayo. Was so flavorful & delicious; thank you!

name: brings back memories tuna casserole
review: Pretty good. Used organic soup and whole wheat noodles to make it a little healthier.

name: stroganoff
review: Pretty good. I used organic soup, and added some worcestershire and ketchup (1 tablespoon each), then topped with chopped parsley.

name: peanut butter banana toast
review: One of our favorites!

name: crock pot pulled chicken
review: We thought it mostly just tasted like tomato soup. Tried adding some more worcestershire, then a bit of hot sauce and cumin. That helped a bit but we still weren't crazy about it.

name: noodles and tomatoes
review: My hubby's grandma used to make this with her home canned tomatoes. It is mild, tasty comfort food! Thanks Denise for posting - it is a family favorite.

name: amazing buffalo chicken   weight watchers
review: Made these for my husband tonight & they worked out well! He is not on weight watchers so I used regular butter for the butter spread. I had no celery seed so I used salt instead. I added more hot sauce (aka Tabasco sauce), more Worcestershire to give it more kick. I used the oven method & served extra sauce on the side.

name: weight watchers cornmeal pancakes
review: Simply wonderful! I have never had cornmeal pancakes; have always wanted to try them. I cut the recipe down for just 2 pancakes--used whole wheat flour, 1 egg white, sugar free maple syrup for the molasses & added some cinnamon. I might add a little more sugar next time but otherwise they were great!!!

name: springtime grilled salmon
review: Due to rain, we I had bake our salmon in the oven. I baked them in foil packets so they didn't get dried out. The adults really liked it. The kids, not so much. Served with Rosemary Garlic bread and tossed salads

name: pulled pork  crock pot
review: Easy but terrific. Huge hit.

name: eggplant parmigiana   weight watchers
review: This was WONDERFUL! I made some changes but stuck to the recipe as best I could. I salted the eggplant as previous reviewers did to pull out the moisture. I switched the amounts of Parmesan cheese & breadcrumbs (used whole wheat) & added some oregano. I got 8 slices out of my eggplant so I was only able to do 2 layers. I didn't use egg whites; just nonstick cooking spray, used low fat mozzarella, and used spaghetti sauce (not regular tomato sauce). I think baking a little longer would get it heated through better; next time I'll bake for 15-20 min. Served over whole wheat spaghetti. Thanks so much for sharing!!

name: 4 minute spicy garlic shrimp
review: Faster than drive thru or take out and much better too! I served it with a salad and cheddar biscuits. Next time I may try it over angel hair pasta.

name: southwest breakfast casserole
review: We enjoyed this south-of-the-boarder twist of a traditional breakfast casserole. It had great flavor and the corn and beans were a nice addition. The pork chorizo I used was finely ground and did not separate into crumply bits as it cooked as other sausages do, rather into a paste. It lent tremendous flavor to the dish yet did not give the mouth feel of meat. My husband said he could "taste" but not "feel" the sausage. I'll try again with a different brand. Thanks Tammarie,

name: michigan cherry dark chocolate fudge
review: I just used dried cherries, and this was the best fudge I've ever made!

name: smith island ten layer cake
review: The cake looks impressive, but I wasn't crazy about it. The super thin layers end up getting a bit dry, and the frosting was a little strange. I let it cool a bit to thicken up before using it, but then it got too thick by the end. I ended up just making some chocolate ganache to pour over the top.

name: southern living s cream cheese pound cake
review: Amazing! Really moist and wonderful. I even used Gluten free flour and couldn't tell a difference.

name: peanut butter chocolate chip muffins
review: So delicious! I needed to bake mine a bit longer. Thought they were done with a toothpick test, but ended up falling in the center as they started cooling.

name: greek yoghurt and fruit salad
review: Very good. I used raspberries, blueberries, and kiwi for the fruit. Nice light snack!

name: chocolate peanut butter moon pies
review: Not sure if I used too much of the marshmallow cream, or didn't get it thick enough, but I had a lot of trouble with it oozing out of the pies. It was also WAY too sugary for me, though others like them.

name: very berry sugar cookie cobbler
review: Tasted good, but SUPER sweet! I would skip the added sugar next time.

name: peanut butter no bake cookies
review: These are really good but SUPER sweet. I used natural peanut butter. Next time I will cut the sugar in half.

name: baked margarita pie
review: Delicious and easy! I didn't know we were out of margarita mix so used a mix of lemon juice, lime, juice, and simple syrup to make my own.

name: sweet potato pie vi
review: I should have read the review to reduce the amount of sugar. But good flavor.

name: cauliflower rice   low carb
review: SO easy!

name: strawberry jello fluff dessert
review: SUPER sweet but tasty.

name: my favorite chimichanga
review: These were fantastic! I did the baking method and loved how they turned out.

name: oreo cookie brownies
review: Really fun way to make brownies

name: skylike chili   skyline chili copycat
review: Delicious! One of my favorite variations on copycat Skyline Chili! I used a 28 oz can of tomato puree instead of the sauce it called for, and Certified Angus Beef ground beef .... absolutely delish! The second time I made it, I substituted one 14.5 oz. petite diced tomatoes, and one 6 oz. can Cento tomato paste. I made up for the loss of the additional liquid by adding more broth.

name: pan fried trout
review: I used my herb seasoning salt before the corn meal, and made it in the oven on broil. So delicious!

name: pumpkin pie bread
review: It's good but very sweet. I made it in one large pan.

name: delicious crock pot barbecued pulled pork
review: So easy to make. I felt bad for leaving my dog home all day while delicious, mouth watering smells filled my house. But I loved having dinner ready when I got home. Just popped the beans and some biscuits in the oven and everything was done.

name: roasted beets with honey balsamic glaze
review: Really enjoyed this simple recipe; i did use maple syrup instead of honey.

name: crock pot chicken with black beans   cream cheese
review: Really tasty. I used an Instant Pot and pressure cooked it on the meat setting for 35 minutes. No problem using frozen meat that way since it heats up so quickly. I mashed it a bit before serving to smash up the chicken.

name: oven roasted hot dogs
review: Nice way to bulk cook hot dogs with great texture.

name: easter bunny cupcakes
review: This was such a cute idea! I used candy eyes, a pink skittle, and colored the split marshmallows with a pink food coloring marker. I also used a homemade lemon buttercream instead of canned frosting.

name: chipotle deviled eggs
review: These were really good but definitely needed salt. I should have tasted the filling before piping it into the whites. But it worked great to have some fleur de sel on the tray for people to sprinkle on the eggs themselves. Or you could give a quick sprinkle of salt over them all before serving.

name: tons of blueberry coffee cake
review: Great recipe and a keeper. I used frozen blueberries that I rolled in flour. I put half my batter in pan spread the blueberries covered with remaining batter and add topping. Don't worry; the batter is very thick, but comes out just perfect.

name: thanksgiving stuffing  cheat  using stove top
review: We all agreed that two onions was way too much. Next time I would only use one. Otherwise, we enjoyed it.

name: peanut butter blossoms
review: One of our favorite cookies to make. They are always a big hit. It you don't have creamy peanut butter, don't worry. We used crunchy and they turned out fine. We used Nestle Crunch bells left over from Christmas. We have also used the Hershey hugs and kisses, as well as miniature peanut butter cups. They all turned out great.

name: quinoa stuffed acorn squash
review: SO good! I added a drizzle of white balsamic vinegar to give some brightness and enhance the flavors in the quinoa.

name: pork chops with ginger pear sauce
review: Made as written. Incredible flavor! Served it with baby kale salad the first day, but heated the baby kale in the sauce for leftovers and that was great too!

name: cinnamon apple popcorn
review: Good flavor but I think I will double the cinnamon butter mix next time. Also the apples get a bit hard so I would dry them less next time.

name: spicy skillet pork chops
review: Spicy but good.

name: amazing nacho dip for a crowd
review: SO good! Love the gooey melty version of a seven layer dip.

name: italian stuffed artichokes
review: Good but needed a few tweaks. I rubbed a cut lemon on the artichoke after prepping it which helps with flavor and keeping it from browning before it cooks. I also added lemon zest and used fresh garlic in the stuffing. Then I put a sliced lemon, some parsley, and garlic cloves in the water in the pan to give some aromatics to the steam.

name: southwest spaghetti squash
review: The flavor was good but the texture was tough. Next time I will drain the tomatoes. I will also drain the spaghetti squash strands in a colander after cooking them. There was just way to much liquid and it made for a mushy texture.

name: roasted garlic cheese spread
review: AMAZING!

name: garlic lovin  salmon
review: I liked how quick and easy this was to make and it tasted pretty good too. However, the kiddo wasn't impressed.

name: fruity pebbles parfait
review: This was really fun. Great way to put a healthier spin on a sugary cereal. My kids loved it!

name: peachy salsa chicken
review: I made this using beyond meat grilled chicken strips, Trader Joe's Fall Harvest Salsa, and Marcy Jams! Spiced Peach jam. The result was wonderful. Both DH and I enjoyed the blend of sweet and spicy. I served it with brown rice and steamed broccoli on the side.

name: fruit loop waffles
review: Wouldn't want to make these on a regular basis, but very fun for a once in a while treat and a nice twist on waffles.

name: breakfast cereal popsicles
review: I didn't really like these, but my kids sure did!

name: milk   cereal smoothies
review: Not crazy about this. My kids liked it though.

name: mom s cheat doughnuts
review: SUCH a great idea! Super easy and fun to make. We topped ours with cereals.

name: cowboy breakfast casserole
review: I REALLY liked how this basically turned into a pan of breakfast sandwiches I could slice apart. Great for fast and easy breakfasts for the week! Also, I cut the crusts off the bread.

name: crockpot dijon chicken
review: We are a house divided on this recipe. My family members either thought it was really good or they didn't like it at all. The chicken was really tender and it was easy to put together.

name: grilled lobster
review: Perfect! Made it just as written. Worth the $60 for two lobsters!

name: taqueria style tacos   carne asada
review: Best carne asada I've made!!!

name: quiche aux asperges et saumon  asparagus   salmon quiche
review: Lovely recipe. I used sour cream instead of creme fraiche and it was still quite good.

name: wonderful parmesan zucchini strips
review: So good!

name: romany creams
review: I haven't filled the cookies yet, for the time being I'm just "tasting" them plain. They are crisp, coconutty cookies with a light chocolate flavor. My yield for this recipe was 87 single cookies (10 grams each.) The recipe was very clear and easy to follow. I did use unsweetened shredded coconut, which I minced a little with the food processor. Other than that, I made no changes. Thank you very much for sharing this recipe with us.

name: the simplest  tastiest crockpot chicken recipe
review: I used fresh sliced mushrooms instead of canned. We were surprised that this didn't have more flavor to it. Next time I will play with some spices and add some kind of seasoning. It wasn't awful, just on the bland side.

name: sweet bacon wrapped venison tenderloin
review: We hadn't had venison in years. A dear friend gave us some so I was looking for ways to make it. Anything with bacon in the name sounds good to DD. So the outcome surprised me. DH really liked it, but DD didn't care for it at all. I didn't eat any, but as far as the cooking goes, it was fairly simple to make with only a few ingredients. I lined the pan under the rack with foil, so clean up was fairly easy.

name: candy cane chocolate chunk cookies
review: I was glad to come across this because I needed a recipe to use up some candy canes. However, I should have read all the reviews before making these. If I had seen Marg's review, I would have known to use non stick foil when baking. The melted candy cane pieces stuck to the pan and the cookie texture is somewhat delicate and crumbled trying to get them off the pan. I think I may like these better in a more chewy, less cake like dough. Next time I may alter the dough or at least bake on parchment or pan lined with non- stick foil.

name: vanilla nut granola
review: This was wonderful.
