I lost my original granola recipe (found it finally) but I ended up combining a few elements to make my own version: I added 2 tbsp honey & upped the cinnamon to 1 tsp (next time I might do 1 1/2 tsp) I used sliced almonds for the pecans & really appreciated the applesauce element & the lower amount of butter. I only had sugar free maple syrup in the fridge; I might sub more honey for that next time. Baking time varied for me; I finally upped my oven to 325 b/c it was taking too long! At first I thought it wasn't sweet enough but as it cooled it started to sweeten up more. A lovely recipe!

name: linda s tacos ole
review: This was a great way to liven up tacos. I used my own taco seasoning mix & had only jarred jalepenos in the fridge so I added a few of those. Loved the ease of the recipe as well; came together in no time. Thanks so much for sharing!

name: sunny s lemon curry chicken
review: Super delicious! I prepared the sauce as described. I used skinless chicken legs, and I coated them with egg and breadcrumbs (as we don't corn flakes for breakfast) and I mixed the remaining egg with breadcrumbs and I pressed this over the legs. As a light crust was formed I turned the chicken and I brushed it with the sauce. It turned out crunchy and super tasty. Next time I will double the the sauce fir more liquid. Thanks a lot for this amazing recipe!

name: venison  or beef   mushroom stroganoff
review: DD didn't care for this at all. Ended up eating just the egg noodles with butter, salt and pepper. DH however, really likes it and said he would give it 4 stars. It is definitely a weekend meal. As I look at the mess in my kitchen and consider how long it takes to make, there is no way I could have done this on a week night. But, it takes time to do it right, or else you would have venison so tough it'd be hard to eat. So fast and tough or slow and tender, you choose.

name: old fashioned rice custard
review: This is a wonderful recipe! I used brown rice because that's what I had on hand. I also added 1 tsp cinnamon - my G'mas influence I'm sure. And since I had no raisins I used craisins. Delicious! Thank you for posting!

name: maui ahi poke
review: An excellent recipe. First time to re-create the different pokes in Hawaii. This recipe pretty well nailed it. I followed the recipe exactly, even had the Hawaiian sea salt on hand. I will make this again, but will only use a pinch of salt and then adjust the taste in the finished dish. Thank you so much for sharing this delightful recipe.

name: traditional irish coffee
review: Using quality Irish whiskey really improves this drink. An excellent hot toddy anytime, but a must for St. Patrick's Day.

name: black bean   corn tacos with radish salsa   feta
review: These were amazing!!!

name: roasted beet pasta
review: This was so fun! First time using my pasta rollers for my mixer. I had to add a lot more flour to get a dough that wasn't too sticky to roll, but the kneading and resting definitely led to a nice light dough. I tossed the cooked pasta with some melted butter, parmesan, parsley, and lemon zest. Such a lovely spring pasta!

name: morel risotto
review: This was pretty good, but I really felt like the heavy morel taste needed some acidity to balance it out. Maybe a little lemon juice and zest. I would try it again with those added. This may also be because I had to rehydrate dried morels as I can't get fresh ones in my area.

name: venison steak marinade
review: It's not very often I find a recipe that we all agree on. But this one fit the bill. I used 3 teaspoons of minced garlic. We love our garlic and I always double what the recipe calls for. Glad I did, because for us, it was perfect!

name: spinach ricotta pie with a hint of feta
review: This is really terrific. I made half the recipe, but have made it a few times. I lined my 8x8 baking pan with parchment paper - no need to grease the pan, plus the paper absorbs any residual moisture from the spinach. I did use frozen chopped spinach, such a great timesaver. Once I added chopped green onion tops to the cheese mix, which worked well. Last time I omitted the oregano and added a big handful of chopped fresh dill - this ende d being my favorite version thus far. A very nice addition to Lenten menus. It would also work well as a side.

name: spicy red bean   rice
review: This is my favorite lunchtime entrée. I use a 1-lb. bag of small red beans, soaked with salt for 8 hours, then pressure cook them as Cuban Black beans with a ham hock. I drain off the liquid and use the cooked beans instead of the canned kidney beans called for in this recipe. Meanwhile, I will have already prepared 2 cups brown rice with its soaking and rinsing, then pressure cooking that. I prefer my rice to be separate from the beans for contrast. I let the resulting Spicy Bean mix cool. I pull out a stack of 1.25-cup Rubbermaid containers, put 1/2 cup of cooked rice in each container, then one ladleful of Spicy Beans on top. I put the lid on and freeze my individual portions. As a result, I could take a container from the freezer and let it thaw until lunch, and warm it up in the microwave. I usually had this with a garden salad. Very satisfying, and spicy enough to be interesting.

name: chicken broccoli alfredo soup
review: When I ran across this recipe, I thought it sounded like something my family would love. Being on a "lower fat" diet, there was no way I could make it as written though. I was really pleased with how well the recipe modified to meet my dietary needs. It was still rich and delicious, and everyone loved it. Here is my lightened up version: http://www.food.com/recipe/light-chicken-broccoli-alfredo-soup-lower-fat-393857 Served with http://www.food.com/recipe/italian-herb-parmesan-bread-bread-machine-abm-346173

name: crispy barbecue onions
review: I will make these again. Great flavor. I made a half batch of the flour seasoning. There was still way too much leftover flour seasoning. Next time I'll make a 1/4th batch of the flour seasoning and that should be enough to coat the onions without having leftover flour.

name: the perfect roast chicken with garlic and sun dried tomatoes
review: I'm always on the look out for a beautiful roast chicken recipe. I'm really happy with the results of this recipe. The sun-dried tomatoes intrigued me. The ones I purchased were in a jar and were marinated. So the fragrant oil from the sun-dried tomatoes flavored the chicken also. I love the idea of a sprinkling of sugar on the skin. It makes the skin crispy and gives it a pretty golden color.

name: chicken with tomatoes  olives and fennel
review: In the memory of SarasotaCook. This is an excellent midweek recipe, it was so quick and easy and very delicious. Thank you Kim

name: quick  easy and spicy sausage gravy over grits or biscuits
review: This recipe was made on 4/5/17 in memory of Sarasota Cook,Kchurchill5,or Kim. I did have to make a sub on the cheese,mild cheddar was used. And to cut back the heat level a bit, I only used 2 ounces of the chilis. And it was served over canned biscuits. Thanks for a great recipe Kim. :) RIP Kim " Keep Smiling :) "

name: grilled venison packets
review: Everyone in my family gave these between 3 and 4 stars. The one comment I kept getting was the venison didn't have as much flavor as the mushrooms. Next time I will probably add steak seasoning directly to the venison before adding the butter, onions, mushrooms and final steak seasoning. Love how quick this was to put together and clean up was a breeze.

name: how to make ice cream in a bag  no cooking  no ice cream machine
review: We had SO much fun making this on a sick day! The kids loved wearing their mittens and shaking it up.

name: fantastic marinade for grilled shrimp
review: This marinade is incredible! I actually like it even more as a sauce. I will be making it again to use as a sauce for chicken, beef, seafood. SO good!

name: caribbean grilled burger with pineapple sauce
review: These are delicious! Needed some salt in the burger and the pineapple sauce. I also added a bit of apple cider vinegar to the pineapple sauce. Slathered some mayo on the bun. Delicious with a hint of spice, and the kids loved them too!

name: crock pot chili dogs
review: Thought it was okay.

name: smoked whole brisket with burnt ends
review: We had a small brisket so only used about 1/3 of the rub. Great flavor! I skipped burning the ends since we don't really like it burnt.

name: bananas  n cream bundt cake
review: When I made this I used 3/4 reduced fat sour cream and 1/4 vanilla greek yogurt, because I didn't have enough of either one to make a full cup. While I didn't eat any of this, I did make it and take it to work. The ladies really enjoyed it. I wouldn't hesitate to make it again.

name: austin s hyde park bar   grill mac and cheese
review: This has excellent flavor, but it was really, really hard to wait for it to cool long enough to thicken to a desirable consistency. We attempted to eat our salad first, but even after letting it cool on the counter for fifteen minutes, popping it in the oven to let the top cheese melt, and then plating it to allow it to cool in a smaller consistency, we still felt like we were eating mac & cheese soup. I must say, patience is a virtue, because as I was putting the rest in the refrigerator an hour later - it was a perfect consistency. This would be great for a buffet, where it will hold up over a longer period of time for sure and for people with a LOT of patience.

name: soft homemade flour tortillas
review: LOVE THESE! My sister got me hooked on these, they are sooooo much better than storebought! Crazy good and crazy easy to make. I like to leave them in little balls in a tupperware in the fridge, then roll them out as needed.

name: weight watchers juicy hamburgers
review: Good and simple

name: crab stuffed cherry tomatoes
review: Very time intensive, but impressive presentation and tasty. I added a small sprig of basil on top of each one.

name: basil shrimp with feta and orzo
review: Absolutely delicious!!!

name: the roast beef po boy  and how to make any po boy
review: SO good!!!

name: grilled scallops and mushrooms in foil packets
review: Really delicious! I used fresh ground pepper, lemon juice, and lemon zest in place of the lemon pepper.

name: fabulous frozen green beans
review: It started off wonderfully, until I opened the bag of beans and poured it in. The condensation from the steam poured into the pan as well and turned my nice toasty breadcrumbs to mush. Still tasted ok, but next time I will know better.

name: easy venison steaks
review: I made this using a store version of Mrs. Dash. Let it cook 6 minutes, flipped it and let it cook another 5. At this point it was medium, which is how I would have liked it. But my husband doesn't like any pink so he put it back on for a couple more minutes.

name: cajun chicken thighs
review: My husband really liked these. Not hot, but still had a very good flavor to them.

name: green beans with lemon herb butter
review: I used fresh green beans from the market. Used my steamer to cook them and then tossed them in the pan with the melted butter and seasonings. They were a wonderful side to our grilled chicken.

name: baked italian potato wedges
review: Thanks for this amazing recipe. I used grated parmesan cheese, messed with the spices a bit (kind of eyeballed it) for two potatoes. Roasted wonderfully for 35 min. Thank you for sharing!

name: grilled cauliflower
review: I made this for my family for dinner tonight. Their reviews weren't what I expected. My husband, who really likes cauliflower, just thought it was just okay. My daughter, who typically isn't a huge fan of cauliflower, loved it. And the remaining could give or take it.

name: marinated boneless venison loin
review: I made this with venison loin given to us by a friend. I didn't change anything but would recommend marinating longer than two hours. My family said it didn't have as much flavor as they would have liked and was a little tough. Longer marinade time might help these issues.

name: rainbow layer cake
review: SO stunning! We had an unbirthday party and did a little photoshoot with the kids devouring their cake. It was super fun. Taking the rest to a get together tomorrow night.

name: pork machaca  tender pulled mexican pork
review: AMAZING! Seriously awesome taco meat! I didn't have chicken boullion so I just added a tablespoon of salt. Still had great flavor.

name: green   yellow squash  linguini  w  shrimp scampi
review: I made this for dinner tonight using 3 zucchini and 3 summer squash. I had just over a pound of fresh shrimp, so I threw it all in. I only had red wine so I substituted chicken broth for the white wine. I used dried basil and parsley even though I wasn't sure because they recipe didn't specify dried or fresh. The flavor was good, but it had a little more heat than I had wanted. Next time I will go easier on the red pepper flakes.

name: red lobster garlic cheese biscuits
review: I didn't have self rising flower so I used all purpose flour and added a tablespoon of baking powder and a teaspoon of salt. I also opted to use the Crisco. Dropping them by heaping tablespoon full, I only got 10 biscuits. Not the 20 as stated in the recipe. Luckily, we didn't have any dinner guests, so it was plenty for our family. I didn't grease the pan and they still turned out great. No problems sticking at all and they were pretty tasty to boot!

name: peppers and steak for crock pot
review: Simple and good. I was confused by the cup of beef boullion. Was that supposed to be stock? I used a tablespoon of Better than Boullion. We were okay with the soft peppers.

name: the best peanut butter oatmeal cookies
review: This is a great recipe! The cookies turned out perfectly. The only change I made was to substitute coconut oil for the shortening. Otherwise made as directed. Yummy!

name: crock pot tropical apple crisp
review: Good, especially with homemade ice cream!

name: coconut chicken curry   crock pot
review: Easy to make. Much better with double the curry powder and drizzling with sriracha sauce after serving.

name: cajun shrimp burger
review: Pretty good, SUPER messy! Not as spicy as we were expecting. I'd definitely kick the spice up next time.

name: montreal steak
review: Really good! I cooked it sous vide, and then seared it on a grill pan.

name: 15 minute shrimp scampi
review: This was good. I used frozen shrimp, and they cooked up quickly. I also added lemon juice and parsley.

name: bacon wrapped grilled chicken sandwich
review: AMAZING! Really wonderful.

name: down east corn chowder  crock pot
review: Simple and good. I didn't have mace so used nutmeg and some fresh parsley.

name: dolmades
review: SO good! Love the sauce especially.

name: shrimp w spinach   sun dried tomatoes
review: I made this for dinner tonight using fresh baby spinach. Made as written, we all thought it was okay and gave it 3 stars. Except for my daughter, who didn't like it at all. Used a garlic pepper grinder to give it a little more flavor and topped with more fresh shredded Parmesan and upped the stars to 4.

name: tebasaki  japanese style deep fried chicken wings
review: I couldn't get past the fried chicken wings by themselves. Delicious. I WILL try them with the sauce...sometime...but in the meantime the frying technique is a great discovery. 2017--given the number of times I have made these, they deserve 5 stars.

name: teriyaki ranch baked chicken
review: Cheese was a little over done on top, but otherwise it turned out great!

name: creamy avocado lime dip
review: Delicious with shrimp!

name: taco tater tots casserole
review: This is a nice twist on Tater-tot Casserole. It came together quickly and is a great dish. I did make a couple of changes based on the other reviews. I added a can of drained black beans, drained the corn and used regular salsa and a nice big scoop of nacho cheese. My tots were broccoli cheese tots. Delicious! DH is already asking me to make this again! Thanks Mary!

name: lemon rosemary grilled chicken
review: Delicious!

name: amazing peanut butter chocolate chip brownies
review: These really were amazing!!! I used natural peanut butter, used a 13X9 pan & baked for 25 minutes. Simply delicious; thank you so much for sharing!!!

name: cuban sandwich
review: After having a mind blowing Cuban sandwich in a little cafe in Miami, I never thought I could recreate it. But this was incredible! I pressed the sandwich as it grilled on my grill pan so the pork juices smushed out and the sandwich fried up in the juices. AMAZING!

name: spicy stir fried green beans and scallions
review: Good and easy!

name: homemade beef jerky
review: SO spicy but SO good!

name: easy stove top macaroni   cheese
review: Perfect basic mac and cheese. The whole family loves it! We used good quality sharp cheddar and a added the milk slowly to get a perfect roux. I also removed it from the heat to stir the cheese in so it didn't overheat and get gritty.

name: thai turkey burgers with cucumber pepper relish and spicy mayo
review: Whoooooeeeee! That mayo is truly spicy! Good burger. I added some lettuce.

name: perfect jasmine rice  pressure cooker
review: Although I have an electric pressure cooker, I find my 3-quart stovetop Kuhn Rikon pressure cooker to be more convenient for just cooking rice on the side, and the rice is more "perfect" (distinct rice, not mushy). Your measurements were spot on! (Note: I make rice in my electric pressure cooker often, but I don't get as much yield as I do on the stovetop, and the texture is slightly less satisfactory - when I do, I have to change the ratios of rice:water, as well, using the advice on hippressurecooking dot com.) I rinsed (but did not soak) my jasmine rice before cooking. Note: my gas stovetop runs hot, so I switched the rice to a new burner with an extra grate on top, and that maintains the correct pressure much better - I have a high-powered gas stovetop, so I'll live with that adjustment, so I can still wok away when I desire.

name: sarasota s perfect fresh tuna  sliders
review: The black olive sauce is very good...I will use that for tuna salad in the future.

name: peas  pasta and a red pepper vinaigrette salad
review: The vinaigrette is a wonderful recipe in itself that I will make again. I made it in the blender which was very quick and easy, yet much better than store bought dressing. I omitted the honey and didn't miss it at all. Next time I would reduce the amount of shallot in the salad itself. Maybe mine were bigger than most! Very impressive for a potluck or simple summer dining.

name: stir fry sweet and spicy peachy slaw
review: Stir frying a salad? Wasn't sure about the concept but the result was delicious. Took this to a barbecue and got lots of compliments. Great recipe!

name: sarasota s quick shrimp asian salad
review: So light and refreshing...great when you make it and keeps well in the refrigerator. Fresh bean sprouts are a must!

name: authentic italian meatballs
review: Recipe is amazing. I won't toss out my old meatball recipe in case I need meatballs @ a faster rate (I cook mine in the oven), but this will hopefully become my go to! I read a few reviews to help me out. I cut the recipe in half & used 1/2 lean ground turkey & 1/2 chicken Italian sausage. I needed 1/2 cup whole wheat bread crumbs to hold them together. I added Italian seasoning & oregano, and used dried parsely. Recipe made about 14 meatballs, using a cookie scoop I used my own sauce recipe. I seared the meatballs in olive oil, and waited till the sauce was warm (or warm enough!) before dropping the meatballs in! I also tried not to stir for a good 1/2 hour to let the meatballs cook. Amazingly, my sauce was extra tasty as well as the meatballs being very tender & juicy. Thanks so much for sharing!

name: anginetti  italian lemon drop cookies
review: As written, I felt the lemon flavor was way too weak. The cookies were so bland, I used fresh squeezed lemon juice to make the icing and added the zest from one lemon to it as well. That helped a lot, but I wish I had added zest to the dough as well. Very pretty little cookies and popular at the party I took them to.

name: lemon mushroom chicken
review: This is a keeper; thank you sharing this one.

name: sausage gravy
review: While we thought this was good, it did lack in flavor. Next time I will definitely add some seasoning in addition to the pepper.

name: easy crispy cornflake potatoes
review: Love how crispy these are! You really have to get the cornflake crumbs pretty small for them to stick. I ended up pulsing them in my blender. I made a garlic lime aioli to dip it in, so thought the flavor was fine, but it would also be good with seasonings.

name: beef taquitos  oamc
review: SO good!!! I had a can of leftover refried beans to use up, so mixed some of that in as well. LOVE the roast in this.

name: chile sirloin burgers with salsa verde
review: Wonderul burger! The salsa verde has an amazing roasted flavor.

name: chicken and white bean stew
review: LOVE this stew! It's really flavorful and good for hot or cold weather. We enjoyed it cold just as much as hot. I added the juice of one lime to brighten up the flavor a bit.

name: delicious crock pot barbecued pulled pork
review: Very good! Skipped the brown sugar in the sauce as it is already plenty sweet. We ate these on whole wheat buns with an apple cider vinegar broccoli slaw.

name: maple glazed ham steak
review: Made this on the BBQ and it was perfection! Thanks for sharing.

name: orange raspberry chicken
review: Lovely recipe. I added some fresh mint to the finished recipe, and I also used four chicken breasts cut in half since they were so large.

name: moroccan spiced chicken and fennel
review: Wonderful!

name: crispy oatmeal chocolate chip cookies  michael smith
review: Great recipe because it makes a small batch; just what I was looking for. Very good!!! Thanks.

name: red tipped leaf lettuce salad
review: Loved it over spinach. Took your advice and used only the celery salt. Will use this on green salads again - and maybe use valencia or naval oranges. Thanks Big D Texas!

name: our family favourite crock pot chili  oamc
review: Not bad. Very tomato-y. I'm glad I used homemade taco seasoning so I could control the amount of salt. I think it would have been too salty otherwise.

name: cheesecake factory bang bang chicken and shrimp by todd wilbur
review: Wow, that was a lot of work! It was good but don't know that I'd make it again. If I did, I'd definitely use a bit less coconut milk. I was fine with the peanut sauce being thick. I just spooned it on the top.

name: onion parmesan roasted red potatoes
review: I used this homemade onion soup mix: http://www.food.com/recipe/homemade-dry-onion-soup-mix-110331 My oven was at a higher temperature (400 degrees F) because that was the temp my main dish needed to cook at. Even at the higher temp. my potatoes were not quite done and required an additional 10-15 minutes bake time. But they turned out fine and the family liked them.

name: homemade dry onion soup mix
review: Needed onion soup mix for a recipe and used this instead. Worked perfectly!

name: southern buttermilk biscuits
review: Thank you so much for this recipe. My husband said they were the best. I followed the recipe & I thank you for such great directions. I used a large cutter so I only got 5 biscuits but they made good sandwiches. I baked @ 400 for 10 minutes & that was enough--not sure what was up with the difference? But glad I watched them carefully. Thank you again!

name: cinnamon peanut butter brownies
review: These were wonderful. I doubled the recipe & used a 13X9 pan. I think the baking time was about 32-34 min? I used smooth peanut butter & my husband said they were great. thank you!

name: cream cheese sugar cookies
review: These were so, so good!! I followed the recipe (used 1/2 tsp almond extract) and used a big cookie scoop but the baking time was right around 11 min still--interesting! Was a great way to use up some cream cheese, too--thank you for sharing!

name: caramelized baked chicken legs wings
review: This one is keeper; we loved it. I followed other suggestion; bought the heat up to finish it off as well as a tsp of Sambal Oelek. Thanks for sharing.

name: ciabatta bread
review: AMAZING! This was my first time making ciabatta but it won't be the last! I accidentally formed the loaves as rounds instead of ovals as the recipes states. Next time I'll pay more attention! Served it with a high quality Italian olive oil seasoned with a fresh ground pepper medley (4 types of pepper) and Parmesan cheese. I could have made a meal out of it! The air holes were smaller than most ciabatta I've had. I don't know if I handled it too much or it is because of the bread machine mixing it. It didn't compromise the taste though.

name: pinto beans
review: I made these for dinner tonight to serve as a side with our ribs. I didn't make any changes to the recipe and used a high quality bacon. The reviews from my family varied from not liking them at all to saying they were okay but didn't have enough flavor.

name: pan sauted rockfish with capers
review: The flavor wasn't quite there. Thinking maybe it needed some garlic powder seasoning the fish with the salt and pepper.

name: slow cooker chicken  tomato and white bean soup
review: I skipped the bouillon cubes, but otherwise kept the ingredients as written. Use my pressure cooker for 30 minutes and it was delicious!

name: apple butter ribs  crock pot
review: I made these for dinner tonight. I am glad I was home because they were done long before the 9 hour cooking time. The sauce was very greasy, but that is common when using country style ribs. I didn't add the optional liquid smoke. If I make this again I will use it as my family felt they weren't very flavorful.

name: chicken stuffed acorn squash
review: Wonderful flavor!

name: stove top  roasted  red potatoes
review: It isn't often my family agrees on something, but my sometimes picky crew all gave these five stars! I checked the farmers market for potatoes, but no large ones were to be found. So I estimated and bought 2 small baskets of small and medium sized red potatoes. I figure, if you're cutting them all to bite size pieces, it really shouldn't make a difference. I may have doubled the basil, I got side tracked and couldn't remember if I had added it so I threw it in (maybe for the second time?) Also, I grabbed the oregano instead of parsley. But even with all of my distracted cooking moments, they still turned out great. I did cook them longer than called for in hopes to keep them crispy while the burgers were finishing on the grill. DH has already said were making these again. This recipe is a keeper for sure!

name: pork chops with lime   mayo
review: These were delicious! I made a couple changes to amp up the flavor, adding the zest of the lime to the mayo, and sprinkling the pork chops with salt and pepper before grilling.

name: mediterranean turkey meatball sandwiches  pita or wrap
review: SO good! I left the peels on my cucumbers and used Greek yogurt so it would be more of a tzatziki sauce. Served it on naan bread with quartered mini heirloom tomatoes. Wonderful meal!

name: garlic and oregano stove top chicken
review: Really good, juicy and flavorful. Made exactly as written.

name: cracker barrel green chili jack chicken
review: Quite good. I salted the chicken tenders along with the chili powder, and I used re-hydrated freeze dried green chilies, plus a sprinkling of dried cilantro.

name: olive garden chicken scampi  yummy    copycat
review: Delicious! Made just as written except I used regular flour and salted the chicken before coating it in the flour.

name: jolean s cheese potato   smoked sausage casserole
review: I cubed my potatoes before cooking. While the potatoes were cooking I cooked the sausage (I used a vegetarian sausage because we have both vegetarian and carnivores in our family.) This came together quite easily and everyone enjoyed it. Steamed broccoli would be the perfect side to this dish.

name: creamy santa fe chicken and rice
review: I made this and baked it up in a 9 x 13 pan. It turned out pretty good but felt it could have used a little more flavor. My family suggested adding black beans, cumin, more garlic and maybe a sprinkle of shredded cheese on top.

name: oven roasted potatoes with garlic and rosemary
review: I let the potatoes sit for twenty minutes in the oil mixture. Next time I will go with the two hours. They just didn't have enough flavor for us. Will update when we try them again.

name: creamy pumpkin pasta
review: My family thought this was kind of bland. The sauce was very thin but that may have been because I used fresh pumpkin puree, which is much thinner than canned. I ended up cooking some hot Italian sausage links and slicing them up to add to the top of this.

name: yummy yogurt marinated chicken
review: Doubled the minced garlic, as we are a family of garlic lover, this is the norm for us when making a recipe. The family said this had wonderful flavor with just a touch of heat. Our grill runs hot, even on low. But the chicken didn't dry out using this marinade.

name: grilled balsamic eggplant
review: I used fresh herbs and skipped the sugar. Surprising amount of flavor for the amount of the marinade and the time it is in it. I had thin eggplants so I only cut them in half lengthwise. They were done in about 10 minutes.

name: pinto bean   ground beef casserole
review: I don't eat beef, but I made this for my family. I followed the recipe exactly and they gave it 3 stars. They said it was good but didn't have as much flavor as they would have liked. Next time I may use Rotel instead of stewed tomatoes. Once they doctored up, they liked it much butter. They used hot sauce, salsa, sour cream, additional shredded cheese to give it some additional flavor. They would give it an additional star with the additions. Reading the other reviews, it seems like everyone made additions or changes to fit their tastes. I would use this as a great base recipe, then personalize it and make it your own.

name: self rising cornmeal
review: I couldn't find self rising cornmeal and wanted to try a recipe that called for it. Thank goodness I found this. It saved the day and I was able to make the recipe I wanted.

name: garlic roasted asparagus with parmesan
review: Roasting asparagus seems to bring out different flavors than when you steam it. My family likes it both ways. We are all garlic lovers, so this seemed like the natural choice when looking for asparagus recipes. It was enjoyed by all.

name: zucchini and ground beef casserole
review: This was simple and delicious. Fits our low carb diet perfectly. Made as written but reduced cumin a bit . Thanks for the recipe!

name: picadas  pinched masa tartlets
review: Not sure what went wrong. My masa dough was too crumbly when I mixed the flour and water usung the amounts called for. So I added more warm water in small amounts until I could get it to hold together to roll the walnut shape balls. When I tried to flatten the dough balls they either crumbled apart or stuck to my hands. I gave up and made burritos instead.

name: pinto bean and pepper jack burritos 6 ww points
review: Made these with left over pintos from another meal, instead of canned pintos. I also used an extra egg, otherwise there were more beans than egg. This would be great for breakfast.

name: texas pinto beans
review: Made these for DH and he gave them four stars. I cooked them in the crock pot instead of on the stove top. Anything to try and keep the kitchen cooler on a hot July day. We used some of the extra beans in breakfast burritos and today in quesadillas.

name: cheese ravioli with pumpkin sage sauce
review: During the summer we usually get fresh handmade pastas from a couple at our Farmer's Market. Unfortunately, they were out of their cheese ravioli by the time we got there. I had to use Buitoni 4 cheese from the refrigerator section at the grocery store. I substituted broth for the wine, used the dried sage and also used homemade pumpkin puree instead of canned. We weren't crazy about the pine nuts and will probably leave them off next time. But, we will definitely be making this again!

name: easy crock pot salsa chicken
review: It doesn't get any easier. Throw everything in the crockpot and go. Served it over Mexican rice. The entire family liked it. A great week night meal!

name: bisquick sausage egg casserole
review: Every now and then we like to have breakfast food for dinner. I skipped the egg substitute and used all fresh eggs from a friend's chickens. It took the full 60 minutes to cook. We all enjoyed it, but think it would be even better with additional spices or chopped veggies.

name: easy moist banana blueberry muffins
review: These moist muffins have an excellent flavor, especially warm from the oven. I had the batter mixed up by the time the oven had preheated.

name: pasta with mushrooms  ham and peas
review: This recipe is great; I a recipe using ham and mushrooms; didn't have peas and subs with roasted red pepper; added garlic and served in on angel hair; it's a keeper; thanks.

name: chick pea salad
review: Another great summer salad perfect to be combined with grilled meat or other main dishes!   A bit of summer for Mediterranean food lovers! Thanks a lot for posting this recipe!

name: viennese spiced espresso
review: A must for all coffee lovers! Super fast and great result. Enjoy slowly please! Thanks for this recipe

name: rice with pine nuts and pistachios
review: Tasty and impressive rice with wonderful texture! Great side dish for Turkish dishes and much more! I've roasted the nuts while the rice was cooking, so no waste of time and superb presentation! Thanks a lot for this recipe!

name: green beans with tomato and honey
review: We enjoyed the sweetness and unusual spice combination of these beans. The subtle heat from the cayenne pepper was a nice surprise, too. Quick and easy to make, I used fresh green beans from my garden. **Made for 2017 Culinary Quest - Turkey for the Smok'in Chefs**

name: artichoke and pine nut pesto
review: I'm very glad I tried this recipe, it's very easy to be prepare and it was a great gem!

name: artichoke and pine nut pesto
review: We loved this! I served it with tri-color rotini and it was great. I did not adjust the texture because I thought mine was "wet" enough.

name: ethiopian tomato   cucumber salad
review: We love tomato and cucumber salads, but what makes this salad so wonderful is the addition of the hot pepper. It added a little kick that we really enjoyed. I used a large jalapeno, red onion, and the balsamic vinegar. This salad will be made often this summer. It's a great way to use up the excess tomatoes, cucumbers, and peppers that my garden is producing. **Made for 2017 Culinary Quest - Ethiopia for the Smok'in Chefs**

name: corn cooked in husks on the grill with chile lime butter
review: I love the simplicity of this dish and the delicious flavor of the chili and lime which are complementary to the corn. My grill was busy with chicken so i cooked it for a few minutes in the microwave, then after shucking rubbed it with a little butter and finished it off on the grill when the chicken was done. Made for CQ4 by one of the Spice Girls

name: beef pilau
review: This was great! This was super easy to make and the house smelled great while it was simmering away on the stove. I used more tomatoes just to use up the rest of the can and chose green beans. Made for Culinary Quest 2017 for the Smokin' Chefs. Thanks! :)

name: yogurt  date  and walnut parfait
review: I loved, loved, loved this! I eat a lot of yogurt, so I'm always looking for different add-ins to change it up. The dates, toasted walnuts, honey, and cinnamon in these parfaits were so delicious that I ate not one, but two in one sitting. I made as written, using Greek honey yogurt. This has become my new "favorite" way to eat yogurt. Thank you for sharing! **Made for 2017 Culinary Quest - Turkey for Smok'in Chefs**

name: austrian kaesespaetzle  cheese spaetzle
review: YUM! I love spaetzle and I'm always happy to break out my spaetzle maker. This was great! I prepared it as listed and it made a huge amount, which was fine by us. I did put the dish back in the oven for a bit to melt the cheese but that didn't take long. Made for CQ17 for the Smokin' Chefs. Thanks! :)

name: chick pea salad
review: We really enjoyed this delicious chick pea salad. I let it marinate for about 10 hours and the flavors were wonderful. I added extra red and green bell pepper and green onion. Also, I pitted and quartered the olives instead of halving them. Thank you for sharing! **Made for 2017 Culinary Quest - Turkey for Smok'in Chefs**

name: hummus with pine nuts turkish style
review: What a nice recipe for hummus! It is so easy to make. The only comment I have is that you really have to watch the pine nuts you toast for the garnish because they burn fast.

name: berbere spice mix
review: This spice mix is very good. The chili powder and paprika give food a beautiful color. I used it on some lamb chops and my husband was very impressed.

name: ethiopian potato salad
review: We really love this potato salad. I used the jalapenos and did not find them to be too hot at all.

name: healthy cinnamon cream cheese swirl bread  whole wheat
review: Recipe was wonderful. I used the full 2 oz cream cheese and used nice big blobs of cream cheese. I was worried it might cause a problem as it baked but it came out wonderful. I used mini loaf pans (I got 3 out of them) and baked for 25-28 min. You are right; cream cheese icing would be perfect on top! But it was wonderful plain, too!

name: hummus with a twist
review: That lemon juice took this to another level! I loved this recipe and it makes A LOT, which is good for us. I used 4 garlic cloves and that was plenty. I did use a bit more lemon juice and olive oil, just this make it a little creamier. We enjoyed this with a baguette and some naan bread. Thanks! :)

name: acili ezme  turkish style tomato dip condiment
review: This was really good and not too hot, as in spicy. I made this exactly as directed and it was enjoyed by allll! Thanks! :)

name: orange banana nut bread
review: Hi, I went to Taste of Home's website as well to look @ their reviews. One person said they increased the oil so I increased it just a bit as well (1/4 cup). I did not use the zest only b/c I didn't have any--and I left out the walnuts only b/c the bread was going to people that I wasn't sure would be allergic (gave to a friend to try with the idea she might share w/ co workers!). She said the bread tasted fabulous but she couldn't taste the orange part much. that may have been my fault for leaving out the zest; I may increase the juice to 1 cup to help that flavor next time. Thank you for sharing!!!

name: ethiopian tomato   cucumber salad
review: I could totally see this being a perfect side to grilled meats, but I liked it so much when I made it that I ended up eating this for lunch all by itself! I tried it immediately after making it, plus I tried some a couple hours later, and I ate the leftovers the next day. While it was good at all points, I think it tasted best a couple hours after making it. That way, the flavors had time to meld, but it wasn't so long that the tomatoes and cukes were getting soggy. I used the red wine vinegar and a Serrano for the pepper. Thanks for posting, Dreamer, and sorry for the not-so-hot cellphone photo, lol! Made for CQ2017 Ethiopia

name: dill chicken breasts
review: What a great dish for a hot summer night, light and refreshing. I used 2% milk as I did not have cream and it was still fabulous. I will definitely double the yummy sauce next time. Thanks for a great recipe.

name: kaiserschmarrn with peaches
review: Yum , this made a lovely late evening dinner. I cut the recipe to 2 serving which I ate all of! (I don't think half would have been quits a full serving) . This is a dense pancake which has the slight taste of a sweet omelette. I loved the caramelized peach and berries mixed in with the pancake and only wished I had used a larger peach. The directions were very clear and easy to follow. Made for Culinary Quest 4 by one of the Spice Girls

name: turkish green bean salad
review: We really enjoyed that flavors in this dish.

name: ispanak kavurma  turkish spinach
review: We loved this spinach. I am always looking for different cooked spinach recipes. My husband loves a spinach salad, but I do not. He always buys too much, so I get to cook some for me!

name: one pan mongolian beef zoodles
review: Really tasty! There was a bit too much liquid, probably released from the zucchini once it started cooking. I'd either use only 1/4 cup water in the sauce, or salt the zoodles to draw the water off before adding them.

name: tequila grilled chicken
review: I made this for the family. They liked it but wished it had more flavor. Next time I will marinade overnight.

name: curried yam and mango over basmati rice
review: Who would have thought that mango and yams would go together? Well, they do! The seasoning was good in this and the ginger gave it such a good kick. I made this on a bed of basmati rice and it was gobbled up in no time. Thanks! :)

name: cranberry scones
review: This was a tasty breakfast treat. I love the tart cranberries with the spice of the cloves. The recipe calls for a lot of cloves, I really like clove but it can be overwhelming and it gives me heartburn so I cut it way back and added a little cinnamon to balance, the flavor was nicely subtle and had the perfect background flavor. I did find the texture a little heavy and based on the proportions of other scones I make I would probably add more baking powder next time to see it it would lighten them up a bit. I sprinkled some cinnamon sugar on top before baking, whipped cream was perfect with them. Made for Culinary Quest 4 for the Spice Girls.

name: garam masala chicken
review: We loved this quick and easy chicken dish. I used 3 large chicken breasts and cut them into pieces instead of leaving them whole. Also, I sauteed the chicken in garlic infused olive oil for added flavor. Next time I would double the sauce ingredients, it was our favorite part of the dish. **Made for 2017 Culinary Quest - Himalayas for Smok'in Chefs**

name: cauliflower curry
review: We loved this flavorful way of preparing cauliflower. I used 2 tsp. cumin seed and approx. 1 tsp of chili powder. The flavor combination of the spices were delicious. The cilantro on the top was a must. **Made for 2017 Culinary Quest - Himalayas for Smok'in Chefs. **

name: tandoori spice mix
review: This is a very earthy spice mix that would be good on anything. I used it to season a couple of steaks.

name: lentil soup with cumin and lemon
review: OMG this is a really delicious soup! I loved all the healthy ingredients. I would say the lemon juice could be optional, but for me, it really made the soup that extra special. It was also so filling that my husband only needed one bowl instead of his usual two.

name: farmer s omelet
review: We really loved this filling, delicious omelet. I've never had peas in an omelet before, but they worked really well with the mushrooms, bacon, and potates. I made it in my cast iron skillet and after adding the eggs, I cooked it on the stovetop until the bottom was set. I then put it under the broiler to finish cooking. I ate my plain, but my hubby put salsa on his (I doubt the Welsh do this). **Made for 2017 Culinary Quest - Wales for the Smok'in Chefs**

name: baked chicken tenders
review: Tasty! Not crispy, but we were okay with that.

name: baked salmon fish sticks
review: The salmon needed to be salted first. I'll do that next time. Also, 15 minutes was plenty of cook time. Good with a homemade lemon dill aoli.

name: the emperor s slow cooked chicken  crock pot
review: I thought this was just okay. Could have used some more flavor.

name: microwave fried rice
review: Surprisingly good! Not the same as fried rice, but quite tasty. I used freeze dried peas, carrots, onion, and corn, and just added a little extra water. I also added some rice vinegar, chopped garlic, and salt.

name: easy pizza soup or dressed up tomato soup
review: Surprisingly good! I used freeze dried tomato powder instead of the soup. Added garlic and onion powder, and Italian seasoning. Then I used fresh mozzarella chopped small.

name: ww mustard baked chicken  5 points
review: Really tasty.

name: turkey  porcupine meatballs
review: These were good and easy. Served with a cucumber salad.

name: microwave cabbage soup
review: This was good, very simple. I ended up adding a bit of hot sauce. I also used a preshredded cabbage/carrot cole slaw mix.

name: rustic chicken stew
review: We loved, loved, loved this hearty stew! So easy to make with ingredients that I already had on hand. The chunky vegetables and chicken made this a very filling dinner. I increased the chicken broth and cream a little to give the stew more liquid. I topped this with "Nif's Easy Baking Powder Dumplings recipe #351297. Thank you for sharing this wonderful recipe...it is definitely a keeper! **Made for 2017 Culinary Quest - Wales for Smok'in Chefs**

name: nif s easy baking powder dumplings  crock pot or stove top
review: These dumplings are quick and easy to make, and they are so delicious! I used fresh chives from my garden instead of the parsley. I served these on top of "Rustic Chicken Stew" recipe #413657. This will be my "go to" dumpling recipe. **Made for 2017 Culinary Quest - Wales for Smok'in Chefs**

name: chicken with garden gravy
review: This was a very tasty comfort food kind of meal. I pan roasted the chicken on top of the stove and used chicken breasts only. The chicken came out very moist and flavorful I used green beans, extra clove of garlic, butter not margarine. I had a partial can of low sodium chicken broth in the fridge So I used it in place of the bullion. I wanted just a little bit more liquid so used a little half and half so I didn't have to open another can of broth. Made for Culinary Quest 4 by one of the Spice Girls

name: fresh apple cake  optional   with brown sugar icing
review: I prepared to cakes with this quantity: a bunt cake of about 9 inches (for give away) and a smaller rectangular one for us. After 40 minutes I reduced the heat (air forced oven) from 350°F to about 300°F to prevent surface to turn to dark. The cake was fantastic: juicy and at the same time the upper surface crunchy! A real keeper!

name: golden garlic mashed potatoes
review: We really enjoyed these potatoes, my husband especially, he's already asked me to make them again . we love good mashed potatoes and these fit the bill. Made for Culinary Quest 4 by one of the Spice Girls

name: apple ka halwa
review: What for a delicious dessert! I love the spices (especially the cardamom) and these give to the dish a real special taste. Very quick to be prepared and healthy! Thanks a lot for posting this delicious recipe!

name: exotic indian tangy rice
review: Mmmm. Nice and fragrant, I loved this rice. My husband did not. What does he know anyway?

name: tandoori marinade
review: This is a delicious we used it as a marinade for grilled shrimp . I only had about 30 minutes to let is marinate , I can't wait until I can let it set even longer. Made for Culinary Quest 4 by one of the Spice Girls.

name: tasty tandoori  sweet potatoes
review: Sweet potatoes are so good for you that it is nice to have another way to make them. We love the savory-sweet contrast.

name: yummy cheddar muffins
review: These were very flavorful and moist muffins I reduced the onion a little to about 2 TBLS for a half recipe , it's still pretty dominant but good with the cheese. I might use all green onion next time . Made for Culinary Quest 4 by one of the Spice Girls.

name: sear roasted salmon with lemon ginger butter
review: We love salmon and the tang of ginger lemon butter was a nice compliment to the richness of the salmon. I cooked my salmon on top of the stove as I didn't want to heat up the kitchen with the oven. I used the traditional NW method of cooking it skin side down in the skillet until the fish is mostly done, then briefly searing the top. It came out moist and lovely . Made for Culinary Quest 4 by one of the Spice Girls.

name: moist roasted whole chicken
review: Thank you so much for this wonderful recipe! This was my first time roasting a whole chicken. I upped your seasonings a bit because I had a bigger bird, but that's all I did. It baked for about 1 hour 50 min. I used the Internet for some additional instructions to help me--like patting the bird dry, and I tented the bird with foil since it needed additional cooking time (since it was fairly browned). Thanks so much for sharing.

name: cheesy pinto beans
review: I made this for dinner tonight. I did add extra garlic, which I always do when making a recipe, as we are a family of garlic lovers. We didn't care for the crushed tortilla chips on top. They soaked up the juices and we didn't care for the texture. Next time I will leave them off and adjust the ingredients to give this a little more heat.

name: blueberries and cream pie with no roll pie crust
review: Delicious! I typically avoid rolled pie crusts like the plague, so this press-in-pan version was perfect for me! I misread the amount of sugar for the crust, so I added a tablespoon instead of a teaspoon, but it turned out just fine. My pie dish was a little too shallow to hold everything without overflow, so I just took one of those disposable foil pizza pans and cupped it around the pie dish to catch any spillage. I didn't have time to make the fresh whipped cream, so I just served this with some canned whipped cream instead. It's pretty messy if you don't chill it long enough (which I didn't), but it was super-tasty even though it wasn't entirely cohesive. My coworker and I (the only 2 people who have tried it yet) both give it two thumbs up. Thanks for posting! Made for CQ 2017 Wales

name: stilton stuffed eggs
review: These eggs were great and made a satisfying lunch.

name: new potato salad for a crowd
review: I made 1/4 of this recipe and it made more than 4 of us could eat! I love dill pickles so I'd probably double of triple the amount of them next time. So good and a great addition to the smorgasbord. Thanks!

name: mustard dill sauce   to serve with salmon
review: This was a very easy sauce to make and very good with cod too! It would actually be great with any seafood and even chicken. I used a really grainy dijon mustard (personal preference) and forgot to set some dill aside for the top but it went to good use in the mixture. Thanks!

name: broiled fish with dill butter
review: I love fish and this was a great way to cook it! I would use a bit more dill and cayenne because they added a great overall flavour. Thanks PanNan!

name: braised red cabbage with apples   scandanavia
review: Fantastic recipe that cooked itself. Good thing because I was making so many dishes that this one was on the stove a little longer than it should have been but it was perfect! I wouldn't change a thing about this recipe and it was so good with all of the other dishes. Thanks!

name: scandinavian spinach pancakes  pinaattiohukaiset
review: We loved these! I thought that 2 tbsp of batter per pancake sounded like way too little but it was perfect because it spread out nicely, without my help. They are almost like crepes and the ultimate topping was an equal mix of sour cream and jelly. Thanks!

name: pan roasted cauliflower with pine nuts  garlic and rosemary
review: I made this for dinner tonight. While I don't typically care for cauliflower, I enjoyed this. Husband thought it was "okay" and unfortunately, no one else liked it. Guess I know what I am taking to work for lunch tomorrow.

name: moroccan rack of lamb
review: Outstanding! My DH cooked the lamb over the bbq to perfection! My guests raved about this dish! Kudos to a great find!!!

name: carne picada con tocino  fajitas with bacon and onion
review: I loved the speediness and simplicity in preparing this recipe. The meat was a little bland for our tastes, so I added some cumin and garlic salt, as well as lots of salt and pepper. I served it with corn tortillas, avocado salsa, chunky guacamole, and 4-cheese Mexican blend cheese. It made a very yummy, satisfying meal. **Made for 2017 Culinary Quest - Central America for Smok'in Chefs**

name: slow cooker london broil
review: This was pretty good. I pulled the meat out of the sauce and sliced it up with the sauce on the side for dipping if people wanted it.

name: wallumbilla crustless quiche
review: Really good. Whole family loved it. I just used broccoli, nice and simple.

name: pannbiff med lok   meat patties with onions
review: These are super-flavorful and delicious. I intended to serve them with a cream sauce, as suggested, but they didn't need it. I don't usually like "fillers" in my chopped meat, but this was perfect.

name: best ever chunky guacamole
review: We loved this delicious guacamole. I had never had bacon in guacamole before, and it was a yummy addition. I used 2 cloves of garlic and extra cumin, as well as salt and black pepper. I also added a pinch of granulated sugar to offset the tartness from the lime. I served this with Carne Asada tacos. **Made for 2017 Culinary Quest - Central America for Smok'in Chefs**

name: english muffin topped with tarragon egg and smoked salmon
review: Lovely! I just added a bit of dijon mustard on the English muffins, and some salt in the eggs.

name: strawberry thyme butter
review: This is really good. The strawberries turn out to not be very sweet at all. I put it on everything.

name: simple saute scallops
review: Very good. I added a bit of parsley and lemon zest, as well as salting the scallops.

name: nacho s in a cup
review: Really good and easy.

name: diana s avocado salsa
review: Delicious salsa! We loved the combination of flavors in this salsa. I made it as written, except I only used 2 jalapenos instead of 3. I love spicy food, but my hubby, not so much and I had to keep him happy. I served this with Carne Asada tacos. **Made for 2017 Culinary Quest - Central America for Smok'in Chefs **

name: country potato pie
review: This couldn't be easier to make and with ingredients most people have on hand.

name: danish blue cheese pimento spread
review: This is a beautiful and fancy looking recipe, but still very easy. You might want to spread it on toast, but I put it on a grilled strip steak. Tomorrow it is destined to find a place on a baked potato. If there is any left, maybe I'll drag out some rye crisps.

name: super simple smoked salmon crostini
review: My husband surprised me with bagels. I surprised him with this.

name: baba ganoush   the best in the world
review: This is WONDERFUL! I followed the instructions for mashing it to get the correct consistency. I roasted the garlic cloves, and topped with toasted pine nuts in addition to the oil, parsley, and olives. The kalamata olives really add to the flavor!

name: grilled caribbean chicken with pineapple salsa
review: So delicious! The marinade gives the chicken great flavor and kept it moist. The onion in the salsa was a little strong, I might use a sweet onion next time. I used a whole chicken cut in half. Made for Culinary Quest

name: vafler med sitronsmak   norway    lemon waffles
review: Great waffles! the lemon was light but present. i served them with whipped cream and lingon berry jam which brought out the lemon. I made a half recipe which made not quite 8 squares on a traditional 4 square waffle maker. Made for CQ4

name: horseradish meatloaf
review: Yummy meatloaf. It was moist and flavorful, the horseradish gave it a nice spark . Made for CQ4

name: farmer s pork chops
review: This recipe was a winner! We really loved the moist pork chops and the creamy potatoes. There was only two of us eating, so I only used 4 pork chops but I made the entire amount of potatoes. I made this in a 9 x 13" baking dish and microwaved the potato mixture for 10 minutes. I used fresh chives from my garden, and baked the dish for 1 hour. Yummy!! **Made for 2017 Culinary Quest - Scandinavia for Smok'in Chefs**

name: pollo pendejo  foolproof chicken
review: I needed something to pack for dinner at work, so I made sandwiches out of this. I used multi grain flatbread wraps, American cheese, lettuce, pickles, tomato and a little bit of honey chipotle mustard (I warmed the wrap/chicken/cheese in the microwave at work, and added all the cold veggies afterwards). For the chicken, I let it marinate overnight before cooking it. I didn't have light beer, so I used Modelo instead. Once the chicken was fully cooked, I removed it from the sauce and continued to simmer the sauce for a while to reduce it and thicken it up (didn't want the chicken to get overcooked). Very tasty chicken, and versatile, too! Thanks for posting this keeper! Made for CQ 2017 Central America

name: salpicn de res  central american shredded beef salad
review: So good! I used skirt steak for the beef, and I added one chopped cucumber and a handful of chopped green olives to this. Instead of using the lime wedges for garnish, I just squeezed the juice from one lime into the salad, and I mixed in some chopped cilantro as well. Little bit spicy, little bit tangy, and very fresh tasting. The only thing I would do differently next time is either use a different cut of beef, or cook the skirt steak longer to make it a bit more tender. This was perfect for lunch as a tostada topping. Probably gonna make a pot of soup from the leftover beef broth, too. I'll definitely be making this again, thanks for posting! Made for CQ 2017 Central America

name: mom s easy kahlua brownies
review: I made these for my bunco group last night. They were good and super easy, but the Kahlua flavor really didn't come through. Not sure if you could add more and still have them firm up when they bake. I made a Kahlua whipped cream to go on top of them this time. Next time, like another review suggested, I may brush additional Kahlua on the top as soon as they come out of the oven. Luckily they worked out fine for my bunco group because I didn't know that two of the people there don't like Kahlua, so it was good that they couldn't taste it.

name: chocolate banana chocolate chip bundt cake
review: I liked this cake very much. I substituted agave nectar for the brown sugar and found the cake turned out dense, but very moist. Very good.

name: simple thai style lemongrass shrimp soup
review: I made this for dinner last night as we are all battling colds. This warmed us up and the spice helped unclog our sinuses. But a couple family members complained to was too spicy so I will cut back on the chilies or chili paste next time. I used half water and half vegetable broth for the base but other wise followed the directions. I didn't count out the shrimp so there may have been more than what was called for.

name: southwestern bean salad
review: Great salad

name: roasted beet salad with horseradish cream dressing
review: I made just the beets and horseradish cream as a salad. Very, very good. I, like other reviewers, kept adding more horseradish to get it to the level of zing I was looking for. Very earthy with fresh beets, the first time I had ever roasted them. Surprising and very good texture and taste.

name: best albondigas soup
review: Wonderful soup, the meatballs are great! I didn't realize I was out of diced tomatoes which I usually keep on hand, so used a can of tomato sauce and it was still so good.

name: breadstick broomsticks
review: So fun and easy! My store was out of breadsticks that weren't pre-baked, so I used some pre-made whole wheat pizza dough. I think it actually worked better for giving a broomstick shape because I had more control over the size and thickness. Although our friends all thought they were chicken feet!

name: lazy cottage pie
review: Super easy. I used instant mashed potatoes, should have mixed some seasonings into it, but the beef and peas had great flavor from the soup.

name: pissaladiere  provencal onion tart
review: This was SO tasty. I love olives and anchovies, so this was perfect for me. I used whole wheat pizza dough from the store to save time.

name: ham  zucchini   pumpkin risotto
review: Delicious and easy! Lots of stirring time but still simple to make. Only change I made was to toast the rice in the butter first, then add the wine. Toasting the rice heats up the grain’s exterior (toast until the rice is hot to the touch and the color should remain pearly white, not turn brown) and helps the rice to absorb the liquids slowly with becoming soggy.

name: grilled italian marinated swordfish
review: Very good recipe. I used halibut steaks which have similar flavor to swordfish, but are much MUCH lower in mercury.

name: sausage and red bean stew
review: I used sweet Italian chicken sausage. I skipped the cayenne so the kids would like it, then hubby and I added hot sauce to our bowls. Wonderful easy soup!

name: creamy chicken and pumpkin pasta  ww
review: This was SO good! Wonderful flavors, creamy sauce. The olives are a great salty balance to the sweet sauce. I seasoned the chicken with salt and pepper before cooking, and did the same to the pumpkin and tomatoes after cooking.

name: broccoli and tortellini salad
review: Wonderful salad! My grocery delivery accidentally brought sunflower seeds in the shell, so I subbed walnuts for them and loved the extra crunch they gave.

name: warm lemongrass shrimp
review: I made this for dinner. It is a mild flavored dish. I doubled the garlic and probably would add more garlic and shallots next time I make it. I also didn't care for the texture of the lemongrass, but liked the flavor it added.

name: cheesy chicken  broccoli   rice casserole   no canned soups
review: Really good; did omit the thyme. Always on the lookout for a casserole without the soup.

name: lemongrass chicken
review: My family was divided on this recipe. Half liked it, half did not. I made it using the fish sauce option.

name: hot fudge pudding cake
review: I found this recipe on Cooks Illustrated! It was delicious and well received by the friends. I would consider cutting the recipe in half as it is quite rich and you only need a little bit! I found it was the perfect amount of sugar! Next time I would do it in ramekins! The ice cream is the perfect accompaniment!

name: curried rice and artichoke salad
review: So glad you posted this where I could find it! This is a family favorite that my mother-in-law used to make. It is a great salad to make with primarily pantry items that are always on hand - and it's delicious!! Thanks MeemawB!!

name: roast turkey  easy steps for new cooks
review: Love the flavor of the butter under the skin!

name: fresh blueberry cobbler
review: So very easy & super delicious!!!

name: ole  authentic chiles rellenos
review: I would give this 6 stars if I could! It's a lot of work, but the end result is truly authentic and so flavorful. I think a stick of cheese is easier than shredded, but shredded works well too. The brine is really important for the flavors. Definitely making this again!

name: no bake turkey cake
review: This turned out SO cute! Super easy, took about 10 minutes. Bring everything with you and assemble it wherever you're going.

name: green chicken chili
review: We loved this easy, flavorful chili. My anaheim chiles were "huge" so it turned out quite spicy, but very yummy. I used the entire can of corn and didn't drain either the corn or the beans. I cooked it in my 4-qt. crockpot for 2 hours on the "high" setting and 4 hours on "low". After the cooking was done, I turned the cooker back up to "high" and stirred in a slurry of masa harina flour and water to thicken the chili. I adjusted the spices adding more cumin and salt and also some garlic powder. I served it with softened corn tortillas and topped it with sour cream and 4-cheese Mexican blend. The following morning, I used the leftover chili to make huevos rancheros using corn tortillas, refried beans, fried eggs, the chili, sour cream and cheese...delicious! Thank you for sharing this wonderful recipe...it is definitely a keeper! **Made for 2017 Football Pool**

name: the bergy burger
review: I don't normally use steak sauce so I made a homemade Heinz 57 type for my burger. Awesome. I will make my burger like this again. Great combination of flavors and heat to however you want it.

name: healthy cocoa chocolate chip banana pancakes
review: Hi, thanks for this amazing recipe. I think I might add a bit more sugar as I needed more sweetness, and add a bit of cinnamon just for the flavor profile. Thank you!

name: ex mother in law s pork chops with cream of mushroom
review: Amazing. Been enjoying this recipe since I was a kid.Even the leftovers are to die for. I skipped the browning altogether. This is the ONLY recipe I use.

name: white trash hamburger gravy and breakfast biscuits
review: I made this on 10/16/17 for mine and my SO's dinner,and most importantly for Potsie's COOK A THON. Since there was just two of us the recipe was reduced by half ,except for the amount of sausage that remained the same. Instead of serving it over biscuits, I put mine over Fried Potatoes. And it was a wonderful guilty pleasure,which will be made again. No tweaking was needed, perfect as written.Thanks for posting Potsie, and " Keep Smiling :) "

name: anchovy and caper salad dressing
review: This was delicious. It had all the flavours I enjoy and I knew I would love it before I tasted it. Thank you Potsie for posting a yummy recipe. Get Well Soon. x

name: mustard salad dressing
review: This dressing is just yummy, I much prefer to make my own dressing then pre-made bottled ones, that contain lots of nasty preservatives. For cooks who aren't use to the kitchen, I think with seasoning it's personal taste. Less salt and pepper or more salt and pepper, you choose. I chose to add just a pinch to bring the flavours up. Thank you Potsie for another great recipe.

name: don t get crabby with me salad  crab louis
review: Yum! I made two versions of this recipe. One exactly as written (but I had to use can crab meat, its hard to find fresh ones in my area). I also tweaked the recipe and substituted the cream to coconut cream to make it OK for me to eat and used prawns/shrimp. I also omitted the boiled egg. This dressing could be used not only as crab salad but a seafood salad. Its so good! Thank you Potsie for posting your recipe.

name: famous butter chicken
review: I've had my eye on this recipe for years. I used thinly sliced chicken breast s and they cooked in about 35 minutes. I liked how this turned out.

name: baked apple doughnuts for abm
review: I agree, more like a bagel texture than donut, but SO delicious! I ended up making a glaze with maple extract and powdered sugar to drizzle over them as well.

name: chicken breasts with attitude
review: On 10/23/17 I made this for mine and my SO's dinner,but most importantly made it for the " Down Home Cooking " tag game in FF&F. Just like breezermom I couldn't find the Roasted Garlic & Onion Soup mix,so I just used regular Onion Soup Mix. I made a HUGE mistake and accidentally used the whole package, so I certainly didn't add the Sea Salt. Other than that the recipe was made as written. My SO thought it was o.k. but I liked it. :) Thanks so much for taking the time to post this recipe and, " Keep Smiling :) "

name: pumpkin cupcakes
review: I made this using fresh pureed pumpkin that I had in the freezer instead of canned. I have done muffins using just the pumpkin and the spice cake mix. They are excellent but more dense than when you add the eggs and oil. I frosted half with a cream cheese whipped icing and the other half with a cream cheese buttercream icing.

name: the best braciole
review: This was just incredible! Made as written. AMAZING!

name: knoephla soup
review: Wonderful soup! We have a large German and Norwegian community in South Dakota as well, and there are many, many versions of this soup. I used this as a base, then added what my husband and I liked - a bit of sour cream for me, and a bit a apple cider vinegar for him. We both had delightfully full tummy's and leftovers for lunch! Thank you my dear friend HPJ. I will make this again very soon!

name: beef gravy
review: Thank you so much for this recipe; it came in SO handy when I needed beef gravy for a recipe and I was out of the jarred kind. Came out wonderful and the directions were great. Will this work for chicken or turkey gravy; just subbing the type of broth?

name: cranberry wild rice pilaf
review: Really good recipe for fall entertaining.

name: bacon wrapped scallops with cream sauce
review: Incredible! Made as written except for adding some chopped parsley for color before serving. Beautiful and amazing flavor!

name: lina s apple pie dessert cups
review: Fun and easy. Wonton cups are a little tough to bite due to sharp corners, but it's a tasty pretty treat.

name: caramelized onion cranberry cream cheese bites
review: SO tasty! Great party appetizer. I served it on wheat thins.

name: dried cranberries and squash
review: Delicious! My squash were REALLY big, I think maybe the recipe is for the super small individual sized squash. So I doubled the cranberry filling with cinnamon butter. Love the way the cranberries get a caramel flavor to them with the broiling.

name: blue ribbon stuffed mushrooms
review: Out of this world delicious! I used Johnstonviile breakfast sausage patties, I remembered large stuffing mushrooms. Sorry Potsie, but I didn’t remember that the recipe called for white mushrooms. I used teenage portabellas. Everything was super yummy! DH and I ate all but three. Made for the GW Cookathon.

name: balsamic roasted onions
review: These were so good and so filling that it was the only side dish we needed. There were some leftovers, and were easily warmed after a couple of days, but it wasn't the same.

name: sheila s best  balsamic dressing
review: This dressing is so quick and easy to make, and very yummy, too! I love that it uses ingredients that I always have on hand. I used a local olive oil company's balsamic vinegar and olive oil. I often use their flavored balsamic vinegars in my salad dressings, so I can't wait to try them with this recipe. Thank you for sharing this wonderful recipe...it is definitely a keeper. **Made for 2017 Football Pool**

name: slow cooker ranch mushrooms
review: I've made these twice within the last couple of days. I don't use my slow cooker though, I bake them uncovered at 350 for about 30 minutes. So good that I have been using this as a side dish. I will be making this a lot and will think of Sharon when I do.

name: shazam  chinese soup
review: Such a warming up kind and feel good kind of soup. I love the zing the ginger and sesame oil gives, and it uses up the vegetables I have in the fridge.

name: slow cooker ranch mushrooms
review: Such a clever and easy recipe! I used crimini mushrooms as suggested. The mushrooms taste delicious and they are good both hot or cold. I sliced them and used them as a side to lamb chops. I will be making these again and again. Made in memory of Sharon123, an amazing Chef and friend.

name: pumpkin seeds
review: I had just under 2 Tablespoons of butter, so I added a drizzle of olive oil. I also used a garlic salt & pepper blend instead of plain salt. I did have to roast them an extra ten minutes, but they turned out fine. The best part of the kids carving pumpkins is the roasted pumpkin seeds!

name: rissole potatoes
review: I made this recipe 11/5/17 for mine and my SO's dinner, and most importantly for a Cook- A- Thon honoring the memory of Kit..ty of Canada( Jeanette Grieve). Except for not peeling the potatoes the recipe was made as it was written. I thought this was a nice change from regular potatoes. In my opinion, there's no need to change a single thing about this recipe. " Keep Smiling :) "

name: cranberry syrup
review: Delicious!

name: delicious roast chicken  or turkey  cornish hens  etc
review: Perfection!

name: louisiana sweet potato french toast with pecan honey butter
review: So so SO good!

name: mini shrimp cocktail appetizers
review: Easy and tasty.

name: kato s tasty salmon cream cheese surprise
review: What a fantastic recipe. I have to admit that I did not make this myself, but I did eat it—lots of it—when we were visiting twissis in Iceland (see her review). She made it as part of our before-dinner spread of snacks. We really enjoyed the mix of flavours and were also surprised by how well the maple syrup complimented the other ingredients. Definitely a keeper.

name: winter fruit salad with lemon poppy seed dressing
review: Delicious salad, love the dressing! I left the peels on the apple and pear, and swapped the shredded cheese for feta and the cashews for hazelnuts since we had those on hand and our family prefers them.

name: smoked salmon pancakes
review: I'm surprised no one else mentioned the overwhelming taste of baking soda in the pancakes! The salmon and horseradish cream were wonderful, but the baking soda aftertaste from the pancakes was too strong. We ended up just moving the salmon and cream to some wheat thins instead. If I were to make this again I'd just do 2 teaspoons of baking powder and skip the baking soda.

name: taco or fajita seasoning  chipotle or ancho
review: We used this to season vegetarian Quorn tenders then added mushrooms, onions and assorted bell peppers. It made for some pretty tasty fajitas.

name: scarecrow chicken sticks
review: Good and easy. Used unsweetened coconut flakes to reduce sugar, and went with the mayo rather than ranch. Still delicious!

name: crock pot beef roast
review: Good and easy, only 35 minutes cook time on the meat setting on my Instant Pot.

name: twice baked mashed potatoes
review: This was good, but I had to make it a couple times to get just right. Found it worked well with refrigerated mashed potatoes from Costco, and baking it 45 minutes to get it nice and golden. I waited until the last 10 minutes of cooking to add the cheese on top. Then topped with green onions, bacon, and fresh ground pepper.

name: smoked ham salad on gruyere potato coins
review: These are delicious! Skipped the tarragon because I'm not a fan.

name: carrot latkes
review: Good, fun way to eat carrots.

name: turkey breakfast burritos
review: Really good! Added some sage, green onion, and cilantro.

name: cocoa buttermilk cake
review: Oh my goodness, this cake is out of the world. Twissis made it for us when we visited her and we all had a giant piece slathered with vanilla ice cream. Can't wait to make this at home. A sure fire winner in every way.

name: spaghetti with red wine sauce
review: I had a friend that was wanting a wine bottle for a craft project and an opened bottle of wine in the fridge. So I made this for dinner to use up the wine. Because it was opened, I was short a little on the wine, but I just used a little of the pasta water. I did have to add more of the pasta water as it cooked down. I also added extra garlic, which is a must in this house. Perfect week night meal. I had all the ingredients on hand. It was quick and easy to make and everyone enjoyed it.

name: herb and cheese biscuit bites
review: Good and so easy.

name: weight watchers parmesan crusted chicken schnitzels
review: Good flavor!

name: sweet kugel
review: Best kugel I've tried! I used dried cranberries instead of raisins for a pop of color.

name: pear   gorgonzola salad
review: SO pretty and really good!

name: snickerdoodle biscotti
review: SO delicious! I made them as written, then dipped them in melted chocolate and sprinkles for some fun color.

name: chicken cakes with avocado mayonnaise and tomato salsa
review: Oh my goodness these were SO good! The chicken patties taste a lot like bacon, which was good to us! I made as written except for adding the juice of one lemon to the avocado mayo.

name: jamie olivers pasta carbonara
review: Thought this was just okay. Made it as written but it was too pasta heavy for us, without enough flavor. I would cut the noodle amount in half, and add some garlic. I liked the peas and mint though.

name: uncle bill s fried potatoes and onions
review: Didn't realize that we were out of Dill until the potatoes were already cooking. So, we just left it out. It did take a lot longer than ten minutes for the potatoes to cook. But when they were finally done, they were pretty darn tasty!

name: fiesta chicken with jalapeno cilantro creme
review: Oh my goodness, this is a sensational recipe for chicken. I had to make a couple of little changes. I didn't have garlic powder on hand, so used a garlic–ginger paste to cover both ingredients. As an aside, the recipe doesn't say when to add the ginger. I put the garlic–ginger paste in with the egg mixture and that worked fine. I didn't have a fresh jalapeno, so used a pickled one, seeds included. Australia has huge chicken breasts so I made this with two (weight a kilo or 2 pounds). Because my pieces were quite thick, I fried them for 12 minutes (6 a side) and then finished them in the oven. A truly wonderful recipe that will be repeated often.

name: tasty tandoori  sweet potatoes
review: We love sweet potatoes and this is a fantastic way to serve them. I followed the recipe as written, using just a touch more tandoori paste. Yum, yum, yummo!

name: pasta with shrimp and wine
review: I had an opened bottle of wine that I needed to use up. I used angel hair pasta and followed the recipe with one exception. I used 3 bouillon cubes instead of a teaspoon of granules. It was okay, but felt that it needed a little something more. We all ended up adding a couple of twists of the garlic salt & pepper seasoning grinder and topped it with more Parmesan cheese. That seemed to do the trick!

name: roasted pumpkin seeds with a kick from kim
review: Next time I may add a tablespoon of olive oil to the butter for better flavor.

name: double the streusel coffee cake
review: It was very good, but next time I will make it in a 8" square pan instead of an 9"spring form. It came out too thin for my taste. Thanks for sharing.

name: jiffy corn casserole  5 ingredients  easy   delicious
review: This was good, especially given how easy it was to make. I made half the recipe, using the creamed corn and no whole corn. Baked in a small casserole for 45 minutes or so - i think it could have gone longer. I might like to try adding some herbs or spices to up the flavor interest. Still, pretty darn good.

name: baked sweet potatoes from a crock pot
review: An excellent way to cook sweet potatoes. I put a sheet of parchment paper at the bottom of my slow cooker, to catch any juices that exude. They were perfect.

name: west african chicken yassa
review: Great contrast of the super sweet onions and the sour lemon juice. Really good!

name: candy sleighs
review: Cute and easy! The kids loved helping me make them.

name: crock pot holiday dressing
review: We used poultry seasoning instead of poultry magic. We weren't crazy about it, but maybe that's because of that change, so I'm not giving it a star rating.

name: chicken scarpariello   rachael ray
review: Very good!

name: doro wat  ethiopian spicy braised chicken
review: Delicious!

name: 2bleu s cheese blintzes
review: DELICIOUS!

name: easy turkey chili   crock pot
